{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781143421403,"sessionID":"ses_14b95d46bffeZ6ztCn3DXZD284","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_ef4GY4GsjdDIT4pa7h9uSANy","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/save.md","offset":1,"limit":140},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/save.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: description: Save current conversation context into canonical spec-doc continuity surfaces with semantic indexing\n3: argument-hint: \"<spec-folder>\"\n4: allowed-tools: Read, Edit, Bash, Task, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_save, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_update\n5: ---\n6: \n7: # /memory:save\n8: \n9: Thin router for canonical continuity saves.\n10: \n11: ## 1. ROUTING ASSETS\n12: \n13: | Asset | Path | Status | Purpose |\n14: | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n15: | Workflow | _No memory workflow YAML exists in this checkout_ | Missing upstream asset | Keep routing in this file until a workflow YAML is introduced by a separate workflow-asset change. Do not invent or edit YAML from this command. |\n16: | Presentation | `.opencode/commands/memory/assets/save_presentation.md` | Required | Startup questions, save dashboards, result envelopes, trigger-edit display, and error rendering. |\n17: \n18: Before rendering any prompt, dashboard, or result block, read the presentation asset and follow it as the display source of truth.\n19: \n20: ## 2. ROUTER CONTRACT\n21: \n22: Inputs:\n23: - `$ARGUMENTS` may contain an explicit spec folder.\n24: - If `$ARGUMENTS` is empty, resolve the active spec folder using Gate 3 carry-over first, session file evidence second, and a targeted user question only when ambiguous.\n25: \n26: Outputs:\n27: - Default response is a save plan: target route, proposed edits, blockers, advisories, and follow-up actions.\n28: - Explicit apply/full-auto may run `node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js` with AI-authored JSON.\n29: - Immediate retrieval freshness may use `memory_index_scan({ specFolder, includeSpecDocs: true, force: false })` after the save.\n30: \n31: ## 3. WORKFLOW ROUTING\n32: \n33: 1. Resolve and validate `target_folder`.\n34: 2. Check topic/folder alignment and stop for confirmation on mismatch.\n35: 3. Extract session summary, key decisions, modified files, trigger phrases, technical context, tool calls, and notable exchanges.\n36: 4. Choose route category: `narrative_progress`, `narrative_delivery`, `decision`, `handover_state`, `research_finding`, `task_update`, `metadata_only`, or `drop`.\n37: 5. In default mode, return the save plan without mutating.\n38: 6. In explicit apply/full-auto mode, execute the canonical save script, inspect the post-save quality review, patch HIGH issues when practical, then refresh index visibility through MCP.\n39: 7. Render the result using the presentation asset.\n40: \n41: ## 4. HARD RULES\n42: \n43: - Do not use standalone `memory/*.md` files as save destinations.\n44: - Do not claim an automatic hook save unless current hook evidence proves it.\n45: - Do not open raw SQLite or edit memory DB files.\n46: - Do not create or modify workflow YAML from this command.\n47: - Use `/memory:manage retention-sweep` for retention cleanup.\n48: \n49: ## 5. TOOL MAP\n50: \n51: | Need | Tool or Script |\n52: | --- | --- |\n53: | Canonical save apply | `node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js` |\n54: | Immediate index refresh | `mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan` |\n55: | Single-file indexing fallback | `mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_save` |\n56: | Trigger phrase correction | `mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_update` |\n57: \n58: ## 6. RELATED COMMANDS\n59: \n60: - `/memory:search`: Intent-aware context retrieval and analysis tools.\n61: - `/memory:manage`: Database management, checkpoints, ingest, retention, and health.\n62: - `/memory:learn`: Constitutional rules.\n63: - `/speckit:resume`: Session recovery and continuation.\n\n(End of file - total 63 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ndescription: Save current conversation context into canonical spec-doc continuity surfaces with semantic indexing\nargument-hint: \"<spec-folder>\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Edit, Bash, Task, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_save, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_update\n---\n\n# /memory:save\n\nThin router for canonical continuity saves.\n\n## 1. ROUTING ASSETS\n\n| Asset | Path | Status | Purpose |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| Workflow | _No memory workflow YAML exists in this checkout_ | Missing upstream asset | Keep routing in this file until a workflow YAML is introduced by a separate workflow-asset change. Do not invent or edit YAML from this command. |\n| Presentation | `.opencode/commands/memory/assets/save_presentation.md` | Required | Startup questions, save dashboards, result envelopes, trigger-edit display, and error rendering. |\n\nBefore rendering any prompt, dashboard, or result block, read the presentation asset and follow it as the display source of truth.\n\n## 2. ROUTER CONTRACT","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/save.md","text":"---\ndescription: Save current conversation context into canonical spec-doc continuity surfaces with semantic indexing\nargument-hint: \"<spec-folder>\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Edit, Bash, Task, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_save, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_update\n---\n\n# /memory:save\n\nThin router for canonical continuity saves.\n\n## 1. ROUTING ASSETS\n\n| Asset | Path | Status | Purpose |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| Workflow | _No memory workflow YAML exists in this checkout_ | Missing upstream asset | Keep routing in this file until a workflow YAML is introduced by a separate workflow-asset change. Do not invent or edit YAML from this command. |\n| Presentation | `.opencode/commands/memory/assets/save_presentation.md` | Required | Startup questions, save dashboards, result envelopes, trigger-edit display, and error rendering. |\n\nBefore rendering any prompt, dashboard, or result block, read the presentation asset and follow it as the display source of truth.\n\n## 2. ROUTER CONTRACT\n\nInputs:\n- `$ARGUMENTS` may contain an explicit spec folder.\n- If `$ARGUMENTS` is empty, resolve the active spec folder using Gate 3 carry-over first, session file evidence second, and a targeted user question only when ambiguous.\n\nOutputs:\n- Default response is a save plan: target route, proposed edits, blockers, advisories, and follow-up actions.\n- Explicit apply/full-auto may run `node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js` with AI-authored JSON.\n- Immediate retrieval freshness may use `memory_index_scan({ specFolder, includeSpecDocs: true, force: false })` after the save.\n\n## 3. WORKFLOW ROUTING\n\n1. Resolve and validate `target_folder`.\n2. Check topic/folder alignment and stop for confirmation on mismatch.\n3. Extract session summary, key decisions, modified files, trigger phrases, technical context, tool calls, and notable exchanges.\n4. Choose route category: `narrative_progress`, `narrative_delivery`, `decision`, `handover_state`, `research_finding`, `task_update`, `metadata_only`, or `drop`.\n5. In default mode, return the save plan without mutating.\n6. In explicit apply/full-auto mode, execute the canonical save script, inspect the post-save quality review, patch HIGH issues when practical, then refresh index visibility through MCP.\n7. Render the result using the presentation asset.\n\n## 4. HARD RULES\n\n- Do not use standalone `memory/*.md` files as save destinations.\n- Do not claim an automatic hook save unless current hook evidence proves it.\n- Do not open raw SQLite or edit memory DB files.\n- Do not create or modify workflow YAML from this command.\n- Use `/memory:manage retention-sweep` for retention cleanup.\n\n## 5. TOOL MAP\n\n| Need | Tool or Script |\n| --- | --- |\n| Canonical save apply | `node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js` |\n| Immediate index refresh | `mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan` |\n| Single-file indexing fallback | `mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_save` |\n| Trigger phrase correction | `mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_update` |\n\n## 6. RELATED COMMANDS\n\n- `/memory:search`: Intent-aware context retrieval and analysis tools.\n- `/memory:manage`: Database management, checkpoints, ingest, retention, and health.\n- `/memory:learn`: Constitutional rules.\n- `/speckit:resume`: Session recovery and continuation.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":63,"totalLines":63,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/commands/memory/save.md","time":{"start":1781143421398,"end":1781143421403}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0751d83c14c6e763016a2a177d51c08191a3607250b9e589ca"}},"id":"prt_eb46bc1ae001VBSYc4INCF3Gba","sessionID":"ses_14b95d46bffeZ6ztCn3DXZD284","messageID":"msg_eb46b983e001Ogrz7OUheKx8sn"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781143421422,"sessionID":"ses_14b95d46bffeZ6ztCn3DXZD284","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_SznrqSNFAZKw3YXgWfpaNblV","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/search.md","offset":1,"limit":140},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/search.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: description: Unified continuity retrieval: spec-doc search, baselines, memory causal graph, ablations, dashboards.\n3: argument-hint: \"<query> [--intent:<type>] | preflight <specFolder> <taskId> | postflight <specFolder> <taskId> | history <specFolder> | causal <memoryId> | link <sourceId> <targetId> <relation> | unlink <edgeId> | causal-stats | ablation | dashboard\"\n4: allowed-tools: Read, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_quick_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_match_triggers, mcp__mk_spec_memory__task_preflight, mcp__mk_spec_memory__task_postflight, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_drift_why, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_link, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_unlink, mcp__mk_spec_memory__eval_run_ablation, mcp__mk_spec_memory__eval_reporting_dashboard, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_get_learning_history\n5: ---\n6: \n7: # /memory:search\n8: \n9: Thin router for memory retrieval and analysis.\n10: \n11: ## 1. ROUTING ASSETS\n12: \n13: | Asset | Path | Status | Purpose |\n14: | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n15: | Workflow | _No memory workflow YAML exists in this checkout_ | Missing upstream asset | Keep retrieval and analysis routing in this file until a workflow YAML is introduced by a separate workflow-asset change. Do not invent or edit YAML from this command. |\n16: | Presentation | `.opencode/commands/memory/assets/search_presentation.md` | Required | Startup question policy, analysis overview, result tables, empty-result fallback, and clean GPT-via-opencode display rules. |\n17: \n18: Before asking startup questions or displaying results, read the presentation asset and use it as the display source of truth.\n19: \n20: ## 2. STARTUP ROUTING\n21: \n22: If `$ARGUMENTS` is empty, ask one open-ended question from the presentation asset. Do not dump the full intent/menu list at startup. Treat a custom answer as the retrieval query.\n23: \n24: If the first token is an analysis subcommand, route to analysis mode.\n25: \n26: Known analysis subcommands:\n27: - `preflight`\n28: - `postflight`\n29: - `history`\n30: - `causal`\n31: - `link`\n32: - `unlink`\n33: - `causal-stats`\n34: - `ablation`\n35: - `dashboard`\n36: \n37: Any other non-empty input routes to retrieval mode. Parse optional `--intent:<type>`; otherwise let the server or local router infer intent from the query.\n38: \n39: ## 3. RETRIEVAL MODE\n40: \n41: 1. Extract `query` and optional intent override.\n42: 2. Prefer `memory_context({ input: query, mode: \"auto\", intent, includeContent: true, enableDedup: true })`.\n43: 3. Use `memory_quick_search` for fast query-only fallback.\n44: 4. Use `memory_search` only when fine-grained search parameters are needed.\n45: 5. Use `memory_match_triggers` as a supplemental fallback, not as a replacement for direct retrieval.\n46: 6. For structural code questions, use the stable code-graph tools before semantic or lexical memory channels when available.\n47: 7. Render compact, parseable output using the presentation asset.\n48: \n49: Supported intents:\n50: - `add_feature`\n51: - `fix_bug`\n52: - `refactor`\n53: - `security_audit`\n54: - `understand`\n55: - `find_spec`\n56: - `find_decision`\n57: \n58: ## 4. ANALYSIS MODE\n59: \n60: | Subcommand | Tool | Purpose |\n61: | --- | --- | --- |\n62: | `preflight <specFolder> <taskId>` | `task_preflight` | Capture epistemic baseline. |\n63: | `postflight <specFolder> <taskId>` | `task_postflight` | Capture learning delta. |\n64: | `history <specFolder>` | `memory_get_learning_history` | Show learning cycles. |\n65: | `causal <memoryId>` | `memory_drift_why` | Trace decision lineage. |\n66: | `link <sourceId> <targetId> <relation>` | `memory_causal_link` | Create causal relation. |\n67: | `unlink <edgeId>` | `memory_causal_unlink` | Remove causal relation. |\n68: | `causal-stats` | `memory_causal_stats` | Show graph coverage. |\n69: | `ablation` | `eval_run_ablation` | Run channel ablation when enabled. |\n70: | `dashboard` | `eval_reporting_dashboard` | Show evaluation trends. |\n71: \n72: ## 5. HARD RULES\n73: \n74: - Do not infer a query from prior conversation when `$ARGUMENTS` is empty; ask the open-ended startup question.\n75: - Ask targeted follow-up questions only when the query is genuinely ambiguous.\n76: - Do not display the old option dump at startup.\n77: - Do not use forbidden memory/result labels listed in the presentation asset.\n78: - Do not open raw SQLite or edit memory DB files.\n79: - Do not create or modify workflow YAML from this command.\n80: \n81: ## 6. RELATED COMMANDS\n82: \n83: - `/memory:save`: Save conversation context.\n84: - `/memory:manage`: Database management, checkpoints, ingest, retention, and health.\n85: - `/memory:learn`: Constitutional rules.\n86: - `/speckit:resume`: Session recovery and continuation.\n\n(End of file - total 86 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ndescription: Unified continuity retrieval: spec-doc search, baselines, memory causal graph, ablations, dashboards.\nargument-hint: \"<query> [--intent:<type>] | preflight <specFolder> <taskId> | postflight <specFolder> <taskId> | history <specFolder> | causal <memoryId> | link <sourceId> <targetId> <relation> | unlink <edgeId> | causal-stats | ablation | dashboard\"\nallowed-tools: Read, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_quick_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_match_triggers, mcp__mk_spec_memory__task_preflight, mcp__mk_spec_memory__task_postflight, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_drift_why, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_link, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_unlink, mcp__mk_spec_memory__eval_run_ablation, mcp__mk_spec_memory__eval_reporting_dashboard, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_get_learning_history\n---\n\n# /memory:search\n\nThin router for memory retrieval and analysis.\n\n## 1. ROUTING ASSETS\n\n| Asset | Path | Status | Purpose |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| Workflow | _No memory workflow YAML exists in this checkout_ | Missing upstream asset | Keep retrieval and analysis routing in this file until a workflow YAML is introduced by a separate workflow-asset change. Do not invent or edit YAML from this command. |\n| Presentation | `.opencode/commands/memory/assets/search_presentation.md` | Required | Startup question policy, analysis overview, result tables, empty-result fallback, and clean GPT-via-opencode display rules. |\n\nBefore asking startup questions or displaying results, read the presentation asset and use it as the display source of truth.\n\n## 2. STARTUP ROUTING","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/search.md","text":"---\ndescription: Unified continuity retrieval: spec-doc search, baselines, memory causal graph, ablations, dashboards.\nargument-hint: \"<query> [--intent:<type>] | preflight <specFolder> <taskId> | postflight <specFolder> <taskId> | history <specFolder> | causal <memoryId> | link <sourceId> <targetId> <relation> | unlink <edgeId> | causal-stats | ablation | dashboard\"\nallowed-tools: Read, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_quick_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_match_triggers, mcp__mk_spec_memory__task_preflight, mcp__mk_spec_memory__task_postflight, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_drift_why, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_link, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_unlink, mcp__mk_spec_memory__eval_run_ablation, mcp__mk_spec_memory__eval_reporting_dashboard, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_get_learning_history\n---\n\n# /memory:search\n\nThin router for memory retrieval and analysis.\n\n## 1. ROUTING ASSETS\n\n| Asset | Path | Status | Purpose |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| Workflow | _No memory workflow YAML exists in this checkout_ | Missing upstream asset | Keep retrieval and analysis routing in this file until a workflow YAML is introduced by a separate workflow-asset change. Do not invent or edit YAML from this command. |\n| Presentation | `.opencode/commands/memory/assets/search_presentation.md` | Required | Startup question policy, analysis overview, result tables, empty-result fallback, and clean GPT-via-opencode display rules. |\n\nBefore asking startup questions or displaying results, read the presentation asset and use it as the display source of truth.\n\n## 2. STARTUP ROUTING\n\nIf `$ARGUMENTS` is empty, ask one open-ended question from the presentation asset. Do not dump the full intent/menu list at startup. Treat a custom answer as the retrieval query.\n\nIf the first token is an analysis subcommand, route to analysis mode.\n\nKnown analysis subcommands:\n- `preflight`\n- `postflight`\n- `history`\n- `causal`\n- `link`\n- `unlink`\n- `causal-stats`\n- `ablation`\n- `dashboard`\n\nAny other non-empty input routes to retrieval mode. Parse optional `--intent:<type>`; otherwise let the server or local router infer intent from the query.\n\n## 3. RETRIEVAL MODE\n\n1. Extract `query` and optional intent override.\n2. Prefer `memory_context({ input: query, mode: \"auto\", intent, includeContent: true, enableDedup: true })`.\n3. Use `memory_quick_search` for fast query-only fallback.\n4. Use `memory_search` only when fine-grained search parameters are needed.\n5. Use `memory_match_triggers` as a supplemental fallback, not as a replacement for direct retrieval.\n6. For structural code questions, use the stable code-graph tools before semantic or lexical memory channels when available.\n7. Render compact, parseable output using the presentation asset.\n\nSupported intents:\n- `add_feature`\n- `fix_bug`\n- `refactor`\n- `security_audit`\n- `understand`\n- `find_spec`\n- `find_decision`\n\n## 4. ANALYSIS MODE\n\n| Subcommand | Tool | Purpose |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| `preflight <specFolder> <taskId>` | `task_preflight` | Capture epistemic baseline. |\n| `postflight <specFolder> <taskId>` | `task_postflight` | Capture learning delta. |\n| `history <specFolder>` | `memory_get_learning_history` | Show learning cycles. |\n| `causal <memoryId>` | `memory_drift_why` | Trace decision lineage. |\n| `link <sourceId> <targetId> <relation>` | `memory_causal_link` | Create causal relation. |\n| `unlink <edgeId>` | `memory_causal_unlink` | Remove causal relation. |\n| `causal-stats` | `memory_causal_stats` | Show graph coverage. |\n| `ablation` | `eval_run_ablation` | Run channel ablation when enabled. |\n| `dashboard` | `eval_reporting_dashboard` | Show evaluation trends. |\n\n## 5. HARD RULES\n\n- Do not infer a query from prior conversation when `$ARGUMENTS` is empty; ask the open-ended startup question.\n- Ask targeted follow-up questions only when the query is genuinely ambiguous.\n- Do not display the old option dump at startup.\n- Do not use forbidden memory/result labels listed in the presentation asset.\n- Do not open raw SQLite or edit memory DB files.\n- Do not create or modify workflow YAML from this command.\n\n## 6. RELATED COMMANDS\n\n- `/memory:save`: Save conversation context.\n- `/memory:manage`: Database management, checkpoints, ingest, retention, and health.\n- `/memory:learn`: Constitutional rules.\n- `/speckit:resume`: Session recovery and continuation.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":86,"totalLines":86,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/commands/memory/search.md","time":{"start":1781143421419,"end":1781143421422}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0751d83c14c6e763016a2a177d51d481919616cb9d83c4c054"}},"id":"prt_eb46bc1d8001XfC3VM0qHlxMqv","sessionID":"ses_14b95d46bffeZ6ztCn3DXZD284","messageID":"msg_eb46b983e001Ogrz7OUheKx8sn"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781143421433,"sessionID":"ses_14b95d46bffeZ6ztCn3DXZD284","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_yOL2VaWzCxtAokGt7aVlSn4R","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/manage.md","offset":1,"limit":140},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/manage.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: description: Manage indexed-continuity DB: stats, scan, cleanup, retention, validate, checkpoint, ingest.\n3: argument-hint: \"[scan [--force]] | [cleanup] | [retention-sweep [--dry-run]] | [bulk-delete <tier> [--older-than <days>] [--folder <spec>]] | [tier <id> <tier>] | [triggers <id>] | [validate <id> <useful|not>] | [delete <id>] | [health] | [checkpoint <subcommand>] | [ingest <subcommand>]\"\n4: allowed-tools: Read, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_list, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_validate, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_update, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_delete, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_bulk_delete, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_retention_sweep, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_health, mcp__mk_spec_memory__checkpoint_create, mcp__mk_spec_memory__checkpoint_restore, mcp__mk_spec_memory__checkpoint_list, mcp__mk_spec_memory__checkpoint_delete, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_ingest_start, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_ingest_status, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_ingest_cancel\n5: ---\n6: \n7: # /memory:manage\n8: \n9: Thin router for indexed-continuity database management.\n10: \n11: ## 1. ROUTING ASSETS\n12: \n13: | Asset | Path | Status | Purpose |\n14: | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n15: | Workflow | _No memory workflow YAML exists in this checkout_ | Missing upstream asset | Keep management routing in this file until a workflow YAML is introduced by a separate workflow-asset change. Do not invent or edit YAML from this command. |\n16: | Presentation | `.opencode/commands/memory/assets/manage_presentation.md` | Required | Stats, scan, cleanup, retention, tier, trigger, validation, delete, health, checkpoint, ingest, and error displays. |\n17: \n18: Before rendering any dashboard, confirmation prompt, or result block, read the presentation asset and follow it as the display source of truth.\n19: \n20: ## 2. ROUTER CONTRACT\n21: \n22: Default mode is `stats` when `$ARGUMENTS` is empty.\n23: \n24: Recognized modes:\n25: - `stats`\n26: - `scan [--force]`\n27: - `cleanup`\n28: - `retention-sweep [--dry-run]`\n29: - `bulk-delete <tier> [--older-than <days>] [--folder <spec>]`\n30: - `tier <id> <tier>`\n31: - `triggers <id>`\n32: - `validate <id> <useful|not>`\n33: - `delete <id>`\n34: - `health`\n35: - `checkpoint create|restore|list|delete <name>`\n36: - `ingest start|status|cancel ...`\n37: \n38: On an unknown mode, return `STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"Unknown mode: <mode>\"` and list the valid modes.\n39: \n40: ## 3. WORKFLOW ROUTING\n41: \n42: | Mode | Primary Tooling | Confirmation |\n43: | --- | --- | --- |\n44: | `stats` | `memory_stats` plus `memory_list` | No |\n45: | `scan` | `memory_index_scan` | Yes |\n46: | `cleanup` | `memory_list`, `checkpoint_create`, `memory_delete` | Yes |\n47: | `retention-sweep` | `memory_retention_sweep` | Yes for mutating sweep |\n48: | `bulk-delete` | `memory_bulk_delete` | Yes |\n49: | `tier` | `memory_update` | No |\n50: | `triggers` | `memory_update` | User saves explicitly |\n51: | `validate` | `memory_validate` | No |\n52: | `delete` | `memory_delete` | Yes |\n53: | `health` | `memory_health` | No |\n54: | `checkpoint` | checkpoint tools | Restore/delete require confirmation |\n55: | `ingest` | ingest tools | Cancel requires explicit job id |\n56: \n57: ## 4. HARD RULES\n58: \n59: - Never query the database with Bash or raw `sqlite3`.\n60: - All database access goes through the allowed MCP tools.\n61: - Do not fall back to raw SQL when MCP fails; report the MCP error and operator fallback guidance.\n62: - Protected tiers require the confirmation gates described in the presentation asset.\n63: - Do not create or modify workflow YAML from this command.\n64: \n65: ## 5. RELATED COMMANDS\n66: \n67: - `/memory:search`: Intent-aware context retrieval and analysis tools.\n68: - `/memory:save`: Save conversation context.\n69: - `/memory:learn`: Constitutional rules.\n70: - `/speckit:resume`: Session recovery and continuation.\n\n(End of file - total 70 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ndescription: Manage indexed-continuity DB: stats, scan, cleanup, retention, validate, checkpoint, ingest.\nargument-hint: \"[scan [--force]] | [cleanup] | [retention-sweep [--dry-run]] | [bulk-delete <tier> [--older-than <days>] [--folder <spec>]] | [tier <id> <tier>] | [triggers <id>] | [validate <id> <useful|not>] | [delete <id>] | [health] | [checkpoint <subcommand>] | [ingest <subcommand>]\"\nallowed-tools: Read, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_list, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_validate, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_update, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_delete, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_bulk_delete, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_retention_sweep, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_health, mcp__mk_spec_memory__checkpoint_create, mcp__mk_spec_memory__checkpoint_restore, mcp__mk_spec_memory__checkpoint_list, mcp__mk_spec_memory__checkpoint_delete, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_ingest_start, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_ingest_status, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_ingest_cancel\n---\n\n# /memory:manage\n\nThin router for indexed-continuity database management.\n\n## 1. ROUTING ASSETS\n\n| Asset | Path | Status | Purpose |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| Workflow | _No memory workflow YAML exists in this checkout_ | Missing upstream asset | Keep management routing in this file until a workflow YAML is introduced by a separate workflow-asset change. Do not invent or edit YAML from this command. |\n| Presentation | `.opencode/commands/memory/assets/manage_presentation.md` | Required | Stats, scan, cleanup, retention, tier, trigger, validation, delete, health, checkpoint, ingest, and error displays. |\n\nBefore rendering any dashboard, confirmation prompt, or result block, read the presentation asset and follow it as the display source of truth.\n\n## 2. ROUTER CONTRACT","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/manage.md","text":"---\ndescription: Manage indexed-continuity DB: stats, scan, cleanup, retention, validate, checkpoint, ingest.\nargument-hint: \"[scan [--force]] | [cleanup] | [retention-sweep [--dry-run]] | [bulk-delete <tier> [--older-than <days>] [--folder <spec>]] | [tier <id> <tier>] | [triggers <id>] | [validate <id> <useful|not>] | [delete <id>] | [health] | [checkpoint <subcommand>] | [ingest <subcommand>]\"\nallowed-tools: Read, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_list, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_validate, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_update, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_delete, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_bulk_delete, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_retention_sweep, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_health, mcp__mk_spec_memory__checkpoint_create, mcp__mk_spec_memory__checkpoint_restore, mcp__mk_spec_memory__checkpoint_list, mcp__mk_spec_memory__checkpoint_delete, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_ingest_start, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_ingest_status, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_ingest_cancel\n---\n\n# /memory:manage\n\nThin router for indexed-continuity database management.\n\n## 1. ROUTING ASSETS\n\n| Asset | Path | Status | Purpose |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| Workflow | _No memory workflow YAML exists in this checkout_ | Missing upstream asset | Keep management routing in this file until a workflow YAML is introduced by a separate workflow-asset change. Do not invent or edit YAML from this command. |\n| Presentation | `.opencode/commands/memory/assets/manage_presentation.md` | Required | Stats, scan, cleanup, retention, tier, trigger, validation, delete, health, checkpoint, ingest, and error displays. |\n\nBefore rendering any dashboard, confirmation prompt, or result block, read the presentation asset and follow it as the display source of truth.\n\n## 2. ROUTER CONTRACT\n\nDefault mode is `stats` when `$ARGUMENTS` is empty.\n\nRecognized modes:\n- `stats`\n- `scan [--force]`\n- `cleanup`\n- `retention-sweep [--dry-run]`\n- `bulk-delete <tier> [--older-than <days>] [--folder <spec>]`\n- `tier <id> <tier>`\n- `triggers <id>`\n- `validate <id> <useful|not>`\n- `delete <id>`\n- `health`\n- `checkpoint create|restore|list|delete <name>`\n- `ingest start|status|cancel ...`\n\nOn an unknown mode, return `STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"Unknown mode: <mode>\"` and list the valid modes.\n\n## 3. WORKFLOW ROUTING\n\n| Mode | Primary Tooling | Confirmation |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| `stats` | `memory_stats` plus `memory_list` | No |\n| `scan` | `memory_index_scan` | Yes |\n| `cleanup` | `memory_list`, `checkpoint_create`, `memory_delete` | Yes |\n| `retention-sweep` | `memory_retention_sweep` | Yes for mutating sweep |\n| `bulk-delete` | `memory_bulk_delete` | Yes |\n| `tier` | `memory_update` | No |\n| `triggers` | `memory_update` | User saves explicitly |\n| `validate` | `memory_validate` | No |\n| `delete` | `memory_delete` | Yes |\n| `health` | `memory_health` | No |\n| `checkpoint` | checkpoint tools | Restore/delete require confirmation |\n| `ingest` | ingest tools | Cancel requires explicit job id |\n\n## 4. HARD RULES\n\n- Never query the database with Bash or raw `sqlite3`.\n- All database access goes through the allowed MCP tools.\n- Do not fall back to raw SQL when MCP fails; report the MCP error and operator fallback guidance.\n- Protected tiers require the confirmation gates described in the presentation asset.\n- Do not create or modify workflow YAML from this command.\n\n## 5. RELATED COMMANDS\n\n- `/memory:search`: Intent-aware context retrieval and analysis tools.\n- `/memory:save`: Save conversation context.\n- `/memory:learn`: Constitutional rules.\n- `/speckit:resume`: Session recovery and continuation.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":70,"totalLines":70,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/commands/memory/manage.md","time":{"start":1781143421427,"end":1781143421432}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0751d83c14c6e763016a2a177d51ec8191a602170434fa4f0f"}},"id":"prt_eb46bc1ec0011i9B0dJbNlWDA0","sessionID":"ses_14b95d46bffeZ6ztCn3DXZD284","messageID":"msg_eb46b983e001Ogrz7OUheKx8sn"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781143421516,"sessionID":"ses_14b95d46bffeZ6ztCn3DXZD284","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_peQigF7lVpQaCLpTW5w6hDTe","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/learn.md","offset":1,"limit":140},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/learn.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: description: Create and manage constitutional rules — always-surface entries that appear at the top of every search result.\n3: argument-hint: \"[rule-description] | list | edit <filename> | remove <filename> | budget\"\n4: allowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Glob, Bash, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_save, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_list, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_delete, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan\n5: ---\n6: \n7: # /memory:learn\n8: \n9: Thin router for constitutional rule management.\n10: \n11: ## 1. ROUTING ASSETS\n12: \n13: | Asset | Path | Status | Purpose |\n14: | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n15: | Workflow | _No memory workflow YAML exists in this checkout_ | Missing upstream asset | Keep constitutional-rule routing in this file until a workflow YAML is introduced by a separate workflow-asset change. Do not invent or edit YAML from this command. |\n16: | Presentation | `.opencode/commands/memory/assets/learn_presentation.md` | Required | Overview, list, budget, create, edit, remove, confirmation, and result displays. |\n17: \n18: Before rendering any dashboard, approval prompt, or result block, read the presentation asset and use it as the display source of truth.\n19: \n20: ## 2. ROUTER CONTRACT\n21: \n22: Destination: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/constitutional/`.\n23: \n24: Inputs:\n25: - Empty arguments route to overview.\n26: - `list` routes to constitutional rule list.\n27: - `budget` routes to token budget dashboard.\n28: - `edit <filename>` edits an existing constitutional rule.\n29: - `remove <filename>` removes an existing constitutional rule after confirmation.\n30: - Any other text is treated as a proposed new constitutional rule.\n31: \n32: Outputs:\n33: - `STATUS=OK ACTION=<overview|created|listed|edited|removed|budget>`\n34: - `STATUS=CANCELLED ACTION=<action>`\n35: - `STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"<message>\"`\n36: \n37: ## 3. WORKFLOW ROUTING\n38: \n39: 1. Parse `$ARGUMENTS` and choose one route.\n40: 2. For `edit` or `remove` without a filename, list available files and ask one targeted selection question.\n41: 3. For create, verify the rule qualifies as constitutional; suggest `/memory:save` for scoped/session context.\n42: 4. For create/edit/remove, preserve ANCHOR tags and frontmatter shape.\n43: 5. Index changes through `memory_save` or `memory_index_scan` as appropriate.\n44: 6. Verify constitutional visibility with `memory_search` when a new rule is created.\n45: 7. Render all displays from the presentation asset.\n46: \n47: ## 4. HARD RULES\n48: \n49: - Do not infer rule content from screenshots, open files, or prior conversation context.\n50: - Show generated constitutional rule content and wait for approval before writing a new rule.\n51: - For removal, validate filename is basename-only and wait for explicit confirmation.\n52: - Do not create or modify workflow YAML from this command.\n53: \n54: ## 5. RELATED COMMANDS\n55: \n56: - `/memory:search`: Intent-aware context retrieval and analysis tools.\n57: - `/memory:save`: Save conversation context.\n58: - `/memory:manage`: Database management, checkpoints, ingest, retention, and health.\n59: - `/speckit:resume`: Session recovery and continuation.\n\n(End of file - total 59 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ndescription: Create and manage constitutional rules — always-surface entries that appear at the top of every search result.\nargument-hint: \"[rule-description] | list | edit <filename> | remove <filename> | budget\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Glob, Bash, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_save, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_list, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_delete, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan\n---\n\n# /memory:learn\n\nThin router for constitutional rule management.\n\n## 1. ROUTING ASSETS\n\n| Asset | Path | Status | Purpose |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| Workflow | _No memory workflow YAML exists in this checkout_ | Missing upstream asset | Keep constitutional-rule routing in this file until a workflow YAML is introduced by a separate workflow-asset change. Do not invent or edit YAML from this command. |\n| Presentation | `.opencode/commands/memory/assets/learn_presentation.md` | Required | Overview, list, budget, create, edit, remove, confirmation, and result displays. |\n\nBefore rendering any dashboard, approval prompt, or result block, read the presentation asset and use it as the display source of truth.\n\n## 2. ROUTER CONTRACT","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/learn.md","text":"---\ndescription: Create and manage constitutional rules — always-surface entries that appear at the top of every search result.\nargument-hint: \"[rule-description] | list | edit <filename> | remove <filename> | budget\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Glob, Bash, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_save, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_list, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_delete, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan\n---\n\n# /memory:learn\n\nThin router for constitutional rule management.\n\n## 1. ROUTING ASSETS\n\n| Asset | Path | Status | Purpose |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| Workflow | _No memory workflow YAML exists in this checkout_ | Missing upstream asset | Keep constitutional-rule routing in this file until a workflow YAML is introduced by a separate workflow-asset change. Do not invent or edit YAML from this command. |\n| Presentation | `.opencode/commands/memory/assets/learn_presentation.md` | Required | Overview, list, budget, create, edit, remove, confirmation, and result displays. |\n\nBefore rendering any dashboard, approval prompt, or result block, read the presentation asset and use it as the display source of truth.\n\n## 2. ROUTER CONTRACT\n\nDestination: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/constitutional/`.\n\nInputs:\n- Empty arguments route to overview.\n- `list` routes to constitutional rule list.\n- `budget` routes to token budget dashboard.\n- `edit <filename>` edits an existing constitutional rule.\n- `remove <filename>` removes an existing constitutional rule after confirmation.\n- Any other text is treated as a proposed new constitutional rule.\n\nOutputs:\n- `STATUS=OK ACTION=<overview|created|listed|edited|removed|budget>`\n- `STATUS=CANCELLED ACTION=<action>`\n- `STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"<message>\"`\n\n## 3. WORKFLOW ROUTING\n\n1. Parse `$ARGUMENTS` and choose one route.\n2. For `edit` or `remove` without a filename, list available files and ask one targeted selection question.\n3. For create, verify the rule qualifies as constitutional; suggest `/memory:save` for scoped/session context.\n4. For create/edit/remove, preserve ANCHOR tags and frontmatter shape.\n5. Index changes through `memory_save` or `memory_index_scan` as appropriate.\n6. Verify constitutional visibility with `memory_search` when a new rule is created.\n7. Render all displays from the presentation asset.\n\n## 4. HARD RULES\n\n- Do not infer rule content from screenshots, open files, or prior conversation context.\n- Show generated constitutional rule content and wait for approval before writing a new rule.\n- For removal, validate filename is basename-only and wait for explicit confirmation.\n- Do not create or modify workflow YAML from this command.\n\n## 5. RELATED COMMANDS\n\n- `/memory:search`: Intent-aware context retrieval and analysis tools.\n- `/memory:save`: Save conversation context.\n- `/memory:manage`: Database management, checkpoints, ingest, retention, and health.\n- `/speckit:resume`: Session recovery and continuation.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":59,"totalLines":59,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/commands/memory/learn.md","time":{"start":1781143421514,"end":1781143421516}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0751d83c14c6e763016a2a177d51f48191b3c0d47685fabcfa"}},"id":"prt_eb46bc20d001lJDdTHJD4DCrxy","sessionID":"ses_14b95d46bffeZ6ztCn3DXZD284","messageID":"msg_eb46b983e001Ogrz7OUheKx8sn"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781143421522,"sessionID":"ses_14b95d46bffeZ6ztCn3DXZD284","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_xtlIsQPmw5hsPBuYMeeZqWD2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/speckit/plan.md","offset":1,"limit":140},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/speckit/plan.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: description: Planning workflow (8 steps): spec through plan only. Modes :auto, :confirm, :with-context, :with-phases.\n3: argument-hint: \"<feature-description> [:auto|:confirm] [:with-context] [:with-phases] [--intake-only] [--phases N] [--phase-names list] [--phase-folder=<path>] [--spec-folder=PATH] [--level=1|2|3|3+] [--start-state=STATE] [--repair-mode=MODE] [--record-relationships=yes|no] [--depends-on=IDs] [--related-to=IDs] [--supersedes=IDs] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\n4: allowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, memory_context, memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_save, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan\n5: ---\n6: \n7: # SpecKit Plan\n8: \n9: Thin router for the SpecKit planning workflow. This command resolves the execution mode, loads the presentation contract, then executes the owned workflow YAML.\n10: \n11: ## 1. Router Contract\n12: \n13: Do not dispatch agents from this Markdown file. Agent dispatch, workflow steps, and artifact-writing behavior are owned by the workflow YAML assets.\n14: \n15: Load the presentation contract before showing startup questions, checkpoints, dashboards, success output, failure output, or next-step prompts.\n16: \n17: ## 2. Owned Assets\n18: \n19: | Purpose | Asset |\n20: |---------|-------|\n21: | Presentation source of truth | `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_plan_presentation.md` |\n22: | Auto workflow | `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_plan_auto.yaml` |\n23: | Confirm workflow | `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_plan_confirm.yaml` |\n24: \n25: No workflow-asset gap exists for this command.\n26: \n27: ## 3. Mode Routing\n28: \n29: 1. Parse `$ARGUMENTS` for `:auto` or `:confirm`.\n30: 2. Treat `:with-context`, `:with-phases`, `--intake-only`, `--phases`, `--phase-names`, `--phase-folder`, `--spec-folder`, `--level`, `--start-state`, `--repair-mode`, and relationship flags as workflow inputs, not execution modes.\n31: 3. If no mode suffix is present, use the presentation contract's startup prompt to ask for execution mode.\n32: 4. For `:auto`, resolve required setup inputs using the presentation contract's auto-resolution rules before loading YAML.\n33: 5. Load the selected workflow asset and execute it step by step.\n34: \n35: ## 4. Execution Targets\n36: \n37: | Mode | Workflow |\n38: |------|----------|\n39: | `:auto` | `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_plan_auto.yaml` |\n40: | `:confirm` or interactive choice | `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_plan_confirm.yaml` |\n41: \n42: ## 5. Presentation Boundary\n43: \n44: The following content lives only in `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_plan_presentation.md`:\n45: \n46: - Startup-question wording and reply format.\n47: - `:auto` pre-bound setup answer schema, default table, targeted-ask rules, and fail-fast display.\n48: - Checkpoint and dashboard display templates, including deep-context and phase-decomposition checkpoints.\n49: - Success and failure result templates.\n50: - Next-step suggestions and final user prompt wording.\n51: \n52: ## 6. Workflow Summary\n53: \n54: The YAML workflow runs planning from intake through context refresh and terminates before implementation. If a user requests implementation after planning, route to `/speckit:implement`; do not start implementation from this command.\n\n(End of file - total 54 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ndescription: Planning workflow (8 steps): spec through plan only. Modes :auto, :confirm, :with-context, :with-phases.\nargument-hint: \"<feature-description> [:auto|:confirm] [:with-context] [:with-phases] [--intake-only] [--phases N] [--phase-names list] [--phase-folder=<path>] [--spec-folder=PATH] [--level=1|2|3|3+] [--start-state=STATE] [--repair-mode=MODE] [--record-relationships=yes|no] [--depends-on=IDs] [--related-to=IDs] [--supersedes=IDs] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, memory_context, memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_save, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan\n---\n\n# SpecKit Plan\n\nThin router for the SpecKit planning workflow. This command resolves the execution mode, loads the presentation contract, then executes the owned workflow YAML.\n\n## 1. Router Contract\n\nDo not dispatch agents from this Markdown file. Agent dispatch, workflow steps, and artifact-writing behavior are owned by the workflow YAML assets.\n\nLoad the presentation contract before showing startup questions, checkpoints, dashboards, success output, failure output, or next-step prompts.\n\n## 2. Owned Assets\n\n| Purpose | Asset |\n|---------|-------|","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/speckit/plan.md","text":"---\ndescription: Planning workflow (8 steps): spec through plan only. Modes :auto, :confirm, :with-context, :with-phases.\nargument-hint: \"<feature-description> [:auto|:confirm] [:with-context] [:with-phases] [--intake-only] [--phases N] [--phase-names list] [--phase-folder=<path>] [--spec-folder=PATH] [--level=1|2|3|3+] [--start-state=STATE] [--repair-mode=MODE] [--record-relationships=yes|no] [--depends-on=IDs] [--related-to=IDs] [--supersedes=IDs] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, memory_context, memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_save, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan\n---\n\n# SpecKit Plan\n\nThin router for the SpecKit planning workflow. This command resolves the execution mode, loads the presentation contract, then executes the owned workflow YAML.\n\n## 1. Router Contract\n\nDo not dispatch agents from this Markdown file. Agent dispatch, workflow steps, and artifact-writing behavior are owned by the workflow YAML assets.\n\nLoad the presentation contract before showing startup questions, checkpoints, dashboards, success output, failure output, or next-step prompts.\n\n## 2. Owned Assets\n\n| Purpose | Asset |\n|---------|-------|\n| Presentation source of truth | `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_plan_presentation.md` |\n| Auto workflow | `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_plan_auto.yaml` |\n| Confirm workflow | `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_plan_confirm.yaml` |\n\nNo workflow-asset gap exists for this command.\n\n## 3. Mode Routing\n\n1. Parse `$ARGUMENTS` for `:auto` or `:confirm`.\n2. Treat `:with-context`, `:with-phases`, `--intake-only`, `--phases`, `--phase-names`, `--phase-folder`, `--spec-folder`, `--level`, `--start-state`, `--repair-mode`, and relationship flags as workflow inputs, not execution modes.\n3. If no mode suffix is present, use the presentation contract's startup prompt to ask for execution mode.\n4. For `:auto`, resolve required setup inputs using the presentation contract's auto-resolution rules before loading YAML.\n5. Load the selected workflow asset and execute it step by step.\n\n## 4. Execution Targets\n\n| Mode | Workflow |\n|------|----------|\n| `:auto` | `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_plan_auto.yaml` |\n| `:confirm` or interactive choice | `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_plan_confirm.yaml` |\n\n## 5. Presentation Boundary\n\nThe following content lives only in `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_plan_presentation.md`:\n\n- Startup-question wording and reply format.\n- `:auto` pre-bound setup answer schema, default table, targeted-ask rules, and fail-fast display.\n- Checkpoint and dashboard display templates, including deep-context and phase-decomposition checkpoints.\n- Success and failure result templates.\n- Next-step suggestions and final user prompt wording.\n\n## 6. Workflow Summary\n\nThe YAML workflow runs planning from intake through context refresh and terminates before implementation. If a user requests implementation after planning, route to `/speckit:implement`; do not start implementation from this command.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":54,"totalLines":54,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/commands/speckit/plan.md","time":{"start":1781143421520,"end":1781143421521}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0751d83c14c6e763016a2a177d51fc8191847c7b0842667105"}},"id":"prt_eb46bc24f00157dFSfEL15Ctma","sessionID":"ses_14b95d46bffeZ6ztCn3DXZD284","messageID":"msg_eb46b983e001Ogrz7OUheKx8sn"}}
