 | Confirm workflow | `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_resume_confirm.yaml` |\n24: \n25: No workflow-asset gap exists for this command.\n26: \n27: ## 3. Mode Routing\n28: \n29: 1. Parse `$ARGUMENTS` for `:auto` or `:confirm`.\n30: 2. Treat `--phase-folder`, `--no-redirect`, and the positional spec-folder path as workflow inputs.\n31: 3. If no mode suffix is present, default to interactive mode unless the presentation contract's startup display says a confirmation is required.\n32: 4. For `:auto`, resolve required setup inputs using the presentation contract's auto-resolution rules before loading YAML.\n33: 5. Load the selected workflow asset and execute it step by step.\n34: \n35: ## 4. Execution Targets\n36: \n37: | Mode | Workflow |\n38: |------|----------|\n39: | `:auto` | `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_resume_auto.yaml` |\n40: | `:confirm` or default interactive choice | `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_resume_confirm.yaml` |\n41: \n42: ## 5. Presentation Boundary\n43: \n44: The following content lives only in `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_resume_presentation.md`:\n45: \n46: - Startup-question wording and reply format.\n47: - `:auto` pre-bound setup answer schema, default table, targeted-ask rules, and fail-fast display.\n48: - Session-selection, memory-depth, progress, stale-session, and continuation dashboards.\n49: - Resume brief and no-session result templates.\n50: - Related-command and next-step suggestions.\n51: \n52: ## 6. Workflow Summary\n53: \n54: The YAML workflow recovers the smallest safe continuation packet from canonical artifacts first, enriches only when needed, calculates progress, and presents one next safe action.\n\n(End of file - total 54 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ndescription: Resume or recover work on a spec folder: canonical continuity recovery with one next step.\nargument-hint: \"[spec-folder-path] [:auto|:confirm] [--phase-folder=<path>] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, memory_context, memory_search, memory_match_triggers, memory_list, memory_stats, memory_delete, memory_update, memory_validate, memory_index_scan, memory_health, checkpoint_create, checkpoint_list, checkpoint_restore, checkpoint_delete\n---\n\n# SpecKit Resume\n\nThin router for resuming or recovering work on an existing SpecKit packet. This command resolves mode and target folder, loads the presentation contract, then executes the owned workflow YAML.\n\n## 1. Router Contract\n\nDo not dispatch agents from this Markdown file. Session detection, continuity loading, progress calculation, recovery depth, and continuation behavior are owned by the workflow YAML assets.\n\nLoad the presentation contract before showing startup questions, checkpoints, dashboards, resume briefs, stale-session warnings, or next-step prompts.\n\n## 2. Owned Assets\n\n| Purpose | Asset |\n|---------|-------|","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/speckit/resume.md","text":"---\ndescription: Resume or recover work on a spec folder: canonical continuity recovery with one next step.\nargument-hint: \"[spec-folder-path] [:auto|:confirm] [--phase-folder=<path>] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, memory_context, memory_search, memory_match_triggers, memory_list, memory_stats, memory_delete, memory_update, memory_validate, memory_index_scan, memory_health, checkpoint_create, checkpoint_list, checkpoint_restore, checkpoint_delete\n---\n\n# SpecKit Resume\n\nThin router for resuming or recovering work on an existing SpecKit packet. This command resolves mode and target folder, loads the presentation contract, then executes the owned workflow YAML.\n\n## 1. Router Contract\n\nDo not dispatch agents from this Markdown file. Session detection, continuity loading, progress calculation, recovery depth, and continuation behavior are owned by the workflow YAML assets.\n\nLoad the presentation contract before showing startup questions, checkpoints, dashboards, resume briefs, stale-session warnings, or next-step prompts.\n\n## 2. Owned Assets\n\n| Purpose | Asset |\n|---------|-------|\n| Presentation source of truth | `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_resume_presentation.md` |\n| Auto workflow | `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_resume_auto.yaml` |\n| Confirm workflow | `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_resume_confirm.yaml` |\n\nNo workflow-asset gap exists for this command.\n\n## 3. Mode Routing\n\n1. Parse `$ARGUMENTS` for `:auto` or `:confirm`.\n2. Treat `--phase-folder`, `--no-redirect`, and the positional spec-folder path as workflow inputs.\n3. If no mode suffix is present, default to interactive mode unless the presentation contract's startup display says a confirmation is required.\n4. For `:auto`, resolve required setup inputs using the presentation contract's auto-resolution rules before loading YAML.\n5. Load the selected workflow asset and execute it step by step.\n\n## 4. Execution Targets\n\n| Mode | Workflow |\n|------|----------|\n| `:auto` | `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_resume_auto.yaml` |\n| `:confirm` or default interactive choice | `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_resume_confirm.yaml` |\n\n## 5. Presentation Boundary\n\nThe following content lives only in `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_resume_presentation.md`:\n\n- Startup-question wording and reply format.\n- `:auto` pre-bound setup answer schema, default table, targeted-ask rules, and fail-fast display.\n- Session-selection, memory-depth, progress, stale-session, and continuation dashboards.\n- Resume brief and no-session result templates.\n- Related-command and next-step suggestions.\n\n## 6. Workflow Summary\n\nThe YAML workflow recovers the smallest safe continuation packet from canonical artifacts first, enriches only when needed, calculates progress, and presents one next safe action.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":54,"totalLines":54,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/commands/speckit/resume.md","time":{"start":1781143421526,"end":1781143421533}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0751d83c14c6e763016a2a177d52048191bb68d08a91ead03c"}},"id":"prt_eb46bc255001uwdENeL0I5Ddl5","sessionID":"ses_14b95d46bffeZ6ztCn3DXZD284","messageID":"msg_eb46b983e001Ogrz7OUheKx8sn"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781143421534,"sessionID":"ses_14b95d46bffeZ6ztCn3DXZD284","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_jcMRgEe1UHjKMEQHtqrhshDu","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/create/agent.md","offset":1,"limit":120},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/create/agent.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: description: Create a new OpenCode agent with frontmatter, tool permissions, behavioral rules. Modes :auto, :confirm.\n3: argument-hint: \"<agent_name> [agent_description] [:auto|:confirm] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\n4: allowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Glob, Grep, TodoWrite\n5: ---\n6: \n7: # /create:agent Router\n8: \n9: This command is a thin router. It separates execution routing from user-facing presentation.\n10: \n11: ## Routing Assets\n12: \n13: | Asset | Path | Purpose |\n14: | --- | --- | --- |\n15: | Presentation contract | `.opencode/commands/create/assets/create_agent_presentation.md` | Startup questions, setup dashboard, and completion display |\n16: | Auto workflow | `.opencode/commands/create/assets/create_agent_auto.yaml` | Autonomous workflow execution |\n17: | Confirm workflow | `.opencode/commands/create/assets/create_agent_confirm.yaml` | Interactive checkpointed workflow execution |\n18: \n19: ## Execution Order\n20: \n21: 1. Read `.opencode/commands/create/assets/create_agent_presentation.md`.\n22: 2. Run the presentation contract's Phase 0 verification and setup resolution.\n23: 3. Resolve execution mode from `$ARGUMENTS` or the setup answer: `:auto` or `:confirm`.\n24: 4. Load exactly one workflow YAML:\n25:    - `:auto` -> `.opencode/commands/create/assets/create_agent_auto.yaml`\n26:    - `:confirm` or omitted mode -> `.opencode/commands/create/assets/create_agent_confirm.yaml`\n27: 5. Execute the selected YAML step by step.\n28: 6. Use the presentation contract, not this router, for user prompts, setup/status dashboards, and final result display.\n29: \n30: ## Routing Rules\n31: \n32: - Do not dispatch agents from this router.\n33: - Do not edit workflow YAML while executing this command.\n34: - If any referenced asset is missing, stop and report the missing path.\n35: - The YAML owns workflow behavior; the presentation Markdown owns user-visible wording and layout.\n36: \n37: User request: {{args}}\n\n(End of file - total 37 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ndescription: Create a new OpenCode agent with frontmatter, tool permissions, behavioral rules. Modes :auto, :confirm.\nargument-hint: \"<agent_name> [agent_description] [:auto|:confirm] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Glob, Grep, TodoWrite\n---\n\n# /create:agent Router\n\nThis command is a thin router. It separates execution routing from user-facing presentation.\n\n## Routing Assets\n\n| Asset | Path | Purpose |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| Presentation contract | `.opencode/commands/create/assets/create_agent_presentation.md` | Startup questions, setup dashboard, and completion display |\n| Auto workflow | `.opencode/commands/create/assets/create_agent_auto.yaml` | Autonomous workflow execution |\n| Confirm workflow | `.opencode/commands/create/assets/create_agent_confirm.yaml` | Interactive checkpointed workflow execution |\n\n## Execution Order\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/create/agent.md","text":"---\ndescription: Create a new OpenCode agent with frontmatter, tool permissions, behavioral rules. Modes :auto, :confirm.\nargument-hint: \"<agent_name> [agent_description] [:auto|:confirm] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Glob, Grep, TodoWrite\n---\n\n# /create:agent Router\n\nThis command is a thin router. It separates execution routing from user-facing presentation.\n\n## Routing Assets\n\n| Asset | Path | Purpose |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| Presentation contract | `.opencode/commands/create/assets/create_agent_presentation.md` | Startup questions, setup dashboard, and completion display |\n| Auto workflow | `.opencode/commands/create/assets/create_agent_auto.yaml` | Autonomous workflow execution |\n| Confirm workflow | `.opencode/commands/create/assets/create_agent_confirm.yaml` | Interactive checkpointed workflow execution |\n\n## Execution Order\n\n1. Read `.opencode/commands/create/assets/create_agent_presentation.md`.\n2. Run the presentation contract's Phase 0 verification and setup resolution.\n3. Resolve execution mode from `$ARGUMENTS` or the setup answer: `:auto` or `:confirm`.\n4. Load exactly one workflow YAML:\n   - `:auto` -> `.opencode/commands/create/assets/create_agent_auto.yaml`\n   - `:confirm` or omitted mode -> `.opencode/commands/create/assets/create_agent_confirm.yaml`\n5. Execute the selected YAML step by step.\n6. Use the presentation contract, not this router, for user prompts, setup/status dashboards, and final result display.\n\n## Routing Rules\n\n- Do not dispatch agents from this router.\n- Do not edit workflow YAML while executing this command.\n- If any referenced asset is missing, stop and report the missing path.\n- The YAML owns workflow behavior; the presentation Markdown owns user-visible wording and layout.\n\nUser request: {{args}}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":37,"totalLines":37,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/commands/create/agent.md","time":{"start":1781143421528,"end":1781143421534}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0751d83c14c6e763016a2a177d520c8191a3bbfa511fc40096"}},"id":"prt_eb46bc257001SWUfCzvKoM5Uwy","sessionID":"ses_14b95d46bffeZ6ztCn3DXZD284","messageID":"msg_eb46b983e001Ogrz7OUheKx8sn"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781143421555,"sessionID":"ses_14b95d46bffeZ6ztCn3DXZD284","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_1ZrlmTvGo1kURFZyVea6YAvT","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/doctor/speckit.md","offset":1,"limit":120},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/doctor/speckit.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: description: Router for /doctor <target>; dispatches subsystem diagnostics through _routes.yaml.\n3: argument-hint: \"<target> [flags] | list | ?\"\n4: allowed-tools: Read, Bash, Grep, Glob, Edit, Write, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_status, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_query, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_context, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_scan, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_apply, mcp__mk_code_index__detect_changes, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_health, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_drift_why, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__embedder_status, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_link, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_recommend, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_status, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_validate, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_rebuild, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__skill_graph_scan, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__skill_graph_query, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__skill_graph_status\n5: ---\n6: <!-- skill_agent: system-spec-kit -->\n7: \n8: # /doctor Router\n9: \n10: This command is a thin router. It resolves the target and setup values, then loads the target workflow YAML and the presentation contract.\n11: \n12: ## Router Contract\n13: \n14: Do not dispatch agents from this Markdown file. Do not edit workflow YAML while executing this command.\n15: \n16: Load the presentation contract before showing startup questions, setup dashboards, approval prompts, diagnostic dashboards, result summaries, or next-step text.\n17: \n18: ## Owned Assets\n19: \n20: | Purpose | Asset |\n21: |---------|-------|\n22: | Route manifest | `.opencode/commands/doctor/_routes.yaml` |\n23: | Presentation source of truth | `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_speckit_presentation.md` |\n24: \n25: ## Workflow Assets\n26: \n27: These existing YAML assets are referenced only. The router must not modify them.\n28: \n29: | Target | Workflow |\n30: |--------|----------|\n31: | `memory` | `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_memory.yaml` |\n32: | `embeddings` | `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_embeddings.yaml` |\n33: | `causal-graph` | `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_causal-graph.yaml` |\n34: | `code-graph` | `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_code-graph.yaml` |\n35: | `deep-loop` | `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_deep-loop.yaml` |\n36: | `skill-advisor` | `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_skill-advisor.yaml` |\n37: | `skill-budget` | `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_skill-budget.yaml` |\n38: \n39: No workflow-asset gap exists for this command.\n40: \n41: ## Execution Order\n42: \n43: 1. Read `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_speckit_presentation.md`.\n44: 2. Read `.opencode/commands/doctor/_routes.yaml`.\n45: 3. Parse the first positional token from `$ARGUMENTS` as `target`; support `list`, `?`, `--list`, and compatibility alias `--target=<name>`.\n46: 4. If target is unresolved, ask the presentation contract's target-resolution prompt and wait.\n47: 5. If target is unknown, render the presentation contract's unknown-target failure and stop.\n48: 6. Resolve `yaml`, `setup_vars`, `allowed_flags`, `mutating`, `mcp_tools`, and script invocations from `_routes.yaml`.\n49: 7. Parse remaining flags using only the resolved target's `allowed_flags`; reject cross-target flags using the presentation contract's error wording.\n50: 8. Resolve any missing setup variables using the presentation contract's per-target setup prompts.\n51: 9. Load the resolved workflow YAML from `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/<yaml>` and execute it step by step.\n52: 10. Use the presentation contract, not this router, for user prompts, dashboards, result summaries, and next-step display.\n53: \n54: ## Routing Rules\n55: \n56: - `_routes.yaml` is the canonical routing and mutation-class manifest.\n57: - `execution_mode` is always `INTERACTIVE`.\n58: - The positional target is parsed before any flag; global flag pre-parse is forbidden.\n59: - Unknown or cross-target flags fail before YAML load.\n60: - The YAML start condition is: target bound, workflow asset exists, presentation asset loaded, and every target setup variable resolved.\n61: - If any referenced asset is missing, stop and report the missing path.\n62: - Companion commands are not routed through this file: `/doctor:update` and `/doctor:mcp install|debug` have their own routers.\n63: - The YAML owns workflow behavior; the presentation Markdown owns visible wording and layout.\n64: \n65: ## Presentation Boundary\n66: \n67: The following content lives only in `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_speckit_presentation.md`:\n68: \n69: - Target-resolution menu, help text, accepted answers, and failure wording.\n70: - Per-target setup prompts for unresolved fields.\n71: - Subsystem manifest display for `list`, `?`, or `--list`.\n72: - Diagnostic dashboard and result-summary templates.\n73: - Troubleshooting and next-step display text.\n74: \n75: User request: {{args}}\n\n(End of file - total 75 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ndescription: Router for /doctor <target>; dispatches subsystem diagnostics through _routes.yaml.\nargument-hint: \"<target> [flags] | list | ?\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Bash, Grep, Glob, Edit, Write, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_status, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_query, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_context, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_scan, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_apply, mcp__mk_code_index__detect_changes, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_health, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_drift_why, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__embedder_status, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_link, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_recommend, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_status, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_validate, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_rebuild, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__skill_graph_scan, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__skill_graph_query, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__skill_graph_status\n---\n<!-- skill_agent: system-spec-kit -->\n\n# /doctor Router\n\nThis command is a thin router. It resolves the target and setup values, then loads the target workflow YAML and the presentation contract.\n\n## Router Contract\n\nDo not dispatch agents from this Markdown file. Do not edit workflow YAML while executing this command.\n\nLoad the presentation contract before showing startup questions, setup dashboards, approval prompts, diagnostic dashboards, result summaries, or next-step text.\n\n## Owned Assets\n\n| Purpose | Asset |","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/doctor/speckit.md","text":"---\ndescription: Router for /doctor <target>; dispatches subsystem diagnostics through _routes.yaml.\nargument-hint: \"<target> [flags] | list | ?\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Bash, Grep, Glob, Edit, Write, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_status, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_query, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_context, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_scan, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_apply, mcp__mk_code_index__detect_changes, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_health, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_drift_why, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__embedder_status, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_link, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_recommend, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_status, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_validate, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_rebuild, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__skill_graph_scan, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__skill_graph_query, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__skill_graph_status\n---\n<!-- skill_agent: system-spec-kit -->\n\n# /doctor Router\n\nThis command is a thin router. It resolves the target and setup values, then loads the target workflow YAML and the presentation contract.\n\n## Router Contract\n\nDo not dispatch agents from this Markdown file. Do not edit workflow YAML while executing this command.\n\nLoad the presentation contract before showing startup questions, setup dashboards, approval prompts, diagnostic dashboards, result summaries, or next-step text.\n\n## Owned Assets\n\n| Purpose | Asset |\n|---------|-------|\n| Route manifest | `.opencode/commands/doctor/_routes.yaml` |\n| Presentation source of truth | `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_speckit_presentation.md` |\n\n## Workflow Assets\n\nThese existing YAML assets are referenced only. The router must not modify them.\n\n| Target | Workflow |\n|--------|----------|\n| `memory` | `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_memory.yaml` |\n| `embeddings` | `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_embeddings.yaml` |\n| `causal-graph` | `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_causal-graph.yaml` |\n| `code-graph` | `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_code-graph.yaml` |\n| `deep-loop` | `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_deep-loop.yaml` |\n| `skill-advisor` | `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_skill-advisor.yaml` |\n| `skill-budget` | `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_skill-budget.yaml` |\n\nNo workflow-asset gap exists for this command.\n\n## Execution Order\n\n1. Read `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_speckit_presentation.md`.\n2. Read `.opencode/commands/doctor/_routes.yaml`.\n3. Parse the first positional token from `$ARGUMENTS` as `target`; support `list`, `?`, `--list`, and compatibility alias `--target=<name>`.\n4. If target is unresolved, ask the presentation contract's target-resolution prompt and wait.\n5. If target is unknown, render the presentation contract's unknown-target failure and stop.\n6. Resolve `yaml`, `setup_vars`, `allowed_flags`, `mutating`, `mcp_tools`, and script invocations from `_routes.yaml`.\n7. Parse remaining flags using only the resolved target's `allowed_flags`; reject cross-target flags using the presentation contract's error wording.\n8. Resolve any missing setup variables using the presentation contract's per-target setup prompts.\n9. Load the resolved workflow YAML from `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/<yaml>` and execute it step by step.\n10. Use the presentation contract, not this router, for user prompts, dashboards, result summaries, and next-step display.\n\n## Routing Rules\n\n- `_routes.yaml` is the canonical routing and mutation-class manifest.\n- `execution_mode` is always `INTERACTIVE`.\n- The positional target is parsed before any flag; global flag pre-parse is forbidden.\n- Unknown or cross-target flags fail before YAML load.\n- The YAML start condition is: target bound, workflow asset exists, presentation asset loaded, and every target setup variable resolved.\n- If any referenced asset is missing, stop and report the missing path.\n- Companion commands are not routed through this file: `/doctor:update` and `/doctor:mcp install|debug` have their own routers.\n- The YAML owns workflow behavior; the presentation Markdown owns visible wording and layout.\n\n## Presentation Boundary\n\nThe following content lives only in `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_speckit_presentation.md`:\n\n- Target-resolution menu, help text, accepted answers, and failure wording.\n- Per-target setup prompts for unresolved fields.\n- Subsystem manifest display for `list`, `?`, or `--list`.\n- Diagnostic dashboard and result-summary templates.\n- Troubleshooting and next-step display text.\n\nUser request: {{args}}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":75,"totalLines":75,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/commands/doctor/speckit.md","time":{"start":1781143421550,"end":1781143421555}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0751d83c14c6e763016a2a177d521081918780116d30392d97"}},"id":"prt_eb46bc2580012ma8yN5LQATNA0","sessionID":"ses_14b95d46bffeZ6ztCn3DXZD284","messageID":"msg_eb46b983e001Ogrz7OUheKx8sn"}}
