{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1781143423454,"sessionID":"ses_14b95d46bffeZ6ztCn3DXZD284","part":{"id":"prt_eb46bc9db001KkcQNPQsV0JygZ","messageID":"msg_eb46bc4ab001n5EAhRr4mgfCrg","sessionID":"ses_14b95d46bffeZ6ztCn3DXZD284","snapshot":"08452c522195b926f57a49b1383e0fe07431f0ca","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781143439433,"sessionID":"ses_14b95d46bffeZ6ztCn3DXZD284","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_wGnCFTsgAsTNk3oPfaUaaf6H","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/doctor/_routes.yaml","offset":1,"limit":240},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/doctor/_routes.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n2: # DOCTOR ROUTER — CANONICAL ROUTE MANIFEST\n3: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n4: # Source of truth for /doctor <target> dispatch.\n5: # Read by: .opencode/commands/doctor/speckit.md (the router)\n6: # Validated by: .opencode/commands/doctor/scripts/route-validate.sh\n7: # Consumed by: Skill Advisor lexical lane (per-target trigger_phrases)\n8: #\n9: # Schema (per route):\n10: #   target:           string — positional name the user types\n11: #   yaml:             string — YAML asset filename in assets/\n12: #   setup_vars:       list   — variables the router resolves and passes to YAML\n13: #   allowed_flags:    list   — per-target flag schema (target-first parsing)\n14: #   mutating:         enum   — read-only | add-only | mutates\n15: #   gate3_location:   string — concrete mutation target (or \"n/a\" for read-only)\n16: #   mcp_tools:        list   — subset of router's frontmatter allowed-tools union\n17: #   trigger_phrases:  list   — advisor lexical-routing phrases for this target\n18: #\n19: # Code-graph implementation/docs are owned by .opencode/skills/system-code-graph/;\n20: # stable code_graph/detect_changes MCP tools are registered through mk-code-index.\n21: # Skill-advisor recommendation tools are registered through mk-skill-advisor.\n22: # To add a new target: append a route here, then re-run route-validate.sh.\n23: # To remove a target: delete the route AND its corresponding assets/doctor_<target>.yaml.\n24: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n25: schema_version: 1\n26: routes:\n27:   - target: memory\n28:     yaml: doctor_memory.yaml\n29:     setup_vars: [execution_mode, intent, incremental, no_snapshot, dry_run]\n30:     allowed_flags: [\"--incremental=true|false\", \"--no-snapshot\", \"--dry-run\"]\n31:     mutating: read-only\n32:     gate3_location: \"n/a (read-only diagnostic; reports drift and recommends action, no DB writes)\"\n33:     mcp_tools:\n34:       - mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_health\n35:       - mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan\n36:       - mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_drift_why\n37:       - mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search\n38:       - mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_stats\n39:     script_invocations:\n40:       - 'Warm-only: probe the existing mk-spec-memory IPC socket first; only when it answers, run node .opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs memory_health --format json --timeout-ms 500 --warm-only (the flag guarantees no daemon start; exit 75 = backend unavailable, retryable)'\n41:     trigger_phrases:\n42:       - \"memory continuity index drift\"\n43:       - \"memory health rebuild\"\n44:       - \"context-index doctor\"\n45:       - \"voyage embedding rebuild\"\n46: \n47:   - target: embeddings\n48:     yaml: doctor_embeddings.yaml\n49:     setup_vars: [execution_mode]\n50:     allowed_flags: []\n51:     mutating: read-only\n52:     gate3_location: \"n/a (read-only provider and model-server status)\"\n53:     mcp_tools:\n54:       - mcp__mk_spec_memory__embedder_status\n55:     trigger_phrases:\n56:       - \"embedding provider status\"\n57:       - \"hf-local model-server health\"\n58:       - \"embedder_status diagnostics\"\n59: \n60:   - target: causal-graph\n61:     yaml: doctor_causal-graph.yaml\n62:     setup_vars: [execution_mode, intent, confidence_threshold, no_snapshot, dry_run]\n63:     allowed_flags: [\"--confidence-threshold=N\", \"--no-snapshot\", \"--dry-run\"]\n64:     mutating: read-only\n65:     gate3_location: \"n/a (read-only diagnostic; samples causal_edges and recommends candidates, no writes)\"\n66:     mcp_tools:\n67:       - mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_stats\n68:       - mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_drift_why\n69:       - mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search\n70:     trigger_phrases:\n71:       - \"causal edges drift\"\n72:       - \"causal graph doctor\"\n73:       - \"lineage coverage\"\n74:       - \"memory_causal_stats\"\n75: \n76:   - target: code-graph\n77:     yaml: doctor_code-graph.yaml\n78:     setup_vars: [execution_mode, scope]\n79:     allowed_flags:\n80:       - \"--scope=stale|missed|bloat|all|excludes\"\n81:       - \"--operation=rescan|prune-excludes|repair-nodes|recover-sqlite-corruption|rollback-bad-run\"\n82:       - \"--dry-run\"\n83:       - \"--confirm\"\n84:     mutating: read-only\n85:     gate3_location: \"n/a (Phase A diagnostic is read-only; emits an exclude/language report, never scans or writes the index)\"\n86:     mcp_tools:\n87:       - mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_status\n88:       - mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_query\n89:       - mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_context\n90:       - mcp__mk_code_index__detect_changes\n91:       - mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context\n92:       - mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search\n93:     script_invocations:\n94:       - 'Warm-only: probe the existing mk-code-index IPC socket first; only when it answers, run node .opencode/bin/code-index.cjs code_graph_status --format json --timeout-ms 500 --warm-only (the flag guarantees no daemon start; exit 75 = backend unavailable, retryable)'\n95:     trigger_phrases:\n96:       - \"code-graph index drift\"\n97:       - \"code-graph rebuild\"\n98:       - \"code-graph stale excludes\"\n99:       - \"code-graph corruption recover\"\n100: \n101:   - target: deep-loop\n102:     yaml: doctor_deep-loop.yaml\n103:     setup_vars: [execution_mode, intent, scope, no_snapshot, dry_run]\n104:     allowed_flags: [\"--scope=research|review|both\", \"--no-snapshot\", \"--dry-run\"]\n105:     mutating: read-only\n106:     gate3_location: \"n/a (read-only diagnostic; reads coverage graph + iteration folders, never upserts)\"\n107:     mcp_tools: []\n108:     script_invocations:\n109:       - 'node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/status.cjs --spec-folder \"{spec_folder}\" --loop-type \"{loop_type}\" --session-id \"{session_id}\"'\n110:       - 'node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/query.cjs --spec-folder \"{spec_folder}\" --loop-type \"{loop_type}\" --session-id \"{session_id}\" --query-type \"{query_type}\"'\n111:       - 'node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs --spec-folder \"{spec_folder}\" --loop-type \"{loop_type}\" --session-id \"{session_id}\"'\n112:     trigger_phrases:\n113:       - \"deep-loop coverage\"\n114:       - \"deep-loop graph rebuild\"\n115:       - \"deep-research convergence drift\"\n116:       - \"deep-review iteration graph\"\n117: \n118:   - target: skill-advisor\n119:     yaml: doctor_skill-advisor.yaml\n120:     setup_vars: [execution_mode, scope, skip_tests, dry_run]\n121:     allowed_flags: [\"--skip-tests\", \"--dry-run\", \"--scope=all|explicit|derived|lexical\"]\n122:     mutating: mutates\n123:     gate3_location: \"lib/scorer/lanes/*.ts + .opencode/skills/*/graph-metadata.json\"\n124:     mcp_tools:\n125:       - mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_recommend\n126:       - mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_status\n127:       - mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_validate\n128:       - mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_rebuild\n129:       - mcp__mk_skill_advisor__skill_graph_scan\n130:       - mcp__mk_skill_advisor__skill_graph_query\n131:       - mcp__mk_skill_advisor__skill_graph_status\n132:       - mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context\n133:       - mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search\n134:     script_invocations:\n135:       - 'Warm-only: probe the existing mk-skill-advisor IPC socket first; only when it answers, run node .opencode/bin/skill-advisor.cjs advisor_status --workspace-root \"$PWD\" --format json --timeout-ms 500 --warm-only (the flag guarantees no daemon start; exit 75 = backend unavailable, retryable)'\n136:     trigger_phrases:\n137:       - \"skill advisor scoring\"\n138:       - \"skill advisor rebuild\"\n139:       - \"advisor recommendation tuning\"\n140:       - \"skill_graph scan\"\n141: \n142:   - target: skill-budget\n143:     yaml: doctor_skill-budget.yaml\n144:     setup_vars: [execution_mode, json_output, top_n, fail_over, project_ceiling]\n145:     allowed_flags: [\"--json\", \"--top-n=N\", \"--fail-over=N\", \"--project-ceiling=N\"]\n146:     mutating: read-only\n147:     gate3_location: \"n/a (read-only audit; no spec folder required)\"\n148:     mcp_tools: []   # script-only audit; no MCP calls\n149:     script_invocations:\n150:       - 'Warm-only: probe the existing mk-skill-advisor IPC socket first; only when it answers, run node .opencode/bin/skill-advisor.cjs advisor_status --workspace-root \"$PWD\" --format json --timeout-ms 500 --warm-only (the flag guarantees no daemon start; exit 75 = backend unavailable, retryable)'\n151:     trigger_phrases:\n152:       - \"skill budget audit\"\n153:       - \"description budget check\"\n154:       - \"skill char count drift\"\n155:       - \"frontmatter description trim\"\n156: \n157: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n158: # COMPANION COMMAND ROUTES (/doctor:mcp sub-actions)\n159: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n160: # /doctor:mcp dispatches via its own command (.opencode/commands/doctor/mcp.md).\n161: # These rows are tracked here for advisor + CI visibility only — the mcp.md\n162: # command parses its own sub-action argv and dispatches to the right YAML.\n163: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n164: mcp_subroutes:\n165:   - sub_action: install\n166:     yaml: doctor_mcp_install.yaml\n167:     allowed_flags: [\"--server <name>\", \"--runtime <name>\"]\n168:     mutating: mutates\n169:     gate3_location: \"MCP server install dirs + runtime config (.opencode.json / .claude/settings.json / .codex/config.toml)\"\n170:     trigger_phrases:\n171:       - \"MCP install\"\n172:       - \"MCP server fresh install\"\n173:       - \"reinstall MCP\"\n174: \n175:   - sub_action: debug\n176:     yaml: doctor_mcp_debug.yaml\n177:     allowed_flags: [\"--fix\", \"--server <name>\"]\n178:     mutating: mutates\n179:     gate3_location: \"MCP server logs + runtime config repair\"\n180:     trigger_phrases:\n181:       - \"MCP server broken\"\n182:       - \"MCP debug\"\n183:       - \"MCP connection failure\"\n184:       - \"mcp-doctor.sh\"\n185: \n186: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n187: # ORCHESTRATOR (NOT routed through /doctor — kept here for reference)\n188: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n189: # /doctor:update is a STANDALONE command at .opencode/commands/doctor/update.md.\n190: # It does NOT route through /doctor. This block exists for advisor visibility.\n191: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n192: standalone:\n193:   - command: /doctor:update\n194:     file: .opencode/commands/doctor/update.md\n195:     yaml: doctor_update.yaml\n196:     mutating: mutates\n197:     trigger_phrases:\n198:       - \"spec-kit version migration\"\n199:       - \"doctor update orchestrator\"\n200:       - \"rebuild all spec-kit databases\"\n201:       - \"doctor full sync\"\n\n(End of file - total 201 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DOCTOR ROUTER — CANONICAL ROUTE MANIFEST\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# Source of truth for /doctor <target> dispatch.\n# Read by: .opencode/commands/doctor/speckit.md (the router)\n# Validated by: .opencode/commands/doctor/scripts/route-validate.sh\n# Consumed by: Skill Advisor lexical lane (per-target trigger_phrases)\n#\n# Schema (per route):\n#   target:           string — positional name the user types\n#   yaml:             string — YAML asset filename in assets/\n#   setup_vars:       list   — variables the router resolves and passes to YAML\n#   allowed_flags:    list   — per-target flag schema (target-first parsing)\n#   mutating:         enum   — read-only | add-only | mutates\n#   gate3_location:   string — concrete mutation target (or \"n/a\" for read-only)\n#   mcp_tools:        list   — subset of router's frontmatter allowed-tools union\n#   trigger_phrases:  list   — advisor lexical-routing phrases for this target\n#\n# Code-graph implementation/docs are owned by .opencode/skills/system-code-graph/;\n# stable code_graph/detect_changes MCP tools are registered through mk-code-index.","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/doctor/_routes.yaml","text":"# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DOCTOR ROUTER — CANONICAL ROUTE MANIFEST\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# Source of truth for /doctor <target> dispatch.\n# Read by: .opencode/commands/doctor/speckit.md (the router)\n# Validated by: .opencode/commands/doctor/scripts/route-validate.sh\n# Consumed by: Skill Advisor lexical lane (per-target trigger_phrases)\n#\n# Schema (per route):\n#   target:           string — positional name the user types\n#   yaml:             string — YAML asset filename in assets/\n#   setup_vars:       list   — variables the router resolves and passes to YAML\n#   allowed_flags:    list   — per-target flag schema (target-first parsing)\n#   mutating:         enum   — read-only | add-only | mutates\n#   gate3_location:   string — concrete mutation target (or \"n/a\" for read-only)\n#   mcp_tools:        list   — subset of router's frontmatter allowed-tools union\n#   trigger_phrases:  list   — advisor lexical-routing phrases for this target\n#\n# Code-graph implementation/docs are owned by .opencode/skills/system-code-graph/;\n# stable code_graph/detect_changes MCP tools are registered through mk-code-index.\n# Skill-advisor recommendation tools are registered through mk-skill-advisor.\n# To add a new target: append a route here, then re-run route-validate.sh.\n# To remove a target: delete the route AND its corresponding assets/doctor_<target>.yaml.\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nschema_version: 1\nroutes:\n  - target: memory\n    yaml: doctor_memory.yaml\n    setup_vars: [execution_mode, intent, incremental, no_snapshot, dry_run]\n    allowed_flags: [\"--incremental=true|false\", \"--no-snapshot\", \"--dry-run\"]\n    mutating: read-only\n    gate3_location: \"n/a (read-only diagnostic; reports drift and recommends action, no DB writes)\"\n    mcp_tools:\n      - mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_health\n      - mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan\n      - mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_drift_why\n      - mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search\n      - mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_stats\n    script_invocations:\n      - 'Warm-only: probe the existing mk-spec-memory IPC socket first; only when it answers, run node .opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs memory_health --format json --timeout-ms 500 --warm-only (the flag guarantees no daemon start; exit 75 = backend unavailable, retryable)'\n    trigger_phrases:\n      - \"memory continuity index drift\"\n      - \"memory health rebuild\"\n      - \"context-index doctor\"\n      - \"voyage embedding rebuild\"\n\n  - target: embeddings\n    yaml: doctor_embeddings.yaml\n    setup_vars: [execution_mode]\n    allowed_flags: []\n    mutating: read-only\n    gate3_location: \"n/a (read-only provider and model-server status)\"\n    mcp_tools:\n      - mcp__mk_spec_memory__embedder_status\n    trigger_phrases:\n      - \"embedding provider status\"\n      - \"hf-local model-server health\"\n      - \"embedder_status diagnostics\"\n\n  - target: causal-graph\n    yaml: doctor_causal-graph.yaml\n    setup_vars: [execution_mode, intent, confidence_threshold, no_snapshot, dry_run]\n    allowed_flags: [\"--confidence-threshold=N\", \"--no-snapshot\", \"--dry-run\"]\n    mutating: read-only\n    gate3_location: \"n/a (read-only diagnostic; samples causal_edges and recommends candidates, no writes)\"\n    mcp_tools:\n      - mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_stats\n      - mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_drift_why\n      - mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search\n    trigger_phrases:\n      - \"causal edges drift\"\n      - \"causal graph doctor\"\n      - \"lineage coverage\"\n      - \"memory_causal_stats\"\n\n  - target: code-graph\n    yaml: doctor_code-graph.yaml\n    setup_vars: [execution_mode, scope]\n    allowed_flags:\n      - \"--scope=stale|missed|bloat|all|excludes\"\n      - \"--operation=rescan|prune-excludes|repair-nodes|recover-sqlite-corruption|rollback-bad-run\"\n      - \"--dry-run\"\n      - \"--confirm\"\n    mutating: read-only\n    gate3_location: \"n/a (Phase A diagnostic is read-only; emits an exclude/language report, never scans or writes the index)\"\n    mcp_tools:\n      - mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_status\n      - mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_query\n      - mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_context\n      - mcp__mk_code_index__detect_changes\n      - mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context\n      - mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search\n    script_invocations:\n      - 'Warm-only: probe the existing mk-code-index IPC socket first; only when it answers, run node .opencode/bin/code-index.cjs code_graph_status --format json --timeout-ms 500 --warm-only (the flag guarantees no daemon start; exit 75 = backend unavailable, retryable)'\n    trigger_phrases:\n      - \"code-graph index drift\"\n      - \"code-graph rebuild\"\n      - \"code-graph stale excludes\"\n      - \"code-graph corruption recover\"\n\n  - target: deep-loop\n    yaml: doctor_deep-loop.yaml\n    setup_vars: [execution_mode, intent, scope, no_snapshot, dry_run]\n    allowed_flags: [\"--scope=research|review|both\", \"--no-snapshot\", \"--dry-run\"]\n    mutating: read-only\n    gate3_location: \"n/a (read-only diagnostic; reads coverage graph + iteration folders, never upserts)\"\n    mcp_tools: []\n    script_invocations:\n      - 'node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/status.cjs --spec-folder \"{spec_folder}\" --loop-type \"{loop_type}\" --session-id \"{session_id}\"'\n      - 'node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/query.cjs --spec-folder \"{spec_folder}\" --loop-type \"{loop_type}\" --session-id \"{session_id}\" --query-type \"{query_type}\"'\n      - 'node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs --spec-folder \"{spec_folder}\" --loop-type \"{loop_type}\" --session-id \"{session_id}\"'\n    trigger_phrases:\n      - \"deep-loop coverage\"\n      - \"deep-loop graph rebuild\"\n      - \"deep-research convergence drift\"\n      - \"deep-review iteration graph\"\n\n  - target: skill-advisor\n    yaml: doctor_skill-advisor.yaml\n    setup_vars: [execution_mode, scope, skip_tests, dry_run]\n    allowed_flags: [\"--skip-tests\", \"--dry-run\", \"--scope=all|explicit|derived|lexical\"]\n    mutating: mutates\n    gate3_location: \"lib/scorer/lanes/*.ts + .opencode/skills/*/graph-metadata.json\"\n    mcp_tools:\n      - mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_recommend\n      - mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_status\n      - mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_validate\n      - mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_rebuild\n      - mcp__mk_skill_advisor__skill_graph_scan\n      - mcp__mk_skill_advisor__skill_graph_query\n      - mcp__mk_skill_advisor__skill_graph_status\n      - mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context\n      - mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search\n    script_invocations:\n      - 'Warm-only: probe the existing mk-skill-advisor IPC socket first; only when it answers, run node .opencode/bin/skill-advisor.cjs advisor_status --workspace-root \"$PWD\" --format json --timeout-ms 500 --warm-only (the flag guarantees no daemon start; exit 75 = backend unavailable, retryable)'\n    trigger_phrases:\n      - \"skill advisor scoring\"\n      - \"skill advisor rebuild\"\n      - \"advisor recommendation tuning\"\n      - \"skill_graph scan\"\n\n  - target: skill-budget\n    yaml: doctor_skill-budget.yaml\n    setup_vars: [execution_mode, json_output, top_n, fail_over, project_ceiling]\n    allowed_flags: [\"--json\", \"--top-n=N\", \"--fail-over=N\", \"--project-ceiling=N\"]\n    mutating: read-only\n    gate3_location: \"n/a (read-only audit; no spec folder required)\"\n    mcp_tools: []   # script-only audit; no MCP calls\n    script_invocations:\n      - 'Warm-only: probe the existing mk-skill-advisor IPC socket first; only when it answers, run node .opencode/bin/skill-advisor.cjs advisor_status --workspace-root \"$PWD\" --format json --timeout-ms 500 --warm-only (the flag guarantees no daemon start; exit 75 = backend unavailable, retryable)'\n    trigger_phrases:\n      - \"skill budget audit\"\n      - \"description budget check\"\n      - \"skill char count drift\"\n      - \"frontmatter description trim\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# COMPANION COMMAND ROUTES (/doctor:mcp sub-actions)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# /doctor:mcp dispatches via its own command (.opencode/commands/doctor/mcp.md).\n# These rows are tracked here for advisor + CI visibility only — the mcp.md\n# command parses its own sub-action argv and dispatches to the right YAML.\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nmcp_subroutes:\n  - sub_action: install\n    yaml: doctor_mcp_install.yaml\n    allowed_flags: [\"--server <name>\", \"--runtime <name>\"]\n    mutating: mutates\n    gate3_location: \"MCP server install dirs + runtime config (.opencode.json / .claude/settings.json / .codex/config.toml)\"\n    trigger_phrases:\n      - \"MCP install\"\n      - \"MCP server fresh install\"\n      - \"reinstall MCP\"\n\n  - sub_action: debug\n    yaml: doctor_mcp_debug.yaml\n    allowed_flags: [\"--fix\", \"--server <name>\"]\n    mutating: mutates\n    gate3_location: \"MCP server logs + runtime config repair\"\n    trigger_phrases:\n      - \"MCP server broken\"\n      - \"MCP debug\"\n      - \"MCP connection failure\"\n      - \"mcp-doctor.sh\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# ORCHESTRATOR (NOT routed through /doctor — kept here for reference)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# /doctor:update is a STANDALONE command at .opencode/commands/doctor/update.md.\n# It does NOT route through /doctor. This block exists for advisor visibility.\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nstandalone:\n  - command: /doctor:update\n    file: .opencode/commands/doctor/update.md\n    yaml: doctor_update.yaml\n    mutating: mutates\n    trigger_phrases:\n      - \"spec-kit version migration\"\n      - \"doctor update orchestrator\"\n      - \"rebuild all spec-kit databases\"\n      - \"doctor full sync\"","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":201,"totalLines":201,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/commands/doctor/_routes.yaml","time":{"start":1781143439429,"end":1781143439432}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_074c2a0376ef6969016a2a178f5dec8191a6b810c63edb23ca"}},"id":"prt_eb46c0826001xPYyMcFbCmw879","sessionID":"ses_14b95d46bffeZ6ztCn3DXZD284","messageID":"msg_eb46bc4ab001n5EAhRr4mgfCrg"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781143439466,"sessionID":"ses_14b95d46bffeZ6ztCn3DXZD284","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_0RO9Eaj3NUwddxBmo2nE04hu","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_speckit_presentation.md","offset":1,"limit":230},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_speckit_presentation.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # /doctor Presentation Contract\n2: \n3: This file is the single source of truth for user-facing presentation in `/doctor <target>`: startup questions, subsystem manifest display, setup dashboards, diagnostic dashboards, result templates, troubleshooting, and next-step text. The command router owns target resolution and asset routing only. The workflow YAML owns execution behavior.\n4: \n5: ## 1. Startup Presentation\n6: \n7: When `$ARGUMENTS` lacks a recognized positional target, ask this prompt first after reading `_routes.yaml`.\n8: \n9: ```text\n10: What do you want to do?\n11: \n12:    1) Update everything to match latest spec-kit release   (e.g. 3.3.0.0 -> 3.4.x)\n13:    2) Debug Memory database              (search index, spec-doc indexing)\n14:    3) Debug Embeddings                   (provider choice, hf-local health)\n15:    4) Debug Causal-Graph                 (spec lineage, drift_why)\n16:    5) Debug Code-Graph                   (structural index, stale/missed/bloat)\n17:    6) Debug Deep-Loop history            (research/review iteration graphs)\n18:    7) Re-tune Skill Advisor              (which skill gets recommended)\n19:    8) Audit Skill Description budget     (char counts, CI-friendly)\n20:    0) Full sweep - rebuild everything    (no migration, current schema)\n21:    H) Help me decide\n22:    X) Cancel\n23: ```\n24: \n25: Accepted answers:\n26: \n27: | Answer | Result |\n28: |--------|--------|\n29: | `1` | Abort `/doctor`; display `Switch to /doctor:update --migrate for upgrade migration. Exiting /doctor.` |\n30: | `2` | target = `memory` |\n31: | `3` | target = `embeddings` |\n32: | `4` | target = `causal-graph` |\n33: | `5` | target = `code-graph` |\n34: | `6` | target = `deep-loop` |\n35: | `7` | target = `skill-advisor` |\n36: | `8` | target = `skill-budget` |\n37: | `0` | Abort `/doctor`; display `Switch to /doctor:update for full sweep. Exiting /doctor.` |\n38: | `H` | Show the help block, then ask the startup prompt again |\n39: | `X`, empty, `cancel` | `STATUS=CANCEL` |\n40: \n41: On any other response, re-emit the menu once. On a second invalid response, return `STATUS=FAIL ERROR=unknown_selection`.\n42: \n43: ### Help Block\n44: \n45: ```text\n46: Pick by symptom:\n47: \n48:    Search returns stale or empty results               -> 2  Memory\n49:    \"context-index__*.sqlite missing\" warning           -> 2  Memory\n50:    Model mismatch or hf-local loading state unclear    -> 3  Embeddings\n51:    memory_drift_why returns nothing                    -> 4  Causal-Graph\n52:    \"causal coverage <60%\" warning                      -> 4  Causal-Graph\n53:    \"code-graph stale/missed/bloat\" warning             -> 5  Code-Graph\n54:    \"code_graph_status: unhealthy\" or code-graph errors -> 5  Code-Graph\n55:    deep-research/deep-review iteration graph empty     -> 6  Deep-Loop\n56:    Convergence not detected between iterations         -> 6  Deep-Loop\n57:    Skill Advisor recommends the wrong skill            -> 7  Skill Advisor\n58:    New skill not appearing in advisor results          -> 7  Skill Advisor\n59:    Description char-count over hard cap                -> 8  Skill Budget\n60: \n61: Quick reference for confusable pairs:\n62:    Code-Graph (5) is STRUCTURAL - functions, files, dirs, AST\n63:    Skill Advisor (7) tunes ROUTING quality (which skill gets picked)\n64:    Skill Budget (8) audits CHAR COUNTS (frontmatter description size)\n65: \n66: Press 1-8, 0, or X.\n67: ```\n68: \n69: ### Unknown Target Failure\n70: \n71: ```text\n72: Unknown target: [target]\n73: Valid targets: memory, embeddings, causal-graph, code-graph, deep-loop, skill-advisor, skill-budget\n74: Try: /doctor list\n75: STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"unknown_target\"\n76: ```\n77: \n78: ### Cross-Target Flag Failure\n79: \n80: ```text\n81: Flag '[flag]' is not valid for target '[target]'. Did you mean `/doctor [suggested-target] [flag]`?\n82: STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"cross_target_flag_injection\"\n83: ```\n84: \n85: ## 2. Subsystem Manifest Display\n86: \n87: Render this table for `list`, `?`, or `--list`. Values should mirror `_routes.yaml`.\n88: \n89: | Target | Workflow | Mutation Class | One-Line Purpose |\n90: |--------|----------|----------------|------------------|\n91: | `memory` | `doctor_memory.yaml` | read-only | Diagnose the memory continuity index; report drift and recommend action |\n92: | `embeddings` | `doctor_embeddings.yaml` | read-only | Inspect provider selection and hf-local model-server status |\n93: | `causal-graph` | `doctor_causal-graph.yaml` | read-only | Diagnose causal-edge integrity; sample drift and recommend candidates |\n94: | `code-graph` | `doctor_code-graph.yaml` | read-only | Diagnose code-graph index; report stale, missed, or bloat findings |\n95: | `deep-loop` | `doctor_deep-loop.yaml` | read-only | Diagnose deep-loop coverage graphs for research and review |\n96: | `skill-advisor` | `doctor_skill-advisor.yaml` | mutates | Audit and re-tune skill advisor scoring lanes |\n97: | `skill-budget` | `doctor_skill-budget.yaml` | read-only | Audit skill, command, and agent description budgets |\n98: \n99: ## 3. Setup Prompts\n100: \n101: Ask only prompts needed for unresolved setup variables. Do not split a required setup question into multiple visible turns.\n102: \n103: ### Memory Rebuild Mode\n104: \n105: ```text\n106: Rebuild mode?\n107:    1) Incremental - only changed files (fast, ~30s, default)\n108:    2) Full        - every file (5-15 min; needed after upgrade)\n109: ```\n110: \n111: Accept `1`, `I`, or Enter as `incremental=true`. Accept `2`, `F`, or `full` as `incremental=false`.\n112: \n113: ### Code-Graph Scope\n114: \n115: Ask this only when `--scope` was not passed and the operation needs a scope.\n116: \n117: ```text\n118: Code-graph scope?\n119:    1) stale     - files indexed but mtime moved\n120:    2) missed    - files in repo but not indexed\n121:    3) bloat     - large dirs hogging the graph\n122:    4) all       - full scan (default)\n123:    5) excludes  - review the exclude config\n124: ```\n125: \n126: Accept `1-5`; empty defaults to `all`.\n127: \n128: ## 4. Setup Dashboard\n129: \n130: Render this compact panel after setup and before YAML execution when target resolution or flags were non-trivial.\n131: \n132: ```text\n133: DOCTOR ROUTE SETUP\n134: Target: [target]\n135: Workflow: .opencode/commands/doctor/assets/[yaml]\n136: Mutation class: [read-only|add-only|mutates]\n137: Execution mode: INTERACTIVE\n138: Setup values: [key=value list]\n139: Presentation: .opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_speckit_presentation.md\n140: Next: load workflow YAML\n141: ```\n142: \n143: ## 5. Diagnostic Result Templates\n144: \n145: Use the target workflow output contract when it provides a stricter report shape. Use these family templates for summary display and fallback rendering.\n146: \n147: ### Read-Only Diagnostic Summary\n148: \n149: ```text\n150: DOCTOR DIAGNOSTIC RESULT\n151: Target: [target]\n152: Workflow: [yaml]\n153: Status: [OK|DEGRADED|STALE|MISSING|ATTENTION|EMPTY|CANCELLED|FAIL]\n154: Mutation class: read-only\n155: Evidence: [health checks, counts, sampled records, or report path]\n156: Recommendation: [operator action or none]\n157: STATUS=[status]\n158: ```\n159: \n160: ### Mutating Target Summary\n161: \n162: ```text\n163: DOCTOR MUTATING RESULT\n164: Target: [target]\n165: Workflow: [yaml]\n166: Status: [OK|CANCELLED|FAIL|ROLLED_BACK]\n167: Approved changes: [none|summary]\n168: Files modified: [list or none]\n169: Verification: [checks run and result]\n170: Rollback: [path or not required]\n171: STATUS=[status]\n172: ```\n173: \n174: ### Failure Summary\n175: \n176: ```text\n177: DOCTOR TARGET FAILED\n178: Target: [target]\n179: Step: [setup|workflow phase]\n180: Error: [message]\n181: Next: [recommended command or manual action]\n182: STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"[message]\"\n183: ```\n184: \n185: ## 6. Troubleshooting Display\n186: \n187: | Situation | Suggested Action |\n188: |-----------|------------------|\n189: | Need dependency-safe full rebuild | Use `/doctor:update` |\n190: | MCP servers are broken | Use `/doctor:mcp debug --fix` |\n191: | Fresh-install MCP servers | Use `/doctor:mcp install` |\n192: | Cross-target flag rejected | Use the suggested target from the error |\n193: | Route manifest parse error | Run `bash .opencode/commands/doctor/scripts/route-validate.sh` |\n194: \n195: End interactive presentations with: `What would you like to do next?`\n\n(End of file - total 195 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# /doctor Presentation Contract\n\nThis file is the single source of truth for user-facing presentation in `/doctor <target>`: startup questions, subsystem manifest display, setup dashboards, diagnostic dashboards, result templates, troubleshooting, and next-step text. The command router owns target resolution and asset routing only. The workflow YAML owns execution behavior.\n\n## 1. Startup Presentation\n\nWhen `$ARGUMENTS` lacks a recognized positional target, ask this prompt first after reading `_routes.yaml`.\n\n```text\nWhat do you want to do?\n\n   1) Update everything to match latest spec-kit release   (e.g. 3.3.0.0 -> 3.4.x)\n   2) Debug Memory database              (search index, spec-doc indexing)\n   3) Debug Embeddings                   (provider choice, hf-local health)\n   4) Debug Causal-Graph                 (spec lineage, drift_why)\n   5) Debug Code-Graph                   (structural index, stale/missed/bloat)\n   6) Debug Deep-Loop history            (research/review iteration graphs)\n   7) Re-tune Skill Advisor              (which skill gets recommended)\n   8) Audit Skill Description budget     (char counts, CI-friendly)\n   0) Full sweep - rebuild everything    (no migration, current schema)","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_speckit_presentation.md","text":"# /doctor Presentation Contract\n\nThis file is the single source of truth for user-facing presentation in `/doctor <target>`: startup questions, subsystem manifest display, setup dashboards, diagnostic dashboards, result templates, troubleshooting, and next-step text. The command router owns target resolution and asset routing only. The workflow YAML owns execution behavior.\n\n## 1. Startup Presentation\n\nWhen `$ARGUMENTS` lacks a recognized positional target, ask this prompt first after reading `_routes.yaml`.\n\n```text\nWhat do you want to do?\n\n   1) Update everything to match latest spec-kit release   (e.g. 3.3.0.0 -> 3.4.x)\n   2) Debug Memory database              (search index, spec-doc indexing)\n   3) Debug Embeddings                   (provider choice, hf-local health)\n   4) Debug Causal-Graph                 (spec lineage, drift_why)\n   5) Debug Code-Graph                   (structural index, stale/missed/bloat)\n   6) Debug Deep-Loop history            (research/review iteration graphs)\n   7) Re-tune Skill Advisor              (which skill gets recommended)\n   8) Audit Skill Description budget     (char counts, CI-friendly)\n   0) Full sweep - rebuild everything    (no migration, current schema)\n   H) Help me decide\n   X) Cancel\n```\n\nAccepted answers:\n\n| Answer | Result |\n|--------|--------|\n| `1` | Abort `/doctor`; display `Switch to /doctor:update --migrate for upgrade migration. Exiting /doctor.` |\n| `2` | target = `memory` |\n| `3` | target = `embeddings` |\n| `4` | target = `causal-graph` |\n| `5` | target = `code-graph` |\n| `6` | target = `deep-loop` |\n| `7` | target = `skill-advisor` |\n| `8` | target = `skill-budget` |\n| `0` | Abort `/doctor`; display `Switch to /doctor:update for full sweep. Exiting /doctor.` |\n| `H` | Show the help block, then ask the startup prompt again |\n| `X`, empty, `cancel` | `STATUS=CANCEL` |\n\nOn any other response, re-emit the menu once. On a second invalid response, return `STATUS=FAIL ERROR=unknown_selection`.\n\n### Help Block\n\n```text\nPick by symptom:\n\n   Search returns stale or empty results               -> 2  Memory\n   \"context-index__*.sqlite missing\" warning           -> 2  Memory\n   Model mismatch or hf-local loading state unclear    -> 3  Embeddings\n   memory_drift_why returns nothing                    -> 4  Causal-Graph\n   \"causal coverage <60%\" warning                      -> 4  Causal-Graph\n   \"code-graph stale/missed/bloat\" warning             -> 5  Code-Graph\n   \"code_graph_status: unhealthy\" or code-graph errors -> 5  Code-Graph\n   deep-research/deep-review iteration graph empty     -> 6  Deep-Loop\n   Convergence not detected between iterations         -> 6  Deep-Loop\n   Skill Advisor recommends the wrong skill            -> 7  Skill Advisor\n   New skill not appearing in advisor results          -> 7  Skill Advisor\n   Description char-count over hard cap                -> 8  Skill Budget\n\nQuick reference for confusable pairs:\n   Code-Graph (5) is STRUCTURAL - functions, files, dirs, AST\n   Skill Advisor (7) tunes ROUTING quality (which skill gets picked)\n   Skill Budget (8) audits CHAR COUNTS (frontmatter description size)\n\nPress 1-8, 0, or X.\n```\n\n### Unknown Target Failure\n\n```text\nUnknown target: [target]\nValid targets: memory, embeddings, causal-graph, code-graph, deep-loop, skill-advisor, skill-budget\nTry: /doctor list\nSTATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"unknown_target\"\n```\n\n### Cross-Target Flag Failure\n\n```text\nFlag '[flag]' is not valid for target '[target]'. Did you mean `/doctor [suggested-target] [flag]`?\nSTATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"cross_target_flag_injection\"\n```\n\n## 2. Subsystem Manifest Display\n\nRender this table for `list`, `?`, or `--list`. Values should mirror `_routes.yaml`.\n\n| Target | Workflow | Mutation Class | One-Line Purpose |\n|--------|----------|----------------|------------------|\n| `memory` | `doctor_memory.yaml` | read-only | Diagnose the memory continuity index; report drift and recommend action |\n| `embeddings` | `doctor_embeddings.yaml` | read-only | Inspect provider selection and hf-local model-server status |\n| `causal-graph` | `doctor_causal-graph.yaml` | read-only | Diagnose causal-edge integrity; sample drift and recommend candidates |\n| `code-graph` | `doctor_code-graph.yaml` | read-only | Diagnose code-graph index; report stale, missed, or bloat findings |\n| `deep-loop` | `doctor_deep-loop.yaml` | read-only | Diagnose deep-loop coverage graphs for research and review |\n| `skill-advisor` | `doctor_skill-advisor.yaml` | mutates | Audit and re-tune skill advisor scoring lanes |\n| `skill-budget` | `doctor_skill-budget.yaml` | read-only | Audit skill, command, and agent description budgets |\n\n## 3. Setup Prompts\n\nAsk only prompts needed for unresolved setup variables. Do not split a required setup question into multiple visible turns.\n\n### Memory Rebuild Mode\n\n```text\nRebuild mode?\n   1) Incremental - only changed files (fast, ~30s, default)\n   2) Full        - every file (5-15 min; needed after upgrade)\n```\n\nAccept `1`, `I`, or Enter as `incremental=true`. Accept `2`, `F`, or `full` as `incremental=false`.\n\n### Code-Graph Scope\n\nAsk this only when `--scope` was not passed and the operation needs a scope.\n\n```text\nCode-graph scope?\n   1) stale     - files indexed but mtime moved\n   2) missed    - files in repo but not indexed\n   3) bloat     - large dirs hogging the graph\n   4) all       - full scan (default)\n   5) excludes  - review the exclude config\n```\n\nAccept `1-5`; empty defaults to `all`.\n\n## 4. Setup Dashboard\n\nRender this compact panel after setup and before YAML execution when target resolution or flags were non-trivial.\n\n```text\nDOCTOR ROUTE SETUP\nTarget: [target]\nWorkflow: .opencode/commands/doctor/assets/[yaml]\nMutation class: [read-only|add-only|mutates]\nExecution mode: INTERACTIVE\nSetup values: [key=value list]\nPresentation: .opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_speckit_presentation.md\nNext: load workflow YAML\n```\n\n## 5. Diagnostic Result Templates\n\nUse the target workflow output contract when it provides a stricter report shape. Use these family templates for summary display and fallback rendering.\n\n### Read-Only Diagnostic Summary\n\n```text\nDOCTOR DIAGNOSTIC RESULT\nTarget: [target]\nWorkflow: [yaml]\nStatus: [OK|DEGRADED|STALE|MISSING|ATTENTION|EMPTY|CANCELLED|FAIL]\nMutation class: read-only\nEvidence: [health checks, counts, sampled records, or report path]\nRecommendation: [operator action or none]\nSTATUS=[status]\n```\n\n### Mutating Target Summary\n\n```text\nDOCTOR MUTATING RESULT\nTarget: [target]\nWorkflow: [yaml]\nStatus: [OK|CANCELLED|FAIL|ROLLED_BACK]\nApproved changes: [none|summary]\nFiles modified: [list or none]\nVerification: [checks run and result]\nRollback: [path or not required]\nSTATUS=[status]\n```\n\n### Failure Summary\n\n```text\nDOCTOR TARGET FAILED\nTarget: [target]\nStep: [setup|workflow phase]\nError: [message]\nNext: [recommended command or manual action]\nSTATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"[message]\"\n```\n\n## 6. Troubleshooting Display\n\n| Situation | Suggested Action |\n|-----------|------------------|\n| Need dependency-safe full rebuild | Use `/doctor:update` |\n| MCP servers are broken | Use `/doctor:mcp debug --fix` |\n| Fresh-install MCP servers | Use `/doctor:mcp install` |\n| Cross-target flag rejected | Use the suggested target from the error |\n| Route manifest parse error | Run `bash .opencode/commands/doctor/scripts/route-validate.sh` |\n\nEnd interactive presentations with: `What would you like to do next?`","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":195,"totalLines":195,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_speckit_presentation.md","time":{"start":1781143439462,"end":1781143439464}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_074c2a0376ef6969016a2a178f5dfc81918d2912a2b0419bb2"}},"id":"prt_eb46c0857001bAAMJWkuLVObqZ","sessionID":"ses_14b95d46bffeZ6ztCn3DXZD284","messageID":"msg_eb46bc4ab001n5EAhRr4mgfCrg"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781143439492,"sessionID":"ses_14b95d46bffeZ6ztCn3DXZD284","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_yF8YMjdEFMuX01JSA20RgEZv","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_mcp_presentation.md","offset":1,"limit":230},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_mcp_presentation.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # /doctor:mcp Presentation Contract\n2: \n3: This file is the single source of truth for user-facing presentation in `/doctor:mcp`: startup questions, MCP assessment dashboards, install/repair prompts, verification summaries, final reports, troubleshooting, and next-step text. The command router owns sub-action routing only. The workflow YAML owns execution behavior.\n4: \n5: ## 1. Startup Presentation\n6: \n7: When `$ARGUMENTS` lacks a positional sub-action, ask this prompt first.\n8: \n9: ```text\n10: What do you want to do with MCP servers?\n11:    1) Install fresh    (all 5 MCP servers from install guides)\n12:    2) Debug + repair   (diagnose failures, apply guided fixes)\n13:    X) Cancel\n14: ```\n15: \n16: Accepted answers:\n17: \n18: | Answer | Result |\n19: |--------|--------|\n20: | `1`, `I`, `install` | sub_action = `install` |\n21: | `2`, `D`, `debug` | sub_action = `debug` |\n22: | `X`, empty, `cancel` | `STATUS=CANCEL` |\n23: \n24: ### Unknown Sub-Action Failure\n25: \n26: ```text\n27: Unknown sub-action '[sub_action]'. Valid: install, debug. Try `/doctor:mcp install` or `/doctor:mcp debug`.\n28: STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"unknown_sub_action\"\n29: ```\n30: \n31: ### Cross-Sub-Action Flag Failures\n32: \n33: ```text\n34: Flag '--fix' is only valid for `debug`. Did you mean `/doctor:mcp debug --fix`?\n35: STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"cross_sub_action_flag_injection\"\n36: ```\n37: \n38: ```text\n39: Flag '--runtime' is only valid for `install`. Did you mean `/doctor:mcp install --runtime <name>`?\n40: STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"cross_sub_action_flag_injection\"\n41: ```\n42: \n43: ## 2. Setup Dashboard\n44: \n45: Render after sub-action and flags resolve.\n46: \n47: ```text\n48: DOCTOR MCP SETUP\n49: Sub-action: [install|debug]\n50: Workflow: .opencode/commands/doctor/assets/[doctor_mcp_install.yaml|doctor_mcp_debug.yaml]\n51: Server filter: [name|all]\n52: Runtime filter: [name|detected|n/a]\n53: Fix mode: [true|false|n/a]\n54: Presentation: .opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_mcp_presentation.md\n55: Next: load workflow YAML\n56: ```\n57: \n58: ## 3. Install Presentation\n59: \n60: ### Assessment Table\n61: \n62: ```text\n63: MCP INSTALL ASSESSMENT\n64: \n65: | Server | Status | Detail |\n66: |--------|--------|--------|\n67: | Spec Kit Memory | [INSTALLED|STALE|MISSING|SKIPPED] | [detail] |\n68: | Skill Advisor | [INSTALLED|STALE|MISSING|SKIPPED] | [detail] |\n69: | System Code Graph | [INSTALLED|STALE|MISSING|SKIPPED] | [detail] |\n70: | Code Mode | [INSTALLED|STALE|MISSING|SKIPPED] | [detail] |\n71: | Sequential Thinking | [INSTALLED|STALE|MISSING|SKIPPED] | [detail] |\n72: ```\n73: \n74: ### Install Decision Prompt\n75: \n76: ```text\n77: Assessment complete. How would you like to proceed?\n78: \n79: A) Install/reinstall all that need it (MISSING + STALE)\n80: B) Walk through each server interactively\n81: C) Only install MISSING servers (skip STALE)\n82: D) Cancel\n83: ```\n84: \n85: ### Per-Server Install Prompt\n86: \n87: ```text\n88: Ready to install [server label]:\n89: Commands: [install steps]\n90: Proceed? [Y/n/skip]\n91: ```\n92: \n93: ## 4. Debug Presentation\n94: \n95: ### Diagnostic Findings Table\n96: \n97: ```text\n98: MCP DEBUG FINDINGS\n99: \n100: | Server | Status | Issues |\n101: |--------|--------|--------|\n102: | Spec Kit Memory | [PASS|WARN|FAIL] | [summary] |\n103: | Skill Advisor | [PASS|WARN|FAIL] | [summary] |\n104: | System Code Graph | [PASS|WARN|FAIL] | [summary] |\n105: | Code Mode | [PASS|WARN|FAIL] | [summary] |\n106: | Sequential Thinking | [PASS|WARN|FAIL] | [summary] |\n107: ```\n108: \n109: ### Repair Decision Prompt\n110: \n111: ```text\n112: [fail_count] failure(s) and [warn_count] warning(s) found.\n113: \n114: A) Fix all issues automatically\n115: B) Walk through each issue interactively\n116: C) Show detailed report and stop\n117: ```\n118: \n119: ### Per-Issue Prompt\n120: \n121: ```text\n122: Issue: [server] - [check]\n123: Detail: [detail]\n124: Root cause: [hypothesis]\n125: Proposed fix: [repair description]\n126: Command: [repair command]\n127: \n128: Fix now? [Y/n/skip]\n129: ```\n130: \n131: ### Re-Verification Prompt\n132: \n133: ```text\n134: Verification complete: [resolved_count] fixed, [remaining_count] remaining.\n135: \n136: A) Investigate remaining issues\n137: B) Accept current state\n138: ```\n139: \n140: ## 5. Final Report Templates\n141: \n142: ### Install Final Report\n143: \n144: ```text\n145: MCP Install - Final Report\n146: \n147: | Server | Before | After | Action Taken |\n148: |--------|--------|-------|--------------|\n149: | Spec Kit Memory | [before] | [after] | [action] |\n150: | Skill Advisor | [before] | [after] | [action] |\n151: | System Code Graph | [before] | [after] | [action] |\n152: | Code Mode | [before] | [after] | [action] |\n153: | Sequential Thinking | [before] | [after] | [action] |\n154: \n155: Config wiring: [config_summary]\n156: \n157: Next Steps:\n158: - Restart your AI client to pick up MCP servers.\n159: - Test each registered MCP tool.\n160: - If issues persist: /doctor:mcp debug\n161: \n162: STATUS=[OK|CANCELLED|FAIL]\n163: ```\n164: \n165: ### Debug Final Report\n166: \n167: ```text\n168: MCP Doctor - Final Report\n169: \n170: | Server | Before | After | Status |\n171: |--------|--------|-------|--------|\n172: | Spec Kit Memory | [before] | [after] | [status] |\n173: | Skill Advisor | [before] | [after] | [status] |\n174: | System Code Graph | [before] | [after] | [status] |\n175: | Code Mode | [before] | [after] | [status] |\n176: | Sequential Thinking | [before] | [after] | [status] |\n177: \n178: Config wiring: [config_summary]\n179: Next Steps: [next_steps]\n180: STATUS=[OK|CANCELLED|FAIL]\n181: ```\n182: \n183: ## 6. Examples Display\n184: \n185: ```text\n186: Examples:\n187:   /doctor:mcp install\n188:   /doctor:mcp install --server mk-spec-memory\n189:   /doctor:mcp install --runtime claude\n190:   /doctor:mcp debug\n191:   /doctor:mcp debug --fix\n192:   /doctor:mcp debug --server mk_code_index --fix\n193: ```\n194: \n195: ## 7. Troubleshooting Display\n196: \n197: | Situation | Suggested Action |\n198: |-----------|------------------|\n199: | Install just finished | The install workflow runs the health check automatically |\n200: | Install prerequisites missing | Install Node >= 20.11.0, Python >= 3.11, npm, and npx, then rerun |\n201: | Debug repair did not take | Read the cited install guide and apply the manual install section |\n202: | MCP is OK but subsystem doctor fails | Use `/doctor <target>` for subsystem diagnostics |\n203: | Need full spec-kit rebuild | Run `/doctor:mcp debug --fix`, then `/doctor:update` |\n204: \n205: End interactive presentations with: `What would you like to do next?`\n\n(End of file - total 205 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# /doctor:mcp Presentation Contract\n\nThis file is the single source of truth for user-facing presentation in `/doctor:mcp`: startup questions, MCP assessment dashboards, install/repair prompts, verification summaries, final reports, troubleshooting, and next-step text. The command router owns sub-action routing only. The workflow YAML owns execution behavior.\n\n## 1. Startup Presentation\n\nWhen `$ARGUMENTS` lacks a positional sub-action, ask this prompt first.\n\n```text\nWhat do you want to do with MCP servers?\n   1) Install fresh    (all 5 MCP servers from install guides)\n   2) Debug + repair   (diagnose failures, apply guided fixes)\n   X) Cancel\n```\n\nAccepted answers:\n\n| Answer | Result |\n|--------|--------|\n| `1`, `I`, `install` | sub_action = `install` |","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_mcp_presentation.md","text":"# /doctor:mcp Presentation Contract\n\nThis file is the single source of truth for user-facing presentation in `/doctor:mcp`: startup questions, MCP assessment dashboards, install/repair prompts, verification summaries, final reports, troubleshooting, and next-step text. The command router owns sub-action routing only. The workflow YAML owns execution behavior.\n\n## 1. Startup Presentation\n\nWhen `$ARGUMENTS` lacks a positional sub-action, ask this prompt first.\n\n```text\nWhat do you want to do with MCP servers?\n   1) Install fresh    (all 5 MCP servers from install guides)\n   2) Debug + repair   (diagnose failures, apply guided fixes)\n   X) Cancel\n```\n\nAccepted answers:\n\n| Answer | Result |\n|--------|--------|\n| `1`, `I`, `install` | sub_action = `install` |\n| `2`, `D`, `debug` | sub_action = `debug` |\n| `X`, empty, `cancel` | `STATUS=CANCEL` |\n\n### Unknown Sub-Action Failure\n\n```text\nUnknown sub-action '[sub_action]'. Valid: install, debug. Try `/doctor:mcp install` or `/doctor:mcp debug`.\nSTATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"unknown_sub_action\"\n```\n\n### Cross-Sub-Action Flag Failures\n\n```text\nFlag '--fix' is only valid for `debug`. Did you mean `/doctor:mcp debug --fix`?\nSTATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"cross_sub_action_flag_injection\"\n```\n\n```text\nFlag '--runtime' is only valid for `install`. Did you mean `/doctor:mcp install --runtime <name>`?\nSTATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"cross_sub_action_flag_injection\"\n```\n\n## 2. Setup Dashboard\n\nRender after sub-action and flags resolve.\n\n```text\nDOCTOR MCP SETUP\nSub-action: [install|debug]\nWorkflow: .opencode/commands/doctor/assets/[doctor_mcp_install.yaml|doctor_mcp_debug.yaml]\nServer filter: [name|all]\nRuntime filter: [name|detected|n/a]\nFix mode: [true|false|n/a]\nPresentation: .opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_mcp_presentation.md\nNext: load workflow YAML\n```\n\n## 3. Install Presentation\n\n### Assessment Table\n\n```text\nMCP INSTALL ASSESSMENT\n\n| Server | Status | Detail |\n|--------|--------|--------|\n| Spec Kit Memory | [INSTALLED|STALE|MISSING|SKIPPED] | [detail] |\n| Skill Advisor | [INSTALLED|STALE|MISSING|SKIPPED] | [detail] |\n| System Code Graph | [INSTALLED|STALE|MISSING|SKIPPED] | [detail] |\n| Code Mode | [INSTALLED|STALE|MISSING|SKIPPED] | [detail] |\n| Sequential Thinking | [INSTALLED|STALE|MISSING|SKIPPED] | [detail] |\n```\n\n### Install Decision Prompt\n\n```text\nAssessment complete. How would you like to proceed?\n\nA) Install/reinstall all that need it (MISSING + STALE)\nB) Walk through each server interactively\nC) Only install MISSING servers (skip STALE)\nD) Cancel\n```\n\n### Per-Server Install Prompt\n\n```text\nReady to install [server label]:\nCommands: [install steps]\nProceed? [Y/n/skip]\n```\n\n## 4. Debug Presentation\n\n### Diagnostic Findings Table\n\n```text\nMCP DEBUG FINDINGS\n\n| Server | Status | Issues |\n|--------|--------|--------|\n| Spec Kit Memory | [PASS|WARN|FAIL] | [summary] |\n| Skill Advisor | [PASS|WARN|FAIL] | [summary] |\n| System Code Graph | [PASS|WARN|FAIL] | [summary] |\n| Code Mode | [PASS|WARN|FAIL] | [summary] |\n| Sequential Thinking | [PASS|WARN|FAIL] | [summary] |\n```\n\n### Repair Decision Prompt\n\n```text\n[fail_count] failure(s) and [warn_count] warning(s) found.\n\nA) Fix all issues automatically\nB) Walk through each issue interactively\nC) Show detailed report and stop\n```\n\n### Per-Issue Prompt\n\n```text\nIssue: [server] - [check]\nDetail: [detail]\nRoot cause: [hypothesis]\nProposed fix: [repair description]\nCommand: [repair command]\n\nFix now? [Y/n/skip]\n```\n\n### Re-Verification Prompt\n\n```text\nVerification complete: [resolved_count] fixed, [remaining_count] remaining.\n\nA) Investigate remaining issues\nB) Accept current state\n```\n\n## 5. Final Report Templates\n\n### Install Final Report\n\n```text\nMCP Install - Final Report\n\n| Server | Before | After | Action Taken |\n|--------|--------|-------|--------------|\n| Spec Kit Memory | [before] | [after] | [action] |\n| Skill Advisor | [before] | [after] | [action] |\n| System Code Graph | [before] | [after] | [action] |\n| Code Mode | [before] | [after] | [action] |\n| Sequential Thinking | [before] | [after] | [action] |\n\nConfig wiring: [config_summary]\n\nNext Steps:\n- Restart your AI client to pick up MCP servers.\n- Test each registered MCP tool.\n- If issues persist: /doctor:mcp debug\n\nSTATUS=[OK|CANCELLED|FAIL]\n```\n\n### Debug Final Report\n\n```text\nMCP Doctor - Final Report\n\n| Server | Before | After | Status |\n|--------|--------|-------|--------|\n| Spec Kit Memory | [before] | [after] | [status] |\n| Skill Advisor | [before] | [after] | [status] |\n| System Code Graph | [before] | [after] | [status] |\n| Code Mode | [before] | [after] | [status] |\n| Sequential Thinking | [before] | [after] | [status] |\n\nConfig wiring: [config_summary]\nNext Steps: [next_steps]\nSTATUS=[OK|CANCELLED|FAIL]\n```\n\n## 6. Examples Display\n\n```text\nExamples:\n  /doctor:mcp install\n  /doctor:mcp install --server mk-spec-memory\n  /doctor:mcp install --runtime claude\n  /doctor:mcp debug\n  /doctor:mcp debug --fix\n  /doctor:mcp debug --server mk_code_index --fix\n```\n\n## 7. Troubleshooting Display\n\n| Situation | Suggested Action |\n|-----------|------------------|\n| Install just finished | The install workflow runs the health check automatically |\n| Install prerequisites missing | Install Node >= 20.11.0, Python >= 3.11, npm, and npx, then rerun |\n| Debug repair did not take | Read the cited install guide and apply the manual install section |\n| MCP is OK but subsystem doctor fails | Use `/doctor <target>` for subsystem diagnostics |\n| Need full spec-kit rebuild | Run `/doctor:mcp debug --fix`, then `/doctor:update` |\n\nEnd interactive presentations with: `What would you like to do next?`","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":205,"totalLines":205,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_mcp_presentation.md","time":{"start":1781143439486,"end":1781143439491}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_074c2a0376ef6969016a2a178f5e048191bf5d10980852eff4"}},"id":"prt_eb46c0869001r7oshjYLjpdzec","sessionID":"ses_14b95d46bffeZ6ztCn3DXZD284","messageID":"msg_eb46bc4ab001n5EAhRr4mgfCrg"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781143439617,"sessionID":"ses_14b95d46bffeZ6ztCn3DXZD284","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_kXQL6dSCFz9lJtsFcMjy0gAV","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/doctor/mcp.md","offset":1,"limit":120},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/doctor/mcp.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: description: Install or repair MCP servers via /doctor:mcp <install|debug> sub-action routing.\n3: argument-hint: \"<install|debug> [--server <name>] [--runtime <name>] [--fix]\"\n4: allowed-tools: Read, Bash, Grep, Glob, Edit, Write\n5: ---\n6: <!-- skill_agent: system-spec-kit -->\n7: \n8: # /doctor:mcp Router\n9: \n10: This command is a thin router. It resolves the MCP sub-action and setup values, then loads the matching workflow YAML and the presentation contract.\n11: \n12: ## Router Contract\n13: \n14: Do not dispatch agents from this Markdown file. Do not edit workflow YAML while executing this command.\n15: \n16: Load the presentation contract before showing startup questions, setup dashboards, approval prompts, MCP health dashboards, result summaries, or next-step text.\n17: \n18: ## Owned Assets\n19: \n20: | Purpose | Asset |\n21: |---------|-------|\n22: | Presentation source of truth | `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_mcp_presentation.md` |\n23: | Install workflow | `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_mcp_install.yaml` |\n24: | Debug workflow | `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_mcp_debug.yaml` |\n25: \n26: No workflow-asset gap exists for this command.\n27: \n28: ## Execution Order\n29: \n30: 1. Read `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_mcp_presentation.md`.\n31: 2. Parse the first positional token from `$ARGUMENTS` as `sub_action`.\n32: 3. If `sub_action` is missing, ask the presentation contract's sub-action prompt and wait.\n33: 4. If `sub_action` is not `install` or `debug`, render the presentation contract's unknown-sub-action failure and stop.\n34: 5. Bind the workflow asset:\n35:    - `install` -> `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_mcp_install.yaml`\n36:    - `debug` -> `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_mcp_debug.yaml`\n37: 6. Parse remaining flags using only the selected sub-action schema:\n38:    - `install`: `--server <name>`, `--runtime <name>`\n39:    - `debug`: `--fix`, `--server <name>`\n40: 7. Reject cross-sub-action flags before YAML load using the presentation contract's error wording.\n41: 8. Load the selected workflow YAML and execute it step by step.\n42: 9. Use the presentation contract, not this router, for user prompts, dashboards, result summaries, and next-step display.\n43: \n44: ## Routing Rules\n45: \n46: - The sub-action is positional and must be parsed before flags.\n47: - No mode suffix is supported.\n48: - `install` and `debug` have overlapping `--server` flag names; keep their schemas separate.\n49: - If any referenced asset is missing, stop and report the missing path.\n50: - This command repairs MCP infrastructure itself; subsystem database diagnostics stay under `/doctor <target>` and `/doctor:update`.\n51: - The YAML owns workflow behavior; the presentation Markdown owns visible wording and layout.\n52: \n53: ## Presentation Boundary\n54: \n55: The following content lives only in `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_mcp_presentation.md`:\n56: \n57: - Sub-action menu, accepted answers, and cancellation display.\n58: - Unknown-sub-action and cross-sub-action flag errors.\n59: - MCP assessment, install, repair, verification, and final-report display templates.\n60: - Examples, troubleshooting display, and next-step text.\n61: \n62: User request: {{args}}\n\n(End of file - total 62 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ndescription: Install or repair MCP servers via /doctor:mcp <install|debug> sub-action routing.\nargument-hint: \"<install|debug> [--server <name>] [--runtime <name>] [--fix]\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Bash, Grep, Glob, Edit, Write\n---\n<!-- skill_agent: system-spec-kit -->\n\n# /doctor:mcp Router\n\nThis command is a thin router. It resolves the MCP sub-action and setup values, then loads the matching workflow YAML and the presentation contract.\n\n## Router Contract\n\nDo not dispatch agents from this Markdown file. Do not edit workflow YAML while executing this command.\n\nLoad the presentation contract before showing startup questions, setup dashboards, approval prompts, MCP health dashboards, result summaries, or next-step text.\n\n## Owned Assets\n\n| Purpose | Asset |","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/doctor/mcp.md","text":"---\ndescription: Install or repair MCP servers via /doctor:mcp <install|debug> sub-action routing.\nargument-hint: \"<install|debug> [--server <name>] [--runtime <name>] [--fix]\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Bash, Grep, Glob, Edit, Write\n---\n<!-- skill_agent: system-spec-kit -->\n\n# /doctor:mcp Router\n\nThis command is a thin router. It resolves the MCP sub-action and setup values, then loads the matching workflow YAML and the presentation contract.\n\n## Router Contract\n\nDo not dispatch agents from this Markdown file. Do not edit workflow YAML while executing this command.\n\nLoad the presentation contract before showing startup questions, setup dashboards, approval prompts, MCP health dashboards, result summaries, or next-step text.\n\n## Owned Assets\n\n| Purpose | Asset |\n|---------|-------|\n| Presentation source of truth | `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_mcp_presentation.md` |\n| Install workflow | `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_mcp_install.yaml` |\n| Debug workflow | `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_mcp_debug.yaml` |\n\nNo workflow-asset gap exists for this command.\n\n## Execution Order\n\n1. Read `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_mcp_presentation.md`.\n2. Parse the first positional token from `$ARGUMENTS` as `sub_action`.\n3. If `sub_action` is missing, ask the presentation contract's sub-action prompt and wait.\n4. If `sub_action` is not `install` or `debug`, render the presentation contract's unknown-sub-action failure and stop.\n5. Bind the workflow asset:\n   - `install` -> `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_mcp_install.yaml`\n   - `debug` -> `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_mcp_debug.yaml`\n6. Parse remaining flags using only the selected sub-action schema:\n   - `install`: `--server <name>`, `--runtime <name>`\n   - `debug`: `--fix`, `--server <name>`\n7. Reject cross-sub-action flags before YAML load using the presentation contract's error wording.\n8. Load the selected workflow YAML and execute it step by step.\n9. Use the presentation contract, not this router, for user prompts, dashboards, result summaries, and next-step display.\n\n## Routing Rules\n\n- The sub-action is positional and must be parsed before flags.\n- No mode suffix is supported.\n- `install` and `debug` have overlapping `--server` flag names; keep their schemas separate.\n- If any referenced asset is missing, stop and report the missing path.\n- This command repairs MCP infrastructure itself; subsystem database diagnostics stay under `/doctor <target>` and `/doctor:update`.\n- The YAML owns workflow behavior; the presentation Markdown owns visible wording and layout.\n\n## Presentation Boundary\n\nThe following content lives only in `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_mcp_presentation.md`:\n\n- Sub-action menu, accepted answers, and cancellation display.\n- Unknown-sub-action and cross-sub-action flag errors.\n- MCP assessment, install, repair, verification, and final-report display templates.\n- Examples, troubleshooting display, and next-step text.\n\nUser request: {{args}}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":62,"totalLines":62,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/commands/doctor/mcp.md","time":{"start":1781143439613,"end":1781143439617}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_074c2a0376ef6969016a2a178f5e0c819194dc5909ad19ee6d"}},"id":"prt_eb46c08a8001ZgyYStcTJNDZ2f","sessionID":"ses_14b95d46bffeZ6ztCn3DXZD284","messageID":"msg_eb46bc4ab001n5EAhRr4mgfCrg"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781143439629,"sessionID":"ses_14b95d46bffeZ6ztCn3DXZD284","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_9GjHvyVjnEAgYysfBmYRiNHL","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/doctor/update.md","offset":1,"limit":110},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/doctor/update.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: description: Rebuild spec-kit runtime databases in dependency-safe order through the interactive confirm workflow.\n3: argument-hint: \"[--force] [--no-snapshot] [--cleanup-legacy] [--migrate] [--keep-snapshots] [--resume-bootstrap]\"\n4: allowed-tools: Read, Bash, Grep, Glob, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_status, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_query, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_context, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_scan, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_apply, mcp__mk_code_index__detect_changes, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_health, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_drift_why, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_link, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_recommend, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_status, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_validate, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_rebuild, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__skill_graph_scan, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__skill_graph_query, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__skill_graph_status, mcp__mk_spec_memory__eval_run_ablation, mcp__mk_spec_memory__session_health\n5: ---\n6: <!-- skill_agent: system-spec-kit -->\n7: \n8: # /doctor:update Router\n9: \n10: This command is a thin router. It resolves update flags and setup values, then loads the update workflow YAML and the presentation contract.\n11: \n12: ## Router Contract\n13: \n14: Do not dispatch agents from this Markdown file. Do not edit workflow YAML while executing this command.\n15: \n16: Load the presentation contract before showing startup questions, mid-run prompts, dashboards, validation displays, result summaries, or restart-required text.\n17: \n18: ## Owned Assets\n19: \n20: | Purpose | Asset |\n21: |---------|-------|\n22: | Presentation source of truth | `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_update_presentation.md` |\n23: | Update workflow | `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_update.yaml` |\n24: \n25: No workflow-asset gap exists for this command.\n26: \n27: ## Execution Order\n28: \n29: 1. Read `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_update_presentation.md`.\n30: 2. Parse `$ARGUMENTS` for supported flags: `--force`, `--no-snapshot`, `--cleanup-legacy`, `--migrate`, `--keep-snapshots`, and `--resume-bootstrap`.\n31: 3. Bind setup values: `execution_mode`, `intent`, `force`, `no_snapshot`, `cleanup_legacy`, `migrate`, `keep_snapshots`, `resume_bootstrap`, and `skip_status_check`.\n32: 4. If `--force` is absent, ask the presentation contract's initial confirmation prompt and wait.\n33: 5. If `--force` is present, auto-answer the initial confirmation as proceed; the active-MCP-client prompt still fires when the workflow detects active clients.\n34: 6. Load `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_update.yaml` only after every setup value is bound.\n35: 7. Execute the YAML phase by phase.\n36: 8. Use the presentation contract, not this router, for user prompts, dashboards, result summaries, restart-required display, and next-step text.\n37: \n38: ## Routing Rules\n39: \n40: - This command is always interactive; deleted mode suffixes are invalid.\n41: - Snapshot every SQLite database before mutation unless `--no-snapshot` was explicitly passed.\n42: - If runtime bootstrap changes layout or build artifacts, stop with `STATUS=RESTART_REQUIRED`; start a fresh OpenCode process and rerun with `--resume-bootstrap`.\n43: - `--migrate` reads the migration manifest and refuses on gaps; this command does not create or edit that manifest.\n44: - `--cleanup-legacy` prompts per manifest-listed legacy file; no silent deletion.\n45: - Acquire the update flock before probes or mutations that can enter the database rebuild path.\n46: - Every terminal path writes the update state log defined by the YAML workflow.\n47: - If any referenced asset is missing, stop and report the missing path.\n48: - The YAML owns workflow behavior; the presentation Markdown owns visible wording and layout.\n49: \n50: ## Presentation Boundary\n51: \n52: The following content lives only in `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_update_presentation.md`:\n53: \n54: - Initial confirmation and mid-run prompt catalog.\n55: - Cross-subsystem health dashboard layout.\n56: - Status output, state-log, snapshot, restart-required, and failure display templates.\n57: - Related-command and next-step display text.\n58: \n59: User request: {{args}}\n\n(End of file - total 59 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ndescription: Rebuild spec-kit runtime databases in dependency-safe order through the interactive confirm workflow.\nargument-hint: \"[--force] [--no-snapshot] [--cleanup-legacy] [--migrate] [--keep-snapshots] [--resume-bootstrap]\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Bash, Grep, Glob, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_status, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_query, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_context, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_scan, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_apply, mcp__mk_code_index__detect_changes, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_health, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_drift_why, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_link, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_recommend, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_status, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_validate, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_rebuild, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__skill_graph_scan, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__skill_graph_query, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__skill_graph_status, mcp__mk_spec_memory__eval_run_ablation, mcp__mk_spec_memory__session_health\n---\n<!-- skill_agent: system-spec-kit -->\n\n# /doctor:update Router\n\nThis command is a thin router. It resolves update flags and setup values, then loads the update workflow YAML and the presentation contract.\n\n## Router Contract\n\nDo not dispatch agents from this Markdown file. Do not edit workflow YAML while executing this command.\n\nLoad the presentation contract before showing startup questions, mid-run prompts, dashboards, validation displays, result summaries, or restart-required text.\n\n## Owned Assets\n\n| Purpose | Asset |","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/doctor/update.md","text":"---\ndescription: Rebuild spec-kit runtime databases in dependency-safe order through the interactive confirm workflow.\nargument-hint: \"[--force] [--no-snapshot] [--cleanup-legacy] [--migrate] [--keep-snapshots] [--resume-bootstrap]\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Bash, Grep, Glob, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_status, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_query, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_context, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_scan, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_apply, mcp__mk_code_index__detect_changes, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_health, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_drift_why, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_causal_link, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_recommend, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_status, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_validate, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_rebuild, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__skill_graph_scan, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__skill_graph_query, mcp__mk_skill_advisor__skill_graph_status, mcp__mk_spec_memory__eval_run_ablation, mcp__mk_spec_memory__session_health\n---\n<!-- skill_agent: system-spec-kit -->\n\n# /doctor:update Router\n\nThis command is a thin router. It resolves update flags and setup values, then loads the update workflow YAML and the presentation contract.\n\n## Router Contract\n\nDo not dispatch agents from this Markdown file. Do not edit workflow YAML while executing this command.\n\nLoad the presentation contract before showing startup questions, mid-run prompts, dashboards, validation displays, result summaries, or restart-required text.\n\n## Owned Assets\n\n| Purpose | Asset |\n|---------|-------|\n| Presentation source of truth | `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_update_presentation.md` |\n| Update workflow | `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_update.yaml` |\n\nNo workflow-asset gap exists for this command.\n\n## Execution Order\n\n1. Read `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_update_presentation.md`.\n2. Parse `$ARGUMENTS` for supported flags: `--force`, `--no-snapshot`, `--cleanup-legacy`, `--migrate`, `--keep-snapshots`, and `--resume-bootstrap`.\n3. Bind setup values: `execution_mode`, `intent`, `force`, `no_snapshot`, `cleanup_legacy`, `migrate`, `keep_snapshots`, `resume_bootstrap`, and `skip_status_check`.\n4. If `--force` is absent, ask the presentation contract's initial confirmation prompt and wait.\n5. If `--force` is present, auto-answer the initial confirmation as proceed; the active-MCP-client prompt still fires when the workflow detects active clients.\n6. Load `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_update.yaml` only after every setup value is bound.\n7. Execute the YAML phase by phase.\n8. Use the presentation contract, not this router, for user prompts, dashboards, result summaries, restart-required display, and next-step text.\n\n## Routing Rules\n\n- This command is always interactive; deleted mode suffixes are invalid.\n- Snapshot every SQLite database before mutation unless `--no-snapshot` was explicitly passed.\n- If runtime bootstrap changes layout or build artifacts, stop with `STATUS=RESTART_REQUIRED`; start a fresh OpenCode process and rerun with `--resume-bootstrap`.\n- `--migrate` reads the migration manifest and refuses on gaps; this command does not create or edit that manifest.\n- `--cleanup-legacy` prompts per manifest-listed legacy file; no silent deletion.\n- Acquire the update flock before probes or mutations that can enter the database rebuild path.\n- Every terminal path writes the update state log defined by the YAML workflow.\n- If any referenced asset is missing, stop and report the missing path.\n- The YAML owns workflow behavior; the presentation Markdown owns visible wording and layout.\n\n## Presentation Boundary\n\nThe following content lives only in `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_update_presentation.md`:\n\n- Initial confirmation and mid-run prompt catalog.\n- Cross-subsystem health dashboard layout.\n- Status output, state-log, snapshot, restart-required, and failure display templates.\n- Related-command and next-step display text.\n\nUser request: {{args}}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":59,"totalLines":59,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/commands/doctor/update.md","time":{"start":1781143439627,"end":1781143439628}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_074c2a0376ef6969016a2a178f5e188191947f9b8904c6622e"}},"id":"prt_eb46c08ff001uTgg99Hr263Jnn","sessionID":"ses_14b95d46bffeZ6ztCn3DXZD284","messageID":"msg_eb46bc4ab001n5EAhRr4mgfCrg"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781143439638,"sessionID":"ses_14b95d46bffeZ6ztCn3DXZD284","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_TrTPrVmwihvYSNwFKyHc9PoD","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_update_presentation.md","offset":1,"limit":230},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_update_presentation.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # /doctor:update Presentation Contract\n2: \n3: This file is the single source of truth for user-facing presentation in `/doctor:update`: startup confirmation, mid-run prompts, cross-subsystem dashboards, validation displays, status outputs, restart-required messages, related commands, and next-step text. The command router owns flag parsing and asset routing only. The workflow YAML owns execution behavior.\n4: \n5: ## 1. Startup Confirmation\n6: \n7: Ask this prompt before any mutating phase unless `--force=true`. Lightweight read-only status probes are allowed only after flag parsing.\n8: \n9: ```text\n10: /doctor:update rebuilds ALL spec-kit databases in dependency order with\n11: snapshots + auto-rollback on regression. ETA 8-25 min.\n12: \n13: Mid-run prompts:\n14:    SHORT  steps    -> auto (no prompt)\n15:    MEDIUM steps    -> 1 combined prompt   (Q-MED)\n16:    LONG-POLE step  -> ETA prompt + skip   (Q-LONG, 5-15 min)\n17: \n18:    1) Proceed\n19:    X) Cancel\n20: ```\n21: \n22: Accept `1`, `A`, `Y`, `Proceed`, or Enter as proceed. Accept `X`, `N`, or `Cancel` as `STATUS=CANCELLED`. If input is empty, ask again once; on second empty input, return `STATUS=CANCELLED`.\n23: \n24: ## 2. Mid-Run Prompt Catalog\n25: \n26: Use these prompts verbatim. Do not paraphrase, summarize, or split them into multiple messages.\n27: \n28: ### Q-MED - Combined Medium-Tier Prompt\n29: \n30: When: before `code_graph_scan` and/or `eval_run_ablation`. Suppressed if `--force=true`.\n31: \n32: ```text\n33: Medium-tier steps next:\n34:    code_graph_scan      ~1-3 min   (mutates code-graph.sqlite + config.json)\n35:    eval_run_ablation    ~2-4 min   (mutates speckit-eval.db)\n36: \n37: Phase 3 snapshots in place -> auto-rollback on gold-battery regression.\n38: \n39:    1) Run both\n40:    2) Run code_graph_scan only (skip eval)\n41:    X) Cancel + rollback\n42: ```\n43: \n44: Accept `1`, `A`, `Y`, or `Proceed` as both. Accept `2` or `Skip` as code-graph only. Accept `X`, `N`, or `Cancel` as rollback plus `STATUS=CANCELLED`. Empty input re-asks once; second empty input returns `STATUS=CANCELLED`.\n45: \n46: ### Q-LONG - Long-Pole ETA Prompt\n47: \n48: When: before `memory_index_scan` over context-index and vector-index. Suppressed if `--force=true`.\n49: \n50: ```text\n51: LONG-POLE: memory_index_scan over the active profile DBs (Memory MCP + vector index if Voyage/OpenAI keyed).\n52: \n53:    ETA      5-15 min  (depends on corpus size; Voyage/OpenAI add API throughput when keyed)\n54:    Mutates  full re-index   (rollback available via Phase 3 snapshot)\n55:    Network  Voyage/OpenAI API required only when keyed - confirm credentials\n56: \n57:    1) Proceed\n58:    2) Skip   (advisor -> STALE; deep-loop init still runs)\n59:    X) Cancel + rollback\n60: ```\n61: \n62: Accept `1`, `A`, `Y`, or `Proceed` as proceed. Accept `2` or `Skip` as skipped and marked stale. Accept `X`, `N`, or `Cancel` as rollback plus `STATUS=CANCELLED`. Empty input re-asks once; second empty input returns `STATUS=CANCELLED`.\n63: \n64: ### Q-PROBE - Active-MCP-Client Prompt\n65: \n66: When: Phase 2 detects one or more other MCP clients connected to the spec-kit memory server. Always fires; `--force` reduces it to a single confirmation rather than per-client prompts.\n67: \n68: ```text\n69: Active MCP client(s) detected:\n70:    [comma-separated client_id list]\n71: \n72: The rebuild will cancel their open transactions and stale their cache until reconnect.\n73: \n74:    1) Proceed anyway\n75:    X) Cancel  (rerun when clients are idle)\n76: ```\n77: \n78: Accept `1`, `A`, `Y`, or `Proceed` as proceed. Accept `X`, `N`, or `Cancel` as `STATUS=CANCELLED`. Empty input re-asks once; second empty input returns `STATUS=CANCELLED`.\n79: \n80: ### Q-LEGACY - Per-File Legacy Cleanup Prompt\n81: \n82: When: Phase 9 processes each file listed in the migration manifest's legacy cleanup targets and `--cleanup-legacy=true`.\n83: \n84: ```text\n85: Legacy file: [absolute path]\n86:    Reason:   [manifest reason string]\n87:    Size:     [human-readable size]\n88: \n89:    Y) Delete  (irreversible)\n90:    N) Keep    (default if empty)\n91:    A) Yes to ALL remaining\n92:    Q) Quit cleanup  (keep the rest, continue to Phase 10)\n93: ```\n94: \n95: Accept `Y` or `Delete` as delete. Accept `N`, `Keep`, `Skip`, or empty as keep. Accept `A` or `All` as auto-delete remaining. Accept `Q` or `Quit` as exit Phase 9 early.\n96: \n97: ### Q-FAIL - Step-Failure Recovery Prompt\n98: \n99: When: a step fails its first run and the 5-second-backoff retry. Suppressed if `--force=true`; force mode auto-rolls back.\n100: \n101: ```text\n102: Step \"[step_name]\" failed after retry.\n103:    Phase:    [N]\n104:    Exit:     [code]\n105:    Snapshot: [path]\n106: \n107: Error (last 5 stderr lines):\n108: [excerpt]\n109: \n110:    1) Rollback + cancel       (default if empty after re-ask)\n111:    2) Continue without rollback   (DANGEROUS - subsequent steps may regress)\n112:    3) Retry once more\n113: ```\n114: \n115: Accept `1`, `A`, `Y`, or `Rollback` as rollback plus `STATUS=ROLLED_BACK`. Accept `2` or `Continue` as log warning, skip step, and continue. Accept `3` or `Retry` as a third attempt. Empty input re-asks once; second empty input defaults to rollback.\n116: \n117: ## 3. Setup Dashboard\n118: \n119: Render after flag parsing and before YAML load.\n120: \n121: ```text\n122: DOCTOR UPDATE SETUP\n123: Workflow: .opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_update.yaml\n124: Presentation: .opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_update_presentation.md\n125: Mode: INTERACTIVE\n126: Flags: force=[true|false] no_snapshot=[true|false] cleanup_legacy=[true|false] migrate=[true|false] keep_snapshots=[true|false] resume_bootstrap=[true|false]\n127: Snapshots: [enabled|disabled]\n128: Next: load workflow YAML\n129: ```\n130: \n131: ## 4. Cross-Subsystem Health Dashboard\n132: \n133: Render before selecting dependency actions.\n134: \n135: ```text\n136: Cross-Subsystem Health Dashboard\n137: \n138: | Subsystem     | Status | Age | Coverage | Recommended Action |\n139: |---------------|--------|-----|----------|--------------------|\n140: | code-graph    | [OK|STALE|MISSING|REGRESSED] | [age] | [n/a|metric] | [scan|skip|rollback] |\n141: | context-index | [OK|STALE|MISSING|REGRESSED] | [age] | [metric] | [index-scan|skip|rollback] |\n142: | causal-edges  | [OK|LOW-COVERAGE|REGRESSED] | [age] | [metric] | [init-links|skip|rollback] |\n143: | skill-graph   | [OK|STALE|MISSING] | [age] | [n/a|metric] | [scan|skip] |\n144: | advisor       | [OK|INVALID|STALE] | [age] | [n/a|metric] | [rebuild|validate] |\n145: | deep-loop     | [OK|EMPTY|STALE] | [age] | [n/a|metric] | [upsert|skip] |\n146: | eval          | [OK|STALE|SKIPPED] | [age] | [n/a|metric] | [run-ablation|skip] |\n147: ```\n148: \n149: ## 5. Status Output Templates\n150: \n151: ### Final Status\n152: \n153: ```text\n154: Doctor Update Result\n155: \n156: Final status: STATUS=[OK|FAIL|ROLLED_BACK|CANCELLED|RESTART_REQUIRED]\n157: State log: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/database/.doctor-update.last-run.json\n158: Snapshots: [kept|cleaned|skipped]\n159: Touched subsystems: [list]\n160: Validation: [gold-battery and schema summary]\n161: ```\n162: \n163: ### Restart Required\n164: \n165: ```text\n166: STATUS=RESTART_REQUIRED\n167: \n168: Runtime bootstrap completed before database rebuild started.\n169: Restart OpenCode so MCP tools register, then rerun:\n170:   /doctor:update --resume-bootstrap\n171: ```\n172: \n173: ### Failure\n174: \n175: ```text\n176: STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"[message]\"\n177: State log: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/database/.doctor-update.last-run.json\n178: Failed phase: [phase]\n179: Next: inspect the state log and rerun with the safest applicable flag set.\n180: ```\n181: \n182: ### Rolled Back\n183: \n184: ```text\n185: STATUS=ROLLED_BACK\n186: Reason: [step failure|gold-battery regression|operator choice]\n187: Restored snapshots: [list]\n188: State log: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/database/.doctor-update.last-run.json\n189: ```\n190: \n191: ## 6. Related Commands Display\n192: \n193: | Command | When To Use |\n194: |---------|-------------|\n195: | `/doctor memory` | Isolated context-index and vector-index health diagnosis |\n196: | `/doctor causal-graph` | Isolated causal edge coverage diagnosis |\n197: | `/doctor deep-loop` | Isolated research/review coverage graph diagnosis |\n198: | `/doctor code-graph` | Isolated structural graph diagnosis |\n199: | `/doctor skill-advisor` | Advisor and skill-graph optimization pass |\n200: | `/doctor skill-budget` | Advisor budget/status helper |\n201: | `/doctor:mcp debug --fix` | MCP infrastructure repair before subsystem diagnostics |\n202: \n203: End interactive presentations with: `What would you like to do next?`\n\n(End of file - total 203 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# /doctor:update Presentation Contract\n\nThis file is the single source of truth for user-facing presentation in `/doctor:update`: startup confirmation, mid-run prompts, cross-subsystem dashboards, validation displays, status outputs, restart-required messages, related commands, and next-step text. The command router owns flag parsing and asset routing only. The workflow YAML owns execution behavior.\n\n## 1. Startup Confirmation\n\nAsk this prompt before any mutating phase unless `--force=true`. Lightweight read-only status probes are allowed only after flag parsing.\n\n```text\n/doctor:update rebuilds ALL spec-kit databases in dependency order with\nsnapshots + auto-rollback on regression. ETA 8-25 min.\n\nMid-run prompts:\n   SHORT  steps    -> auto (no prompt)\n   MEDIUM steps    -> 1 combined prompt   (Q-MED)\n   LONG-POLE step  -> ETA prompt + skip   (Q-LONG, 5-15 min)\n\n   1) Proceed\n   X) Cancel\n```","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_update_presentation.md","text":"# /doctor:update Presentation Contract\n\nThis file is the single source of truth for user-facing presentation in `/doctor:update`: startup confirmation, mid-run prompts, cross-subsystem dashboards, validation displays, status outputs, restart-required messages, related commands, and next-step text. The command router owns flag parsing and asset routing only. The workflow YAML owns execution behavior.\n\n## 1. Startup Confirmation\n\nAsk this prompt before any mutating phase unless `--force=true`. Lightweight read-only status probes are allowed only after flag parsing.\n\n```text\n/doctor:update rebuilds ALL spec-kit databases in dependency order with\nsnapshots + auto-rollback on regression. ETA 8-25 min.\n\nMid-run prompts:\n   SHORT  steps    -> auto (no prompt)\n   MEDIUM steps    -> 1 combined prompt   (Q-MED)\n   LONG-POLE step  -> ETA prompt + skip   (Q-LONG, 5-15 min)\n\n   1) Proceed\n   X) Cancel\n```\n\nAccept `1`, `A`, `Y`, `Proceed`, or Enter as proceed. Accept `X`, `N`, or `Cancel` as `STATUS=CANCELLED`. If input is empty, ask again once; on second empty input, return `STATUS=CANCELLED`.\n\n## 2. Mid-Run Prompt Catalog\n\nUse these prompts verbatim. Do not paraphrase, summarize, or split them into multiple messages.\n\n### Q-MED - Combined Medium-Tier Prompt\n\nWhen: before `code_graph_scan` and/or `eval_run_ablation`. Suppressed if `--force=true`.\n\n```text\nMedium-tier steps next:\n   code_graph_scan      ~1-3 min   (mutates code-graph.sqlite + config.json)\n   eval_run_ablation    ~2-4 min   (mutates speckit-eval.db)\n\nPhase 3 snapshots in place -> auto-rollback on gold-battery regression.\n\n   1) Run both\n   2) Run code_graph_scan only (skip eval)\n   X) Cancel + rollback\n```\n\nAccept `1`, `A`, `Y`, or `Proceed` as both. Accept `2` or `Skip` as code-graph only. Accept `X`, `N`, or `Cancel` as rollback plus `STATUS=CANCELLED`. Empty input re-asks once; second empty input returns `STATUS=CANCELLED`.\n\n### Q-LONG - Long-Pole ETA Prompt\n\nWhen: before `memory_index_scan` over context-index and vector-index. Suppressed if `--force=true`.\n\n```text\nLONG-POLE: memory_index_scan over the active profile DBs (Memory MCP + vector index if Voyage/OpenAI keyed).\n\n   ETA      5-15 min  (depends on corpus size; Voyage/OpenAI add API throughput when keyed)\n   Mutates  full re-index   (rollback available via Phase 3 snapshot)\n   Network  Voyage/OpenAI API required only when keyed - confirm credentials\n\n   1) Proceed\n   2) Skip   (advisor -> STALE; deep-loop init still runs)\n   X) Cancel + rollback\n```\n\nAccept `1`, `A`, `Y`, or `Proceed` as proceed. Accept `2` or `Skip` as skipped and marked stale. Accept `X`, `N`, or `Cancel` as rollback plus `STATUS=CANCELLED`. Empty input re-asks once; second empty input returns `STATUS=CANCELLED`.\n\n### Q-PROBE - Active-MCP-Client Prompt\n\nWhen: Phase 2 detects one or more other MCP clients connected to the spec-kit memory server. Always fires; `--force` reduces it to a single confirmation rather than per-client prompts.\n\n```text\nActive MCP client(s) detected:\n   [comma-separated client_id list]\n\nThe rebuild will cancel their open transactions and stale their cache until reconnect.\n\n   1) Proceed anyway\n   X) Cancel  (rerun when clients are idle)\n```\n\nAccept `1`, `A`, `Y`, or `Proceed` as proceed. Accept `X`, `N`, or `Cancel` as `STATUS=CANCELLED`. Empty input re-asks once; second empty input returns `STATUS=CANCELLED`.\n\n### Q-LEGACY - Per-File Legacy Cleanup Prompt\n\nWhen: Phase 9 processes each file listed in the migration manifest's legacy cleanup targets and `--cleanup-legacy=true`.\n\n```text\nLegacy file: [absolute path]\n   Reason:   [manifest reason string]\n   Size:     [human-readable size]\n\n   Y) Delete  (irreversible)\n   N) Keep    (default if empty)\n   A) Yes to ALL remaining\n   Q) Quit cleanup  (keep the rest, continue to Phase 10)\n```\n\nAccept `Y` or `Delete` as delete. Accept `N`, `Keep`, `Skip`, or empty as keep. Accept `A` or `All` as auto-delete remaining. Accept `Q` or `Quit` as exit Phase 9 early.\n\n### Q-FAIL - Step-Failure Recovery Prompt\n\nWhen: a step fails its first run and the 5-second-backoff retry. Suppressed if `--force=true`; force mode auto-rolls back.\n\n```text\nStep \"[step_name]\" failed after retry.\n   Phase:    [N]\n   Exit:     [code]\n   Snapshot: [path]\n\nError (last 5 stderr lines):\n[excerpt]\n\n   1) Rollback + cancel       (default if empty after re-ask)\n   2) Continue without rollback   (DANGEROUS - subsequent steps may regress)\n   3) Retry once more\n```\n\nAccept `1`, `A`, `Y`, or `Rollback` as rollback plus `STATUS=ROLLED_BACK`. Accept `2` or `Continue` as log warning, skip step, and continue. Accept `3` or `Retry` as a third attempt. Empty input re-asks once; second empty input defaults to rollback.\n\n## 3. Setup Dashboard\n\nRender after flag parsing and before YAML load.\n\n```text\nDOCTOR UPDATE SETUP\nWorkflow: .opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_update.yaml\nPresentation: .opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_update_presentation.md\nMode: INTERACTIVE\nFlags: force=[true|false] no_snapshot=[true|false] cleanup_legacy=[true|false] migrate=[true|false] keep_snapshots=[true|false] resume_bootstrap=[true|false]\nSnapshots: [enabled|disabled]\nNext: load workflow YAML\n```\n\n## 4. Cross-Subsystem Health Dashboard\n\nRender before selecting dependency actions.\n\n```text\nCross-Subsystem Health Dashboard\n\n| Subsystem     | Status | Age | Coverage | Recommended Action |\n|---------------|--------|-----|----------|--------------------|\n| code-graph    | [OK|STALE|MISSING|REGRESSED] | [age] | [n/a|metric] | [scan|skip|rollback] |\n| context-index | [OK|STALE|MISSING|REGRESSED] | [age] | [metric] | [index-scan|skip|rollback] |\n| causal-edges  | [OK|LOW-COVERAGE|REGRESSED] | [age] | [metric] | [init-links|skip|rollback] |\n| skill-graph   | [OK|STALE|MISSING] | [age] | [n/a|metric] | [scan|skip] |\n| advisor       | [OK|INVALID|STALE] | [age] | [n/a|metric] | [rebuild|validate] |\n| deep-loop     | [OK|EMPTY|STALE] | [age] | [n/a|metric] | [upsert|skip] |\n| eval          | [OK|STALE|SKIPPED] | [age] | [n/a|metric] | [run-ablation|skip] |\n```\n\n## 5. Status Output Templates\n\n### Final Status\n\n```text\nDoctor Update Result\n\nFinal status: STATUS=[OK|FAIL|ROLLED_BACK|CANCELLED|RESTART_REQUIRED]\nState log: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/database/.doctor-update.last-run.json\nSnapshots: [kept|cleaned|skipped]\nTouched subsystems: [list]\nValidation: [gold-battery and schema summary]\n```\n\n### Restart Required\n\n```text\nSTATUS=RESTART_REQUIRED\n\nRuntime bootstrap completed before database rebuild started.\nRestart OpenCode so MCP tools register, then rerun:\n  /doctor:update --resume-bootstrap\n```\n\n### Failure\n\n```text\nSTATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"[message]\"\nState log: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/database/.doctor-update.last-run.json\nFailed phase: [phase]\nNext: inspect the state log and rerun with the safest applicable flag set.\n```\n\n### Rolled Back\n\n```text\nSTATUS=ROLLED_BACK\nReason: [step failure|gold-battery regression|operator choice]\nRestored snapshots: [list]\nState log: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/database/.doctor-update.last-run.json\n```\n\n## 6. Related Commands Display\n\n| Command | When To Use |\n|---------|-------------|\n| `/doctor memory` | Isolated context-index and vector-index health diagnosis |\n| `/doctor causal-graph` | Isolated causal edge coverage diagnosis |\n| `/doctor deep-loop` | Isolated research/review coverage graph diagnosis |\n| `/doctor code-graph` | Isolated structural graph diagnosis |\n| `/doctor skill-advisor` | Advisor and skill-graph optimization pass |\n| `/doctor skill-budget` | Advisor budget/status helper |\n| `/doctor:mcp debug --fix` | MCP infrastructure repair before subsystem diagnostics |\n\nEnd interactive presentations with: `What would you like to do next?`","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":203,"totalLines":203,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_update_presentation.md","time":{"start":1781143439635,"end":1781143439637}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_074c2a0376ef6969016a2a178f5e208191bbdf8779161a5b88"}},"id":"prt_eb46c090e001j68nc9G7SDLubA","sessionID":"ses_14b95d46bffeZ6ztCn3DXZD284","messageID":"msg_eb46bc4ab001n5EAhRr4mgfCrg"}}
