{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1781143441576,"sessionID":"ses_14b95d46bffeZ6ztCn3DXZD284","part":{"id":"prt_eb46c10a7001Ipwvne40siKyU0","messageID":"msg_eb46c0b25001ymBwM0jF2Snl5R","sessionID":"ses_14b95d46bffeZ6ztCn3DXZD284","snapshot":"08452c522195b926f57a49b1383e0fe07431f0ca","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781143450867,"sessionID":"ses_14b95d46bffeZ6ztCn3DXZD284","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_4Dfh2U0WdyPsTlw0z8dM9BL6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_plan_presentation.md","offset":1,"limit":180},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_plan_presentation.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # SpecKit Plan Presentation Contract\n2: \n3: Presentation source of truth for `/speckit:plan`. The command router owns only mode selection and asset loading. Workflow YAML owns execution. This file owns visible prompts, dashboard layout, and final result displays.\n4: \n5: ## 1. Startup Presentation\n6: \n7: For `:confirm` or no suffix, the consolidated setup prompt is the first visible response. Ask all applicable questions once, then wait. No analysis or tool calls precede the prompt unless the workflow already has an explicit path that needs read-only folder-state classification.\n8: \n9: For `:auto`, do not show the consolidated prompt by default. Resolve setup through the auto-mode table below. Ask targeted questions only for fields marked Tier 2.\n10: \n11: ### Auto Pre-Bound Setup Answers\n12: \n13: Accept one optional marker block in the prompt body before applying defaults.\n14: \n15: ```yaml\n16: PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:\n17:   feature_description: Add passwordless login\n18:   spec_folder: <spec-folder>\n19:   execution_mode: AUTONOMOUS\n20:   dispatch_mode: single_agent\n21:   memory_choice: skip\n22:   research_intent: add_feature\n23:   context_integration: false\n24:   phase_decomposition: false\n25:   phase_count: 3\n26:   phase_names: \"\"\n27:   phase_folder: \"\"\n28:   intake_only: false\n29:   selected_level: \"\"\n30:   start_state: \"\"\n31:   repair_mode: \"\"\n32:   record_relationships: false\n33:   depends_on: \"\"\n34:   related_to: \"\"\n35:   supersedes: \"\"\n36: ```\n37: \n38: Unknown fields warn. Malformed lines are parse errors. Marker values override flags; omitted fields fall back to defaults.\n39: \n40: ### Auto Resolution Table\n41: \n42: | Field | Required | Default | Tier 2 |\n43: |-------|----------|---------|--------|\n44: | `feature_description` | Yes | none | No |\n45: | `spec_folder` | Yes | none | Yes, when feature is present but folder choice is ambiguous |\n46: | `execution_mode` | Yes | `AUTONOMOUS` under `:auto` | No |\n47: | `dispatch_mode` | Yes | `single_agent` | No |\n48: | `memory_choice` | No | `skip` when no prior continuity exists | No |\n49: | `research_intent` | Yes | none | Yes |\n50: | `context_integration` | No | `false` | No |\n51: | `phase_decomposition` | Yes | `false` | No |\n52: | `phase_count` | No | `3` | No |\n53: | `phase_names` | No | none | No |\n54: | `phase_folder` | No | none | No |\n55: | `intake_only` | No | `false` | No |\n56: | `selected_level` | No | none | No |\n57: | `start_state` | No | auto-detect | No |\n58: | `repair_mode` | No | none | No |\n59: | `record_relationships` | No | `false` | No |\n60: | `depends_on` | No | none | No |\n61: | `related_to` | No | none | No |\n62: | `supersedes` | No | none | No |\n63: \n64: ### Consolidated Prompt Template\n65: \n66: ```text\n67: SpecKit Plan setup\n68: \n69: Mode: [auto|confirm|ask]\n70: Feature flags: [with-context yes/no] [with-phases yes/no] [intake-only yes/no]\n71: \n72: Q0. Feature Description, if not provided: What feature should be planned?\n73: Q1. Spec Folder: A) Use existing  B) Create new  C) Update related  D) Skip documentation  E) Phase folder\n74: Q2. Execution Mode, if no suffix: A) Autonomous  B) Interactive\n75: Q3. Dispatch Mode: A) Single Agent  B) Multi-Agent (1+2)  C) Multi-Agent (1+3)\n76: Q4. Prior Work Context, only when prior records exist: A) Latest  B) Recent 3  C) Skip\n77: Q5. Research Intent: A) add_feature  B) fix_bug  C) refactor  D) understand\n78: Q6. Phase Decomposition, if not already enabled: A) No  B) Yes\n79: Q7. Phase Count, if phase decomposition is enabled and not provided: default 3\n80: Q8. Phase Names, if phase decomposition is enabled and not provided: optional comma-separated names\n81: \n82: If folder intake is required, include the intake interview in this same prompt.\n83: \n84: Reply format: \"B, A, A, C, A\" or \"Add auth, B, A, C, A\".\n85: ```\n86: \n87: Never split these questions into separate visible prompts. If `--intake-only` is present, stop after intake emit and do not continue to planning steps.\n88: \n89: ### Auto Fail-Fast Display\n90: \n91: ```text\n92: SpecKit Plan auto setup failed\n93: Missing required inputs: [field-list]\n94: Provide the missing inputs or rerun with :confirm.\n95: STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"missing required setup inputs\"\n96: ```\n97: \n98: ## 2. Dashboard Layout\n99: \n100: Use this compact progress panel whenever the user needs workflow visibility.\n101: \n102: ```text\n103: SPECKIT PLAN DASHBOARD\n104: Spec: [spec_path]\n105: Mode: [AUTONOMOUS|INTERACTIVE]\n106: Step: [current] / 8 - [step name]\n107: Inputs: feature=[set|missing] folder=[set|missing] intent=[value]\n108: Optional flows: context=[on|off] phases=[on|off] intake_only=[on|off]\n109: Artifacts: spec.md [status] | plan.md [status] | tasks.md [status] | checklist.md [status]\n110: Next: [next action]\n111: ```\n112: \n113: ### Deep-Context Checkpoint\n114: \n115: ```text\n116: WORKFLOW CHECKPOINT - Deep-Context Complete\n117: Context Report: [spec_folder]/context/context-report.md\n118: Reuse candidates: [N] | Integration points: [N] | Conventions: [N]\n119: Continue to specification? [Y/continue, n/skip]\n120: ```\n121: \n122: ### Phase-Decomposition Checkpoint\n123: \n124: ```text\n125: WORKFLOW CHECKPOINT - Phase Decomposition Complete\n126: Parent: [parent_folder] | Phases: [N] children created\n127: Continue planning first child ([first_child_folder])? [Y/n/review]\n128: ```\n129: \n130: ## 3. Results Display\n131: \n132: ### Success\n133: \n134: ```text\n135: SpecKit Planning Complete - All 8 steps executed.\n136: Artifacts: spec.md, plan.md, tasks.md, checklist.md when Level 2+, graph-metadata.json scaffolded, continuity refreshed in canonical spec docs\n137: Ready for: /speckit:implement [spec-folder-path]\n138: STATUS=OK PATH=[spec-folder-path]\n139: ```\n140: \n141: ### Failure\n142: \n143: ```text\n144: SpecKit Planning Failed\n145: Error: [description] | Step: [number]\n146: STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"[message]\"\n147: ```\n148: \n149: ### Next-Step Suggestions\n150: \n151: | Condition | Suggested Command | Reason |\n152: |-----------|-------------------|--------|\n153: | Ready to implement | `/speckit:implement [spec-folder-path]` | Continue to implementation |\n154: | Need stakeholder review | Share `plan.md` | Get approval before coding |\n155: | Technical uncertainty | `/deep:start-research-loop [topic]` | Investigate first |\n156: | Need continuity refresh | `/memory:save [spec-folder-path]` | Refresh indexed canonical continuity |\n157: \n158: End interactive presentations with: `What would you like to do next?`\n\n(End of file - total 158 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# SpecKit Plan Presentation Contract\n\nPresentation source of truth for `/speckit:plan`. The command router owns only mode selection and asset loading. Workflow YAML owns execution. This file owns visible prompts, dashboard layout, and final result displays.\n\n## 1. Startup Presentation\n\nFor `:confirm` or no suffix, the consolidated setup prompt is the first visible response. Ask all applicable questions once, then wait. No analysis or tool calls precede the prompt unless the workflow already has an explicit path that needs read-only folder-state classification.\n\nFor `:auto`, do not show the consolidated prompt by default. Resolve setup through the auto-mode table below. Ask targeted questions only for fields marked Tier 2.\n\n### Auto Pre-Bound Setup Answers\n\nAccept one optional marker block in the prompt body before applying defaults.\n\n```yaml\nPRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:\n  feature_description: Add passwordless login\n  spec_folder: <spec-folder>\n  execution_mode: AUTONOMOUS\n  dispatch_mode: single_agent","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_plan_presentation.md","text":"# SpecKit Plan Presentation Contract\n\nPresentation source of truth for `/speckit:plan`. The command router owns only mode selection and asset loading. Workflow YAML owns execution. This file owns visible prompts, dashboard layout, and final result displays.\n\n## 1. Startup Presentation\n\nFor `:confirm` or no suffix, the consolidated setup prompt is the first visible response. Ask all applicable questions once, then wait. No analysis or tool calls precede the prompt unless the workflow already has an explicit path that needs read-only folder-state classification.\n\nFor `:auto`, do not show the consolidated prompt by default. Resolve setup through the auto-mode table below. Ask targeted questions only for fields marked Tier 2.\n\n### Auto Pre-Bound Setup Answers\n\nAccept one optional marker block in the prompt body before applying defaults.\n\n```yaml\nPRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:\n  feature_description: Add passwordless login\n  spec_folder: <spec-folder>\n  execution_mode: AUTONOMOUS\n  dispatch_mode: single_agent\n  memory_choice: skip\n  research_intent: add_feature\n  context_integration: false\n  phase_decomposition: false\n  phase_count: 3\n  phase_names: \"\"\n  phase_folder: \"\"\n  intake_only: false\n  selected_level: \"\"\n  start_state: \"\"\n  repair_mode: \"\"\n  record_relationships: false\n  depends_on: \"\"\n  related_to: \"\"\n  supersedes: \"\"\n```\n\nUnknown fields warn. Malformed lines are parse errors. Marker values override flags; omitted fields fall back to defaults.\n\n### Auto Resolution Table\n\n| Field | Required | Default | Tier 2 |\n|-------|----------|---------|--------|\n| `feature_description` | Yes | none | No |\n| `spec_folder` | Yes | none | Yes, when feature is present but folder choice is ambiguous |\n| `execution_mode` | Yes | `AUTONOMOUS` under `:auto` | No |\n| `dispatch_mode` | Yes | `single_agent` | No |\n| `memory_choice` | No | `skip` when no prior continuity exists | No |\n| `research_intent` | Yes | none | Yes |\n| `context_integration` | No | `false` | No |\n| `phase_decomposition` | Yes | `false` | No |\n| `phase_count` | No | `3` | No |\n| `phase_names` | No | none | No |\n| `phase_folder` | No | none | No |\n| `intake_only` | No | `false` | No |\n| `selected_level` | No | none | No |\n| `start_state` | No | auto-detect | No |\n| `repair_mode` | No | none | No |\n| `record_relationships` | No | `false` | No |\n| `depends_on` | No | none | No |\n| `related_to` | No | none | No |\n| `supersedes` | No | none | No |\n\n### Consolidated Prompt Template\n\n```text\nSpecKit Plan setup\n\nMode: [auto|confirm|ask]\nFeature flags: [with-context yes/no] [with-phases yes/no] [intake-only yes/no]\n\nQ0. Feature Description, if not provided: What feature should be planned?\nQ1. Spec Folder: A) Use existing  B) Create new  C) Update related  D) Skip documentation  E) Phase folder\nQ2. Execution Mode, if no suffix: A) Autonomous  B) Interactive\nQ3. Dispatch Mode: A) Single Agent  B) Multi-Agent (1+2)  C) Multi-Agent (1+3)\nQ4. Prior Work Context, only when prior records exist: A) Latest  B) Recent 3  C) Skip\nQ5. Research Intent: A) add_feature  B) fix_bug  C) refactor  D) understand\nQ6. Phase Decomposition, if not already enabled: A) No  B) Yes\nQ7. Phase Count, if phase decomposition is enabled and not provided: default 3\nQ8. Phase Names, if phase decomposition is enabled and not provided: optional comma-separated names\n\nIf folder intake is required, include the intake interview in this same prompt.\n\nReply format: \"B, A, A, C, A\" or \"Add auth, B, A, C, A\".\n```\n\nNever split these questions into separate visible prompts. If `--intake-only` is present, stop after intake emit and do not continue to planning steps.\n\n### Auto Fail-Fast Display\n\n```text\nSpecKit Plan auto setup failed\nMissing required inputs: [field-list]\nProvide the missing inputs or rerun with :confirm.\nSTATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"missing required setup inputs\"\n```\n\n## 2. Dashboard Layout\n\nUse this compact progress panel whenever the user needs workflow visibility.\n\n```text\nSPECKIT PLAN DASHBOARD\nSpec: [spec_path]\nMode: [AUTONOMOUS|INTERACTIVE]\nStep: [current] / 8 - [step name]\nInputs: feature=[set|missing] folder=[set|missing] intent=[value]\nOptional flows: context=[on|off] phases=[on|off] intake_only=[on|off]\nArtifacts: spec.md [status] | plan.md [status] | tasks.md [status] | checklist.md [status]\nNext: [next action]\n```\n\n### Deep-Context Checkpoint\n\n```text\nWORKFLOW CHECKPOINT - Deep-Context Complete\nContext Report: [spec_folder]/context/context-report.md\nReuse candidates: [N] | Integration points: [N] | Conventions: [N]\nContinue to specification? [Y/continue, n/skip]\n```\n\n### Phase-Decomposition Checkpoint\n\n```text\nWORKFLOW CHECKPOINT - Phase Decomposition Complete\nParent: [parent_folder] | Phases: [N] children created\nContinue planning first child ([first_child_folder])? [Y/n/review]\n```\n\n## 3. Results Display\n\n### Success\n\n```text\nSpecKit Planning Complete - All 8 steps executed.\nArtifacts: spec.md, plan.md, tasks.md, checklist.md when Level 2+, graph-metadata.json scaffolded, continuity refreshed in canonical spec docs\nReady for: /speckit:implement [spec-folder-path]\nSTATUS=OK PATH=[spec-folder-path]\n```\n\n### Failure\n\n```text\nSpecKit Planning Failed\nError: [description] | Step: [number]\nSTATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"[message]\"\n```\n\n### Next-Step Suggestions\n\n| Condition | Suggested Command | Reason |\n|-----------|-------------------|--------|\n| Ready to implement | `/speckit:implement [spec-folder-path]` | Continue to implementation |\n| Need stakeholder review | Share `plan.md` | Get approval before coding |\n| Technical uncertainty | `/deep:start-research-loop [topic]` | Investigate first |\n| Need continuity refresh | `/memory:save [spec-folder-path]` | Refresh indexed canonical continuity |\n\nEnd interactive presentations with: `What would you like to do next?`","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":158,"totalLines":158,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_plan_presentation.md","time":{"start":1781143450861,"end":1781143450865}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0b7ed97bb5d36a2d016a2a179acbd08191840ac5d3a602ffca"}},"id":"prt_eb46c34cb0010EYdaKK8i5Awiu","sessionID":"ses_14b95d46bffeZ6ztCn3DXZD284","messageID":"msg_eb46c0b25001ymBwM0jF2Snl5R"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781143450887,"sessionID":"ses_14b95d46bffeZ6ztCn3DXZD284","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_TVTdwnffVHQ1dKZrsLtuYttM","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_resume_presentation.md","offset":1,"limit":170},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_resume_presentation.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # SpecKit Resume Presentation Contract\n2: \n3: Presentation source of truth for `/speckit:resume`. The command router owns only mode selection and asset loading. Workflow YAML owns execution. This file owns visible prompts, dashboard layout, and final result displays.\n4: \n5: ## 1. Startup Presentation\n6: \n7: For `:confirm` or no suffix, default to interactive recovery and confirm ambiguous session choices. For `:auto`, resolve setup without prompting when a valid spec folder or high-confidence candidate exists.\n8: \n9: ### Auto Pre-Bound Setup Answers\n10: \n11: ```yaml\n12: PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:\n13:   spec_folder: <spec-folder>\n14:   phase_folder: \"\"\n15:   no_redirect: false\n16:   detection_method: provided\n17:   execution_mode: AUTONOMOUS\n18:   continuation_choice: indexed-continuity\n19:   artifact_recovery_choice: continue_anyway\n20:   memory_choice: fast\n21:   artifacts_valid: true\n22:   continuity_sources_available: yes\n23: ```\n24: \n25: Unknown fields warn. Malformed lines are parse errors. Marker values override flags; omitted fields fall back to defaults.\n26: \n27: ### Auto Resolution Table\n28: \n29: | Field | Required | Default | Tier 2 |\n30: |-------|----------|---------|--------|\n31: | `spec_folder` | Yes | none | Yes, when multiple viable folders are detected |\n32: | `phase_folder` | No | none | No |\n33: | `no_redirect` | No | `false` | No |\n34: | `detection_method` | Yes | auto-detect | No |\n35: | `execution_mode` | Yes | `AUTONOMOUS` under `:auto` | No |\n36: | `continuation_choice` | No | none | Yes, only when handoff and indexed continuity disagree |\n37: | `artifact_recovery_choice` | No | `continue_anyway` under resume auto mode | No |\n38: | `memory_choice` | No | `fast` | No |\n39: | `artifacts_valid` | Yes | auto-detect | No |\n40: | `continuity_sources_available` | No | auto-detect | No |\n41: \n42: ### Consolidated Prompt Template\n43: \n44: ```text\n45: SpecKit Resume setup\n46: \n47: Q0. Spec Folder, if not detected or provided: A) List and select  B) Start new with /speckit:complete  C) Cancel  E) Phase folder\n48: Q1. Confirm Detected Session, if auto-detected: A) Yes, resume  B) Select different folder  C) Cancel\n49: Q2. Continuation Validation, if handoff and indexed continuity disagree: A) Use handoff  B) Use indexed continuity  C) Investigate first\n50: Q3. Missing Artifacts, if required artifacts are incomplete: A) Run /speckit:plan  B) Select different folder  C) Continue anyway\n51: Q4. Recovery Depth, when the canonical packet is thin: A) Fast resume  B) Fill missing next step or blockers  C) Deeper context  D) Canonical artifacts only\n52: \n53: Reply format: \"A, A\" or \"A, A, B\".\n54: ```\n55: \n56: Never split these questions into separate visible prompts. Prefer the canonical file ladder before supplemental memory enrichment.\n57: \n58: ### Auto Fail-Fast Display\n59: \n60: ```text\n61: SpecKit Resume auto setup failed\n62: Missing required inputs: [field-list]\n63: Provide a spec folder or rerun with :confirm.\n64: STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"missing required setup inputs\"\n65: ```\n66: \n67: ## 2. Dashboard Layout\n68: \n69: ```text\n70: SPECKIT RESUME DASHBOARD\n71: Spec: [spec_path]\n72: Mode: [AUTONOMOUS|INTERACTIVE]\n73: Detection: [provided|phase-folder|ranked|none]\n74: Artifacts: spec.md [status] | plan.md [status] | tasks.md [status]\n75: Continuity source: [handover|continuity|spec_docs|memory_context|memory_search|combined]\n76: Progress: [done]/[total] tasks | checklist [done]/[total]\n77: Confidence: [high|medium|low]\n78: Next: [next safe action]\n79: ```\n80: \n81: ### Session Selection Panel\n82: \n83: ```text\n84: Found session candidate\n85: Spec: [spec_path]\n86: Last activity: [timestamp]\n87: Artifacts valid: [yes|partial|no]\n88: Resume this session? [Confirm / Select Different / Cancel]\n89: ```\n90: \n91: ### Recovery Depth Panel\n92: \n93: ```text\n94: Recovery depth\n95: A) Fast resume - current brief is enough\n96: B) Fill missing next step / blockers - target only missing essentials\n97: C) Deep context - enrich the canonical packet if essentials remain thin\n98: D) Artifacts only - use handover, continuity, and spec docs without extra memory\n99: ```\n100: \n101: ### Stale Session Warning\n102: \n103: ```text\n104: Stale session warning\n105: Last activity: [date]\n106: Context may be outdated.\n107: A) Resume anyway  B) Fresh start  C) Review first  D) Cancel\n108: ```\n109: \n110: ## 3. Results Display\n111: \n112: ### Resume Brief\n113: \n114: ```text\n115: RESUME BRIEF\n116: Spec: [path]\n117: Confidence: [high|medium|low] | Source: [handover|continuity|spec_docs|mcp_enrichment|combined]\n118: Now: [phase/current task]\n119: Last confirmed: [action]\n120: Next safe action: [action]\n121: Blockers: [none|details]\n122: Progress: [X]% ([done]/[total] tasks)\n123: Why this is next: [short reason based on tasks/checklist/memory]\n124: ```\n125: \n126: ### No Session\n127: \n128: ```text\n129: No active SpecKit session found.\n130: Provide a spec folder path or start a new packet with /speckit:complete.\n131: STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"no active session\"\n132: ```\n133: \n134: ### Next-Step Suggestions\n135: \n136: | Condition | Suggested Command | Reason |\n137: |-----------|-------------------|--------|\n138: | Planning incomplete | `/speckit:plan [feature-description]` | Complete planning phase |\n139: | Ready to implement | `/speckit:implement [spec-folder-path]` | Continue implementation |\n140: | Implementation in progress | Continue from last task | Resume where work stopped |\n141: | Need broader history | `/memory:search history [spec-folder]` | Inspect prior context |\n142: | Ending again | `/memory:save [spec-folder-path]` | Refresh continuity before pausing |\n143: \n144: End interactive presentations with: `What would you like to do next?`\n\n(End of file - total 144 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# SpecKit Resume Presentation Contract\n\nPresentation source of truth for `/speckit:resume`. The command router owns only mode selection and asset loading. Workflow YAML owns execution. This file owns visible prompts, dashboard layout, and final result displays.\n\n## 1. Startup Presentation\n\nFor `:confirm` or no suffix, default to interactive recovery and confirm ambiguous session choices. For `:auto`, resolve setup without prompting when a valid spec folder or high-confidence candidate exists.\n\n### Auto Pre-Bound Setup Answers\n\n```yaml\nPRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:\n  spec_folder: <spec-folder>\n  phase_folder: \"\"\n  no_redirect: false\n  detection_method: provided\n  execution_mode: AUTONOMOUS\n  continuation_choice: indexed-continuity\n  artifact_recovery_choice: continue_anyway\n  memory_choice: fast","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_resume_presentation.md","text":"# SpecKit Resume Presentation Contract\n\nPresentation source of truth for `/speckit:resume`. The command router owns only mode selection and asset loading. Workflow YAML owns execution. This file owns visible prompts, dashboard layout, and final result displays.\n\n## 1. Startup Presentation\n\nFor `:confirm` or no suffix, default to interactive recovery and confirm ambiguous session choices. For `:auto`, resolve setup without prompting when a valid spec folder or high-confidence candidate exists.\n\n### Auto Pre-Bound Setup Answers\n\n```yaml\nPRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:\n  spec_folder: <spec-folder>\n  phase_folder: \"\"\n  no_redirect: false\n  detection_method: provided\n  execution_mode: AUTONOMOUS\n  continuation_choice: indexed-continuity\n  artifact_recovery_choice: continue_anyway\n  memory_choice: fast\n  artifacts_valid: true\n  continuity_sources_available: yes\n```\n\nUnknown fields warn. Malformed lines are parse errors. Marker values override flags; omitted fields fall back to defaults.\n\n### Auto Resolution Table\n\n| Field | Required | Default | Tier 2 |\n|-------|----------|---------|--------|\n| `spec_folder` | Yes | none | Yes, when multiple viable folders are detected |\n| `phase_folder` | No | none | No |\n| `no_redirect` | No | `false` | No |\n| `detection_method` | Yes | auto-detect | No |\n| `execution_mode` | Yes | `AUTONOMOUS` under `:auto` | No |\n| `continuation_choice` | No | none | Yes, only when handoff and indexed continuity disagree |\n| `artifact_recovery_choice` | No | `continue_anyway` under resume auto mode | No |\n| `memory_choice` | No | `fast` | No |\n| `artifacts_valid` | Yes | auto-detect | No |\n| `continuity_sources_available` | No | auto-detect | No |\n\n### Consolidated Prompt Template\n\n```text\nSpecKit Resume setup\n\nQ0. Spec Folder, if not detected or provided: A) List and select  B) Start new with /speckit:complete  C) Cancel  E) Phase folder\nQ1. Confirm Detected Session, if auto-detected: A) Yes, resume  B) Select different folder  C) Cancel\nQ2. Continuation Validation, if handoff and indexed continuity disagree: A) Use handoff  B) Use indexed continuity  C) Investigate first\nQ3. Missing Artifacts, if required artifacts are incomplete: A) Run /speckit:plan  B) Select different folder  C) Continue anyway\nQ4. Recovery Depth, when the canonical packet is thin: A) Fast resume  B) Fill missing next step or blockers  C) Deeper context  D) Canonical artifacts only\n\nReply format: \"A, A\" or \"A, A, B\".\n```\n\nNever split these questions into separate visible prompts. Prefer the canonical file ladder before supplemental memory enrichment.\n\n### Auto Fail-Fast Display\n\n```text\nSpecKit Resume auto setup failed\nMissing required inputs: [field-list]\nProvide a spec folder or rerun with :confirm.\nSTATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"missing required setup inputs\"\n```\n\n## 2. Dashboard Layout\n\n```text\nSPECKIT RESUME DASHBOARD\nSpec: [spec_path]\nMode: [AUTONOMOUS|INTERACTIVE]\nDetection: [provided|phase-folder|ranked|none]\nArtifacts: spec.md [status] | plan.md [status] | tasks.md [status]\nContinuity source: [handover|continuity|spec_docs|memory_context|memory_search|combined]\nProgress: [done]/[total] tasks | checklist [done]/[total]\nConfidence: [high|medium|low]\nNext: [next safe action]\n```\n\n### Session Selection Panel\n\n```text\nFound session candidate\nSpec: [spec_path]\nLast activity: [timestamp]\nArtifacts valid: [yes|partial|no]\nResume this session? [Confirm / Select Different / Cancel]\n```\n\n### Recovery Depth Panel\n\n```text\nRecovery depth\nA) Fast resume - current brief is enough\nB) Fill missing next step / blockers - target only missing essentials\nC) Deep context - enrich the canonical packet if essentials remain thin\nD) Artifacts only - use handover, continuity, and spec docs without extra memory\n```\n\n### Stale Session Warning\n\n```text\nStale session warning\nLast activity: [date]\nContext may be outdated.\nA) Resume anyway  B) Fresh start  C) Review first  D) Cancel\n```\n\n## 3. Results Display\n\n### Resume Brief\n\n```text\nRESUME BRIEF\nSpec: [path]\nConfidence: [high|medium|low] | Source: [handover|continuity|spec_docs|mcp_enrichment|combined]\nNow: [phase/current task]\nLast confirmed: [action]\nNext safe action: [action]\nBlockers: [none|details]\nProgress: [X]% ([done]/[total] tasks)\nWhy this is next: [short reason based on tasks/checklist/memory]\n```\n\n### No Session\n\n```text\nNo active SpecKit session found.\nProvide a spec folder path or start a new packet with /speckit:complete.\nSTATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"no active session\"\n```\n\n### Next-Step Suggestions\n\n| Condition | Suggested Command | Reason |\n|-----------|-------------------|--------|\n| Planning incomplete | `/speckit:plan [feature-description]` | Complete planning phase |\n| Ready to implement | `/speckit:implement [spec-folder-path]` | Continue implementation |\n| Implementation in progress | Continue from last task | Resume where work stopped |\n| Need broader history | `/memory:search history [spec-folder]` | Inspect prior context |\n| Ending again | `/memory:save [spec-folder-path]` | Refresh continuity before pausing |\n\nEnd interactive presentations with: `What would you like to do next?`","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":144,"totalLines":144,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_resume_presentation.md","time":{"start":1781143450883,"end":1781143450885}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0b7ed97bb5d36a2d016a2a179acbe48191b28b998d84dc99ab"}},"id":"prt_eb46c34ee001C4jg011PTD51EP","sessionID":"ses_14b95d46bffeZ6ztCn3DXZD284","messageID":"msg_eb46c0b25001ymBwM0jF2Snl5R"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781143450896,"sessionID":"ses_14b95d46bffeZ6ztCn3DXZD284","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_FetbdzIbUvucGq2O7oudEcUS","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_implement_presentation.md","offset":1,"limit":150},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_implement_presentation.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # SpecKit Implement Presentation Contract\n2: \n3: Presentation source of truth for `/speckit:implement`. The command router owns only mode selection and asset loading. Workflow YAML owns execution. This file owns visible prompts, dashboard layout, and final result displays.\n4: \n5: ## 1. Startup Presentation\n6: \n7: For `:confirm` or no suffix, the consolidated setup prompt is the first visible response after lightweight read-only prerequisite discovery. Ask all applicable questions once, then wait.\n8: \n9: For `:auto`, do not show the consolidated prompt by default. Resolve setup through the auto-mode table below. Ask targeted questions only for fields marked Tier 2.\n10: \n11: ### Auto Pre-Bound Setup Answers\n12: \n13: ```yaml\n14: PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:\n15:   spec_folder: <spec-folder>\n16:   phase_folder: \"\"\n17:   confirm_choice: yes\n18:   execution_mode: AUTONOMOUS\n19:   dispatch_mode: single_agent\n20:   memory_choice: skip\n21:   resume_choice: resume\n22:   prerequisites_valid: true\n23: ```\n24: \n25: Unknown fields warn. Malformed lines are parse errors. Marker values override flags; omitted fields fall back to defaults.\n26: \n27: ### Auto Resolution Table\n28: \n29: | Field | Required | Default | Tier 2 |\n30: |-------|----------|---------|--------|\n31: | `spec_folder` | Yes | none | Yes, when multiple viable folders are detected |\n32: | `phase_folder` | No | none | No |\n33: | `confirm_choice` | Yes | `yes` when prerequisites are valid | No |\n34: | `execution_mode` | Yes | `AUTONOMOUS` under `:auto` | No |\n35: | `dispatch_mode` | Yes | `single_agent` | No |\n36: | `memory_choice` | No | `skip` when no prior continuity exists | No |\n37: | `resume_choice` | No | none | Yes, only when an incomplete-session warning is present |\n38: | `prerequisites_valid` | Yes | auto-detect from artifacts | No |\n39: \n40: ### Consolidated Prompt Template\n41: \n42: ```text\n43: SpecKit Implement setup\n44: \n45: Q0. Spec Folder, if not provided: choose an existing folder with plan.md or provide a phase folder.\n46: Q1. Confirm Spec Folder, if path provided: A) Yes, implement  B) Different folder  C) Cancel and plan first\n47: Q2. Execution Mode, if no suffix: A) Autonomous  B) Interactive\n48: Q3. Dispatch Mode: A) Single Agent  B) Multi-Agent (1+2)  C) Multi-Agent (1+3)\n49: Q4. Prior Work Context, only when prior records exist: A) Latest  B) Recent 3  C) Skip\n50: Q5. Incomplete Session, only when detected: A) Resume  B) Restart  C) Cancel\n51: \n52: Reply format: \"specs/example/, A, A, B\" or \"A, A, A, C\".\n53: ```\n54: \n55: Never split these questions into separate visible prompts. Missing `spec.md` or `plan.md` redirects to planning before implementation begins.\n56: \n57: ### Auto Fail-Fast Display\n58: \n59: ```text\n60: SpecKit Implement auto setup failed\n61: Missing required inputs: [field-list]\n62: Provide the missing inputs or rerun with :confirm.\n63: STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"missing required setup inputs\"\n64: ```\n65: \n66: ## 2. Dashboard Layout\n67: \n68: ```text\n69: SPECKIT IMPLEMENT DASHBOARD\n70: Spec: [spec_path]\n71: Mode: [AUTONOMOUS|INTERACTIVE]\n72: Step: [current] / 9 - [step name]\n73: Prerequisites: spec.md [status] | plan.md [status] | tasks.md [status] | checklist.md [status]\n74: Task progress: [done]/[total] complete\n75: Quality gate: [not-run|pass|blocked]\n76: Current blocker: [none|details]\n77: Next: [next action]\n78: ```\n79: \n80: ### Debug Offer\n81: \n82: ```text\n83: Repeated failures detected on this task.\n84: Dispatch fresh-perspective debug? (y / continue manually / skip)\n85: Current error: [summary]\n86: Affected files: [paths]\n87: Attempts so far: [count]\n88: ```\n89: \n90: ### Completion Gate Panel\n91: \n92: ```text\n93: IMPLEMENTATION COMPLETION GATE\n94: Tasks complete: [done]/[total]\n95: Checklist P0: [all complete|blocked|n/a]\n96: Checklist P1: [complete|deferred with approval|blocked|n/a]\n97: Validation: [not-run|pass|fail]\n98: Summary: implementation-summary.md [exists|missing]\n99: Context refresh: [complete|pending]\n100: ```\n101: \n102: ## 3. Results Display\n103: \n104: ### Success\n105: \n106: ```text\n107: SpecKit Implementation Complete - All 9 steps executed.\n108: Artifacts: tasks.md, implementation-summary.md, nested changelog when applicable, continuity refreshed in canonical spec docs\n109: STATUS=OK PATH=[spec-folder-path]\n110: ```\n111: \n112: ### Failure\n113: \n114: ```text\n115: SpecKit Implementation Failed\n116: Error: [description] | Step: [number]\n117: STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"[message]\"\n118: ```\n119: \n120: ### Next-Step Suggestions\n121: \n122: | Condition | Suggested Command | Reason |\n123: |-----------|-------------------|--------|\n124: | Need runtime verification | Use the project-specific verification command | Confirm behavior |\n125: | Need continuity refresh | `/memory:save [spec-folder-path]` | Refresh indexed canonical continuity |\n126: | Repeated failures | User-dispatched debug pass | Fresh root-cause analysis |\n127: | Need crash recovery | `/speckit:resume` | Recover session state |\n128: \n129: End interactive presentations with: `What would you like to do next?`\n\n(End of file - total 129 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# SpecKit Implement Presentation Contract\n\nPresentation source of truth for `/speckit:implement`. The command router owns only mode selection and asset loading. Workflow YAML owns execution. This file owns visible prompts, dashboard layout, and final result displays.\n\n## 1. Startup Presentation\n\nFor `:confirm` or no suffix, the consolidated setup prompt is the first visible response after lightweight read-only prerequisite discovery. Ask all applicable questions once, then wait.\n\nFor `:auto`, do not show the consolidated prompt by default. Resolve setup through the auto-mode table below. Ask targeted questions only for fields marked Tier 2.\n\n### Auto Pre-Bound Setup Answers\n\n```yaml\nPRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:\n  spec_folder: <spec-folder>\n  phase_folder: \"\"\n  confirm_choice: yes\n  execution_mode: AUTONOMOUS\n  dispatch_mode: single_agent\n  memory_choice: skip","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_implement_presentation.md","text":"# SpecKit Implement Presentation Contract\n\nPresentation source of truth for `/speckit:implement`. The command router owns only mode selection and asset loading. Workflow YAML owns execution. This file owns visible prompts, dashboard layout, and final result displays.\n\n## 1. Startup Presentation\n\nFor `:confirm` or no suffix, the consolidated setup prompt is the first visible response after lightweight read-only prerequisite discovery. Ask all applicable questions once, then wait.\n\nFor `:auto`, do not show the consolidated prompt by default. Resolve setup through the auto-mode table below. Ask targeted questions only for fields marked Tier 2.\n\n### Auto Pre-Bound Setup Answers\n\n```yaml\nPRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:\n  spec_folder: <spec-folder>\n  phase_folder: \"\"\n  confirm_choice: yes\n  execution_mode: AUTONOMOUS\n  dispatch_mode: single_agent\n  memory_choice: skip\n  resume_choice: resume\n  prerequisites_valid: true\n```\n\nUnknown fields warn. Malformed lines are parse errors. Marker values override flags; omitted fields fall back to defaults.\n\n### Auto Resolution Table\n\n| Field | Required | Default | Tier 2 |\n|-------|----------|---------|--------|\n| `spec_folder` | Yes | none | Yes, when multiple viable folders are detected |\n| `phase_folder` | No | none | No |\n| `confirm_choice` | Yes | `yes` when prerequisites are valid | No |\n| `execution_mode` | Yes | `AUTONOMOUS` under `:auto` | No |\n| `dispatch_mode` | Yes | `single_agent` | No |\n| `memory_choice` | No | `skip` when no prior continuity exists | No |\n| `resume_choice` | No | none | Yes, only when an incomplete-session warning is present |\n| `prerequisites_valid` | Yes | auto-detect from artifacts | No |\n\n### Consolidated Prompt Template\n\n```text\nSpecKit Implement setup\n\nQ0. Spec Folder, if not provided: choose an existing folder with plan.md or provide a phase folder.\nQ1. Confirm Spec Folder, if path provided: A) Yes, implement  B) Different folder  C) Cancel and plan first\nQ2. Execution Mode, if no suffix: A) Autonomous  B) Interactive\nQ3. Dispatch Mode: A) Single Agent  B) Multi-Agent (1+2)  C) Multi-Agent (1+3)\nQ4. Prior Work Context, only when prior records exist: A) Latest  B) Recent 3  C) Skip\nQ5. Incomplete Session, only when detected: A) Resume  B) Restart  C) Cancel\n\nReply format: \"specs/example/, A, A, B\" or \"A, A, A, C\".\n```\n\nNever split these questions into separate visible prompts. Missing `spec.md` or `plan.md` redirects to planning before implementation begins.\n\n### Auto Fail-Fast Display\n\n```text\nSpecKit Implement auto setup failed\nMissing required inputs: [field-list]\nProvide the missing inputs or rerun with :confirm.\nSTATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"missing required setup inputs\"\n```\n\n## 2. Dashboard Layout\n\n```text\nSPECKIT IMPLEMENT DASHBOARD\nSpec: [spec_path]\nMode: [AUTONOMOUS|INTERACTIVE]\nStep: [current] / 9 - [step name]\nPrerequisites: spec.md [status] | plan.md [status] | tasks.md [status] | checklist.md [status]\nTask progress: [done]/[total] complete\nQuality gate: [not-run|pass|blocked]\nCurrent blocker: [none|details]\nNext: [next action]\n```\n\n### Debug Offer\n\n```text\nRepeated failures detected on this task.\nDispatch fresh-perspective debug? (y / continue manually / skip)\nCurrent error: [summary]\nAffected files: [paths]\nAttempts so far: [count]\n```\n\n### Completion Gate Panel\n\n```text\nIMPLEMENTATION COMPLETION GATE\nTasks complete: [done]/[total]\nChecklist P0: [all complete|blocked|n/a]\nChecklist P1: [complete|deferred with approval|blocked|n/a]\nValidation: [not-run|pass|fail]\nSummary: implementation-summary.md [exists|missing]\nContext refresh: [complete|pending]\n```\n\n## 3. Results Display\n\n### Success\n\n```text\nSpecKit Implementation Complete - All 9 steps executed.\nArtifacts: tasks.md, implementation-summary.md, nested changelog when applicable, continuity refreshed in canonical spec docs\nSTATUS=OK PATH=[spec-folder-path]\n```\n\n### Failure\n\n```text\nSpecKit Implementation Failed\nError: [description] | Step: [number]\nSTATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"[message]\"\n```\n\n### Next-Step Suggestions\n\n| Condition | Suggested Command | Reason |\n|-----------|-------------------|--------|\n| Need runtime verification | Use the project-specific verification command | Confirm behavior |\n| Need continuity refresh | `/memory:save [spec-folder-path]` | Refresh indexed canonical continuity |\n| Repeated failures | User-dispatched debug pass | Fresh root-cause analysis |\n| Need crash recovery | `/speckit:resume` | Recover session state |\n\nEnd interactive presentations with: `What would you like to do next?`","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":129,"totalLines":129,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_implement_presentation.md","time":{"start":1781143450893,"end":1781143450895}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0b7ed97bb5d36a2d016a2a179acbec8191b0f1eef353a36a3b"}},"id":"prt_eb46c35060011fG3XVNgzODnY4","sessionID":"ses_14b95d46bffeZ6ztCn3DXZD284","messageID":"msg_eb46c0b25001ymBwM0jF2Snl5R"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781143450995,"sessionID":"ses_14b95d46bffeZ6ztCn3DXZD284","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_dq5hbSsfok7V3J9pByv7DpEl","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/speckit/implement.md","offset":1,"limit":90},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/speckit/implement.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: description: Implementation workflow (9 steps): execute pre-planned work. Requires plan.md. Modes :auto, :confirm.\n3: argument-hint: \"<spec-folder> [:auto|:confirm] [--phase-folder=<path>] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\n4: allowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, memory_context, memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_save, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan\n5: ---\n6: \n7: # SpecKit Implement\n8: \n9: Thin router for implementing an already planned SpecKit packet. This command resolves mode and target folder, loads the presentation contract, then executes the owned workflow YAML.\n10: \n11: ## 1. Router Contract\n12: \n13: Do not dispatch agents from this Markdown file. Agent dispatch, implementation steps, debug offers, review gates, and context-save behavior are owned by the workflow YAML assets.\n14: \n15: Load the presentation contract before showing startup questions, checkpoints, dashboards, success output, failure output, or next-step prompts.\n16: \n17: ## 2. Owned Assets\n18: \n19: | Purpose | Asset |\n20: |---------|-------|\n21: | Presentation source of truth | `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_implement_presentation.md` |\n22: | Auto workflow | `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_implement_auto.yaml` |\n23: | Confirm workflow | `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_implement_confirm.yaml` |\n24: \n25: No workflow-asset gap exists for this command.\n26: \n27: ## 3. Mode Routing\n28: \n29: 1. Parse `$ARGUMENTS` for `:auto` or `:confirm`.\n30: 2. Treat `--phase-folder` and the positional spec-folder path as workflow inputs.\n31: 3. If no mode suffix is present, use the presentation contract's startup prompt to ask for execution mode.\n32: 4. For `:auto`, resolve required setup inputs using the presentation contract's auto-resolution rules before loading YAML.\n33: 5. Validate that the target has the required planning artifacts before executing the workflow asset.\n34: 6. Load the selected workflow asset and execute it step by step.\n35: \n36: ## 4. Execution Targets\n37: \n38: | Mode | Workflow |\n39: |------|----------|\n40: | `:auto` | `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_implement_auto.yaml` |\n41: | `:confirm` or interactive choice | `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_implement_confirm.yaml` |\n42: \n43: ## 5. Presentation Boundary\n44: \n45: The following content lives only in `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_implement_presentation.md`:\n46: \n47: - Startup-question wording and reply format.\n48: - `:auto` pre-bound setup answer schema, default table, targeted-ask rules, and fail-fast display.\n49: - Prerequisite, quality-gate, debug-offer, review, and closeout dashboards.\n50: - Success and failure result templates.\n51: - Next-step suggestions and final user prompt wording.\n52: \n53: ## 6. Workflow Summary\n54: \n55: The YAML workflow requires prior planning artifacts, executes implementation tasks, verifies checklist evidence, writes completion artifacts, refreshes context, and closes the implementation pass.\n\n(End of file - total 55 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ndescription: Implementation workflow (9 steps): execute pre-planned work. Requires plan.md. Modes :auto, :confirm.\nargument-hint: \"<spec-folder> [:auto|:confirm] [--phase-folder=<path>] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, memory_context, memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_save, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan\n---\n\n# SpecKit Implement\n\nThin router for implementing an already planned SpecKit packet. This command resolves mode and target folder, loads the presentation contract, then executes the owned workflow YAML.\n\n## 1. Router Contract\n\nDo not dispatch agents from this Markdown file. Agent dispatch, implementation steps, debug offers, review gates, and context-save behavior are owned by the workflow YAML assets.\n\nLoad the presentation contract before showing startup questions, checkpoints, dashboards, success output, failure output, or next-step prompts.\n\n## 2. Owned Assets\n\n| Purpose | Asset |\n|---------|-------|","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/speckit/implement.md","text":"---\ndescription: Implementation workflow (9 steps): execute pre-planned work. Requires plan.md. Modes :auto, :confirm.\nargument-hint: \"<spec-folder> [:auto|:confirm] [--phase-folder=<path>] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, memory_context, memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_save, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan\n---\n\n# SpecKit Implement\n\nThin router for implementing an already planned SpecKit packet. This command resolves mode and target folder, loads the presentation contract, then executes the owned workflow YAML.\n\n## 1. Router Contract\n\nDo not dispatch agents from this Markdown file. Agent dispatch, implementation steps, debug offers, review gates, and context-save behavior are owned by the workflow YAML assets.\n\nLoad the presentation contract before showing startup questions, checkpoints, dashboards, success output, failure output, or next-step prompts.\n\n## 2. Owned Assets\n\n| Purpose | Asset |\n|---------|-------|\n| Presentation source of truth | `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_implement_presentation.md` |\n| Auto workflow | `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_implement_auto.yaml` |\n| Confirm workflow | `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_implement_confirm.yaml` |\n\nNo workflow-asset gap exists for this command.\n\n## 3. Mode Routing\n\n1. Parse `$ARGUMENTS` for `:auto` or `:confirm`.\n2. Treat `--phase-folder` and the positional spec-folder path as workflow inputs.\n3. If no mode suffix is present, use the presentation contract's startup prompt to ask for execution mode.\n4. For `:auto`, resolve required setup inputs using the presentation contract's auto-resolution rules before loading YAML.\n5. Validate that the target has the required planning artifacts before executing the workflow asset.\n6. Load the selected workflow asset and execute it step by step.\n\n## 4. Execution Targets\n\n| Mode | Workflow |\n|------|----------|\n| `:auto` | `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_implement_auto.yaml` |\n| `:confirm` or interactive choice | `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_implement_confirm.yaml` |\n\n## 5. Presentation Boundary\n\nThe following content lives only in `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_implement_presentation.md`:\n\n- Startup-question wording and reply format.\n- `:auto` pre-bound setup answer schema, default table, targeted-ask rules, and fail-fast display.\n- Prerequisite, quality-gate, debug-offer, review, and closeout dashboards.\n- Success and failure result templates.\n- Next-step suggestions and final user prompt wording.\n\n## 6. Workflow Summary\n\nThe YAML workflow requires prior planning artifacts, executes implementation tasks, verifies checklist evidence, writes completion artifacts, refreshes context, and closes the implementation pass.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":55,"totalLines":55,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/commands/speckit/implement.md","time":{"start":1