{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781143450995,"sessionID":"ses_14b95d46bffeZ6ztCn3DXZD284","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_ciLZht66HvjUd5qSFzR1HilF","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_complete_presentation.md","offset":1,"limit":150},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_complete_presentation.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # SpecKit Complete Presentation Contract\n2: \n3: Presentation source of truth for `/speckit:complete`. The command router owns only mode selection and asset loading. Workflow YAML owns execution. This file owns visible prompts, dashboard layout, and final result displays.\n4: \n5: ## 1. Startup Presentation\n6: \n7: For `:confirm` or no suffix, the consolidated setup prompt is the first visible response. Ask all applicable questions once, then wait. No analysis or tool calls precede the prompt unless the workflow already has an explicit path that needs read-only folder-state classification.\n8: \n9: For `:auto`, do not show the consolidated prompt by default. Resolve setup through the auto-mode table below. Ask targeted questions only for fields marked Tier 2.\n10: \n11: ### Auto Pre-Bound Setup Answers\n12: \n13: ```yaml\n14: PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:\n15:   feature_description: Add passwordless login\n16:   spec_folder: <spec-folder>\n17:   execution_mode: AUTONOMOUS\n18:   dispatch_mode: single_agent\n19:   memory_choice: skip\n20:   research_intent: add_feature\n21:   research_integration: false\n22:   context_integration: false\n23:   phase_decomposition: false\n24:   phase_count: 3\n25:   phase_names: \"\"\n26:   phase_folder: \"\"\n27:   selected_level: \"\"\n28:   start_state: \"\"\n29:   repair_mode: \"\"\n30:   record_relationships: false\n31:   depends_on: \"\"\n32:   related_to: \"\"\n33:   supersedes: \"\"\n34: ```\n35: \n36: Unknown fields warn. Malformed lines are parse errors. Marker values override flags; omitted fields fall back to defaults.\n37: \n38: ### Auto Resolution Table\n39: \n40: | Field | Required | Default | Tier 2 |\n41: |-------|----------|---------|--------|\n42: | `feature_description` | Yes | none | No |\n43: | `spec_folder` | Yes | none | Yes, when feature is present but folder choice is ambiguous |\n44: | `execution_mode` | Yes | `AUTONOMOUS` under `:auto` | No |\n45: | `dispatch_mode` | Yes | `single_agent` | No |\n46: | `memory_choice` | No | `skip` when no prior continuity exists | No |\n47: | `research_intent` | Yes | none | Yes |\n48: | `research_integration` | No | `false` | No |\n49: | `context_integration` | No | `false` | No |\n50: | `phase_decomposition` | Yes | `false` | No |\n51: | `phase_count` | No | `3` | No |\n52: | `phase_names` | No | none | No |\n53: | `phase_folder` | No | none | No |\n54: | `selected_level` | No | none | No |\n55: | `start_state` | No | auto-detect | No |\n56: | `repair_mode` | No | none | No |\n57: | `record_relationships` | No | `false` | No |\n58: | `depends_on` | No | none | No |\n59: | `related_to` | No | none | No |\n60: | `supersedes` | No | none | No |\n61: \n62: ### Consolidated Prompt Template\n63: \n64: ```text\n65: SpecKit Complete setup\n66: \n67: Mode: [auto|confirm|ask]\n68: Feature flags: [with-research yes/no] [with-context yes/no] [with-phases yes/no]\n69: \n70: Q0. Feature Description, if not provided: What feature should be built?\n71: Q1. Spec Folder: A) Use existing  B) Create new  C) Update related  D) Skip documentation  E) Phase folder\n72: Q2. Execution Mode, if no suffix: A) Autonomous  B) Interactive\n73: Q3. Dispatch Mode: A) Single Agent  B) Multi-Agent (1+2)  C) Multi-Agent (1+3)\n74: Q4. Prior Work Context, only when prior records exist: A) Latest  B) Recent 3  C) Skip\n75: Q5. Research Intent: A) add_feature  B) fix_bug  C) refactor  D) understand\n76: Q6. Phase Decomposition, if not already enabled: A) No  B) Yes\n77: Q7. Phase Count, if phase decomposition is enabled and not provided: default 3\n78: Q8. Phase Names, if phase decomposition is enabled and not provided: required literal slugs for concrete work areas\n79: \n80: If folder intake is required, include the intake interview in this same prompt.\n81: \n82: Reply format: \"B, A, A, C, A\" or \"Add auth, B, A, C, A\".\n83: ```\n84: \n85: Never split these questions into separate visible prompts.\n86: \n87: ### Auto Fail-Fast Display\n88: \n89: ```text\n90: SpecKit Complete auto setup failed\n91: Missing required inputs: [field-list]\n92: Provide the missing inputs or rerun with :confirm.\n93: STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"missing required setup inputs\"\n94: ```\n95: \n96: ## 2. Dashboard Layout\n97: \n98: ```text\n99: SPECKIT COMPLETE DASHBOARD\n100: Spec: [spec_path]\n101: Mode: [AUTONOMOUS|INTERACTIVE]\n102: Step: [current] / 14 - [step name]\n103: Optional flows: research=[on|off] context=[on|off] phases=[on|off]\n104: Planning artifacts: spec.md [status] | plan.md [status] | tasks.md [status] | checklist.md [status]\n105: Implementation: tasks [done]/[total] | P0 [status] | P1 [status]\n106: Validation: [not-run|pass|fail]\n107: Context refresh: [pending|complete]\n108: Next: [next action]\n109: ```\n110: \n111: ### Research Checkpoint\n112: \n113: ```text\n114: WORKFLOW CHECKPOINT - Research Complete\n115: Research phase complete. Created: research/research.md\n116: Continue to request analysis? [Y/n/review]\n117: ```\n118: \n119: ### Deep-Context Checkpoint\n120: \n121: ```text\n122: WORKFLOW CHECKPOINT - Deep-Context Complete\n123: Context Report: [spec_folder]/context/context-report.md\n124: Reuse candidates: [N] | Integration points: [N] | Conventions: [N]\n125: Continue to research or specification? [Y/continue, n/skip]\n126: ```\n127: \n128: ### Phase-Decomposition Checkpoint\n129: \n130: ```text\n131: WORKFLOW CHECKPOINT - Phase Decomposition Complete\n132: Parent: [parent_folder] | Phases: [N] children created\n133: Continue with first child ([first_child_folder])? [Y/n/review]\n134: ```\n135: \n136: ### Final Closeout Checkpoint\n137: \n138: ```text\n139: WORKFLOW CLOSEOUT\n140: Implementation summary: [exists|missing]\n141: Nested changelog: [written|not applicable|missing]\n142: Validation: [pass|fail]\n143: Continuity: [refreshed|pending]\n144: End workflow or refresh continuity first? [done|memory-save]\n145: ```\n146: \n147: ## 3. Results Display\n148: \n149: ### Success\n150: \n\n(Showing lines 1-150 of 175. Use offset=151 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# SpecKit Complete Presentation Contract\n\nPresentation source of truth for `/speckit:complete`. The command router owns only mode selection and asset loading. Workflow YAML owns execution. This file owns visible prompts, dashboard layout, and final result displays.\n\n## 1. Startup Presentation\n\nFor `:confirm` or no suffix, the consolidated setup prompt is the first visible response. Ask all applicable questions once, then wait. No analysis or tool calls precede the prompt unless the workflow already has an explicit path that needs read-only folder-state classification.\n\nFor `:auto`, do not show the consolidated prompt by default. Resolve setup through the auto-mode table below. Ask targeted questions only for fields marked Tier 2.\n\n### Auto Pre-Bound Setup Answers\n\n```yaml\nPRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:\n  feature_description: Add passwordless login\n  spec_folder: <spec-folder>\n  execution_mode: AUTONOMOUS\n  dispatch_mode: single_agent\n  memory_choice: skip\n  research_intent: add_feature","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_complete_presentation.md","text":"# SpecKit Complete Presentation Contract\n\nPresentation source of truth for `/speckit:complete`. The command router owns only mode selection and asset loading. Workflow YAML owns execution. This file owns visible prompts, dashboard layout, and final result displays.\n\n## 1. Startup Presentation\n\nFor `:confirm` or no suffix, the consolidated setup prompt is the first visible response. Ask all applicable questions once, then wait. No analysis or tool calls precede the prompt unless the workflow already has an explicit path that needs read-only folder-state classification.\n\nFor `:auto`, do not show the consolidated prompt by default. Resolve setup through the auto-mode table below. Ask targeted questions only for fields marked Tier 2.\n\n### Auto Pre-Bound Setup Answers\n\n```yaml\nPRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:\n  feature_description: Add passwordless login\n  spec_folder: <spec-folder>\n  execution_mode: AUTONOMOUS\n  dispatch_mode: single_agent\n  memory_choice: skip\n  research_intent: add_feature\n  research_integration: false\n  context_integration: false\n  phase_decomposition: false\n  phase_count: 3\n  phase_names: \"\"\n  phase_folder: \"\"\n  selected_level: \"\"\n  start_state: \"\"\n  repair_mode: \"\"\n  record_relationships: false\n  depends_on: \"\"\n  related_to: \"\"\n  supersedes: \"\"\n```\n\nUnknown fields warn. Malformed lines are parse errors. Marker values override flags; omitted fields fall back to defaults.\n\n### Auto Resolution Table\n\n| Field | Required | Default | Tier 2 |\n|-------|----------|---------|--------|\n| `feature_description` | Yes | none | No |\n| `spec_folder` | Yes | none | Yes, when feature is present but folder choice is ambiguous |\n| `execution_mode` | Yes | `AUTONOMOUS` under `:auto` | No |\n| `dispatch_mode` | Yes | `single_agent` | No |\n| `memory_choice` | No | `skip` when no prior continuity exists | No |\n| `research_intent` | Yes | none | Yes |\n| `research_integration` | No | `false` | No |\n| `context_integration` | No | `false` | No |\n| `phase_decomposition` | Yes | `false` | No |\n| `phase_count` | No | `3` | No |\n| `phase_names` | No | none | No |\n| `phase_folder` | No | none | No |\n| `selected_level` | No | none | No |\n| `start_state` | No | auto-detect | No |\n| `repair_mode` | No | none | No |\n| `record_relationships` | No | `false` | No |\n| `depends_on` | No | none | No |\n| `related_to` | No | none | No |\n| `supersedes` | No | none | No |\n\n### Consolidated Prompt Template\n\n```text\nSpecKit Complete setup\n\nMode: [auto|confirm|ask]\nFeature flags: [with-research yes/no] [with-context yes/no] [with-phases yes/no]\n\nQ0. Feature Description, if not provided: What feature should be built?\nQ1. Spec Folder: A) Use existing  B) Create new  C) Update related  D) Skip documentation  E) Phase folder\nQ2. Execution Mode, if no suffix: A) Autonomous  B) Interactive\nQ3. Dispatch Mode: A) Single Agent  B) Multi-Agent (1+2)  C) Multi-Agent (1+3)\nQ4. Prior Work Context, only when prior records exist: A) Latest  B) Recent 3  C) Skip\nQ5. Research Intent: A) add_feature  B) fix_bug  C) refactor  D) understand\nQ6. Phase Decomposition, if not already enabled: A) No  B) Yes\nQ7. Phase Count, if phase decomposition is enabled and not provided: default 3\nQ8. Phase Names, if phase decomposition is enabled and not provided: required literal slugs for concrete work areas\n\nIf folder intake is required, include the intake interview in this same prompt.\n\nReply format: \"B, A, A, C, A\" or \"Add auth, B, A, C, A\".\n```\n\nNever split these questions into separate visible prompts.\n\n### Auto Fail-Fast Display\n\n```text\nSpecKit Complete auto setup failed\nMissing required inputs: [field-list]\nProvide the missing inputs or rerun with :confirm.\nSTATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"missing required setup inputs\"\n```\n\n## 2. Dashboard Layout\n\n```text\nSPECKIT COMPLETE DASHBOARD\nSpec: [spec_path]\nMode: [AUTONOMOUS|INTERACTIVE]\nStep: [current] / 14 - [step name]\nOptional flows: research=[on|off] context=[on|off] phases=[on|off]\nPlanning artifacts: spec.md [status] | plan.md [status] | tasks.md [status] | checklist.md [status]\nImplementation: tasks [done]/[total] | P0 [status] | P1 [status]\nValidation: [not-run|pass|fail]\nContext refresh: [pending|complete]\nNext: [next action]\n```\n\n### Research Checkpoint\n\n```text\nWORKFLOW CHECKPOINT - Research Complete\nResearch phase complete. Created: research/research.md\nContinue to request analysis? [Y/n/review]\n```\n\n### Deep-Context Checkpoint\n\n```text\nWORKFLOW CHECKPOINT - Deep-Context Complete\nContext Report: [spec_folder]/context/context-report.md\nReuse candidates: [N] | Integration points: [N] | Conventions: [N]\nContinue to research or specification? [Y/continue, n/skip]\n```\n\n### Phase-Decomposition Checkpoint\n\n```text\nWORKFLOW CHECKPOINT - Phase Decomposition Complete\nParent: [parent_folder] | Phases: [N] children created\nContinue with first child ([first_child_folder])? [Y/n/review]\n```\n\n### Final Closeout Checkpoint\n\n```text\nWORKFLOW CLOSEOUT\nImplementation summary: [exists|missing]\nNested changelog: [written|not applicable|missing]\nValidation: [pass|fail]\nContinuity: [refreshed|pending]\nEnd workflow or refresh continuity first? [done|memory-save]\n```\n\n## 3. Results Display\n\n### Success\n","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":150,"totalLines":175,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_complete_presentation.md","time":{"start":1781143450983,"end":1781143450994}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0b7ed97bb5d36a2d016a2a179acbf08191b4e94fe10f389f96"}},"id":"prt_eb46c352a0018v3irdPW8WbHdR","sessionID":"ses_14b95d46bffeZ6ztCn3DXZD284","messageID":"msg_eb46c0b25001ymBwM0jF2Snl5R"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781143450996,"sessionID":"ses_14b95d46bffeZ6ztCn3DXZD284","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_dU4h5hmRkrJSD2qsSHJFGzvq","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/speckit/complete.md","offset":1,"limit":90},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/speckit/complete.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: description: End-to-end SpecKit workflow (14+ steps). Modes: :auto, :confirm, :with-research, :with-context, :with-phases.\n3: argument-hint: \"<feature-description> [:auto|:confirm] [:with-research] [:with-context] [:with-phases] [--phases N] [--phase-names list] [--phase-folder=<path>] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\n4: allowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, memory_context, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_save, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan\n5: ---\n6: \n7: # SpecKit Complete\n8: \n9: Thin router for the end-to-end SpecKit workflow. This command resolves mode and optional workflow flags, loads the presentation contract, then executes the owned workflow YAML.\n10: \n11: ## 1. Router Contract\n12: \n13: Do not dispatch agents from this Markdown file. Agent dispatch, workflow steps, research/context/phase insertion, artifact writing, validation, and context-save behavior are owned by the workflow YAML assets.\n14: \n15: Load the presentation contract before showing startup questions, checkpoints, dashboards, success output, failure output, or next-step prompts.\n16: \n17: ## 2. Owned Assets\n18: \n19: | Purpose | Asset |\n20: |---------|-------|\n21: | Presentation source of truth | `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_complete_presentation.md` |\n22: | Auto workflow | `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_complete_auto.yaml` |\n23: | Confirm workflow | `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_complete_confirm.yaml` |\n24: \n25: No workflow-asset gap exists for this command.\n26: \n27: ## 3. Mode Routing\n28: \n29: 1. Parse `$ARGUMENTS` for `:auto` or `:confirm`.\n30: 2. Treat `:with-research`, `:with-context`, `:with-phases`, `--phases`, `--phase-names`, and `--phase-folder` as workflow inputs, not execution modes.\n31: 3. If no mode suffix is present, use the presentation contract's startup prompt to ask for execution mode.\n32: 4. For `:auto`, resolve required setup inputs using the presentation contract's auto-resolution rules before loading YAML.\n33: 5. Load the selected workflow asset and execute it step by step.\n34: \n35: ## 4. Execution Targets\n36: \n37: | Mode | Workflow |\n38: |------|----------|\n39: | `:auto` | `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_complete_auto.yaml` |\n40: | `:confirm` or interactive choice | `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_complete_confirm.yaml` |\n41: \n42: ## 5. Presentation Boundary\n43: \n44: The following content lives only in `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_complete_presentation.md`:\n45: \n46: - Startup-question wording and reply format.\n47: - `:auto` pre-bound setup answer schema, default table, targeted-ask rules, and fail-fast display.\n48: - Research, deep-context, phase-decomposition, planning-gate, implementation, checklist, and closeout dashboards.\n49: - Success and failure result templates.\n50: - Next-step suggestions and final user prompt wording.\n51: \n52: ## 6. Workflow Summary\n53: \n54: The YAML workflow runs the full lifecycle from specification through implementation, validation, context refresh, and workflow closeout. Optional research, context, and phase-decomposition flows are routed through the selected workflow asset.\n\n(End of file - total 54 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ndescription: End-to-end SpecKit workflow (14+ steps). Modes: :auto, :confirm, :with-research, :with-context, :with-phases.\nargument-hint: \"<feature-description> [:auto|:confirm] [:with-research] [:with-context] [:with-phases] [--phases N] [--phase-names list] [--phase-folder=<path>] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, memory_context, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_save, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan\n---\n\n# SpecKit Complete\n\nThin router for the end-to-end SpecKit workflow. This command resolves mode and optional workflow flags, loads the presentation contract, then executes the owned workflow YAML.\n\n## 1. Router Contract\n\nDo not dispatch agents from this Markdown file. Agent dispatch, workflow steps, research/context/phase insertion, artifact writing, validation, and context-save behavior are owned by the workflow YAML assets.\n\nLoad the presentation contract before showing startup questions, checkpoints, dashboards, success output, failure output, or next-step prompts.\n\n## 2. Owned Assets\n\n| Purpose | Asset |\n|---------|-------|","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/speckit/complete.md","text":"---\ndescription: End-to-end SpecKit workflow (14+ steps). Modes: :auto, :confirm, :with-research, :with-context, :with-phases.\nargument-hint: \"<feature-description> [:auto|:confirm] [:with-research] [:with-context] [:with-phases] [--phases N] [--phase-names list] [--phase-folder=<path>] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, memory_context, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_save, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan\n---\n\n# SpecKit Complete\n\nThin router for the end-to-end SpecKit workflow. This command resolves mode and optional workflow flags, loads the presentation contract, then executes the owned workflow YAML.\n\n## 1. Router Contract\n\nDo not dispatch agents from this Markdown file. Agent dispatch, workflow steps, research/context/phase insertion, artifact writing, validation, and context-save behavior are owned by the workflow YAML assets.\n\nLoad the presentation contract before showing startup questions, checkpoints, dashboards, success output, failure output, or next-step prompts.\n\n## 2. Owned Assets\n\n| Purpose | Asset |\n|---------|-------|\n| Presentation source of truth | `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_complete_presentation.md` |\n| Auto workflow | `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_complete_auto.yaml` |\n| Confirm workflow | `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_complete_confirm.yaml` |\n\nNo workflow-asset gap exists for this command.\n\n## 3. Mode Routing\n\n1. Parse `$ARGUMENTS` for `:auto` or `:confirm`.\n2. Treat `:with-research`, `:with-context`, `:with-phases`, `--phases`, `--phase-names`, and `--phase-folder` as workflow inputs, not execution modes.\n3. If no mode suffix is present, use the presentation contract's startup prompt to ask for execution mode.\n4. For `:auto`, resolve required setup inputs using the presentation contract's auto-resolution rules before loading YAML.\n5. Load the selected workflow asset and execute it step by step.\n\n## 4. Execution Targets\n\n| Mode | Workflow |\n|------|----------|\n| `:auto` | `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_complete_auto.yaml` |\n| `:confirm` or interactive choice | `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_complete_confirm.yaml` |\n\n## 5. Presentation Boundary\n\nThe following content lives only in `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_complete_presentation.md`:\n\n- Startup-question wording and reply format.\n- `:auto` pre-bound setup answer schema, default table, targeted-ask rules, and fail-fast display.\n- Research, deep-context, phase-decomposition, planning-gate, implementation, checklist, and closeout dashboards.\n- Success and failure result templates.\n- Next-step suggestions and final user prompt wording.\n\n## 6. Workflow Summary\n\nThe YAML workflow runs the full lifecycle from specification through implementation, validation, context refresh, and workflow closeout. Optional research, context, and phase-decomposition flows are routed through the selected workflow asset.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":54,"totalLines":54,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/commands/speckit/complete.md","time":{"start":1781143450992,"end":1781143450996}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0b7ed97bb5d36a2d016a2a179acbfc8191895e27e193e701a9"}},"id":"prt_eb46c356e001amsz8M8lJAu6VE","sessionID":"ses_14b95d46bffeZ6ztCn3DXZD284","messageID":"msg_eb46c0b25001ymBwM0jF2Snl5R"}}
