{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1781143459084,"sessionID":"ses_14b95d46bffeZ6ztCn3DXZD284","part":{"id":"prt_eb46c550b001o12S0O5EnwN35h","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"08452c522195b926f57a49b1383e0fe07431f0ca","messageID":"msg_eb46c375e001VnCcVbK1SdXpZO","sessionID":"ses_14b95d46bffeZ6ztCn3DXZD284","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":169986,"input":9435,"output":224,"reasoning":71,"cache":{"write":0,"read":160256}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1781143460736,"sessionID":"ses_14b95d46bffeZ6ztCn3DXZD284","part":{"id":"prt_eb46c5b7d001noHo5iP2dtOXsd","messageID":"msg_eb46c55ea001lx550C9w7btHiF","sessionID":"ses_14b95d46bffeZ6ztCn3DXZD284","snapshot":"08452c522195b926f57a49b1383e0fe07431f0ca","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781143466207,"sessionID":"ses_14b95d46bffeZ6ztCn3DXZD284","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_ll4waRtjrkfSVm9jO0KOLitV","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/create/assets/create_skill_presentation.md","offset":1,"limit":150},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/create/assets/create_skill_presentation.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # /create:skill Presentation Contract\n2: \n3: This file is the single source of truth for user-facing presentation in `/create:skill`: startup questions, setup/status dashboards, operation display, and result templates. The command router owns asset routing only. The workflow YAML owns execution behavior.\n4: \n5: ## 1. Phase 0 Verification Display\n6: \n7: Run this automatic self-check before setup. This is not a user question.\n8: \n9: ```text\n10: SELF-CHECK: Are you operating as @markdown OR under a valid chained parent handoff?\n11: \n12: Case A: Valid chained handoff detected with --chained\n13: - Required parent fields: skill_name, operation, execution_mode, parent_create_agent_verified=true\n14: - type is required only for reference-only or asset-only\n15: - If all fields are present: create_agent_verified = skipped-chained; chained_handoff_valid = true\n16: - If fields are missing: chained_handoff_valid = false and continue to Case B\n17: \n18: Case B: Standalone invocation\n19: - Verify @markdown indicators and sk-doc validation behavior\n20: - If present: create_agent_verified = true; phase_0_status = PASSED\n21: - If missing or uncertain: hard block\n22: ```\n23: \n24: Hard-block message:\n25: \n26: ```text\n27: This command requires @markdown for template-first generation and sk-doc validation.\n28: Restart with: @markdown /create:skill <skill-name> [operation] [type]\n29: \n30: STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"Markdown agent required\"\n31: ```\n32: \n33: ## 2. Auto Setup Resolution\n34: \n35: For `:auto`, resolve setup using the system auto-mode contract, then load `create_sk_skill_auto.yaml` only when every required field is available.\n36: \n37: Pre-bound setup schema:\n38: \n39: ```yaml\n40: PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:\n41:   skill_name: my-skill\n42:   operation: full-create\n43:   type: workflow\n44:   skill_path: .opencode/skills/\n45:   execution_mode: AUTONOMOUS\n46:   spec_choice: new\n47:   spec_path: <spec-folder>\n48:   memory_choice: skip\n49:   chained_handoff_valid: false\n50: ```\n51: \n52: Default resolution table:\n53: \n54: | Field | Required | Resolves Via | Default | Tier-2 Candidate |\n55: | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n56: | `skill_name` | Yes | first positional token, marker, or chained parent value | none | No |\n57: | `operation` | Yes | second positional token, marker, or chained parent value | none | No |\n58: | `type` | Conditional | third positional token, marker, or chained value | none | Yes, when operation requires type |\n59: | `skill_path` | Yes | `--path`, marker, or default | `.opencode/skills/` | No |\n60: | `execution_mode` | Yes | `:auto`, `:confirm`, or marker | `AUTONOMOUS` under `:auto` | No |\n61: | `spec_choice` | Conditional | marker, chained value, or targeted choice | none | Yes, for full operations |\n62: | `spec_path` | Conditional | marker, derived from spec choice, or chained value | none | No |\n63: | `memory_choice` | No | marker, prior-work detection, or default | `skip` when no prior continuity exists | No |\n64: | `chained_handoff_valid` | No | `--chained` plus parent fields, marker, or default | `false` | No |\n65: \n66: ## 3. Consolidated Startup Prompt\n67: \n68: Ask one prompt containing only applicable questions. Do not split these questions across turns.\n69: \n70: ```text\n71: Before proceeding, please answer:\n72: \n73: Q0. Skill Name (if missing)\n74: Required format: hyphen-case.\n75: \n76: Q1. Operation (if missing)\n77: A) full-create - new skill end-to-end\n78: B) full-update - update existing skill and resources\n79: C) reference-only - create/update one reference document\n80: D) asset-only - create/update one asset document\n81: \n82: Q2. Type (only for reference-only or asset-only)\n83: For reference-only: workflow | patterns | debugging | tools | quick_ref\n84: For asset-only: template | lookup | example | guide\n85: \n86: Q3. Spec Folder (required for full-create/full-update)\n87: A) Existing\n88: B) New\n89: C) Update related\n90: D) Skip\n91: E) Phase folder\n92: \n93: For reference-only/asset-only:\n94: A) Attach existing spec path for continuity tracking\n95: B) Skip spec linkage\n96: \n97: Q4. Prior Work Context (when the existing spec has prior continuity)\n98: A) Load most recent spec-doc record\n99: B) Load up to 3 most recent spec-doc records\n100: C) Skip\n101: \n102: Q5. Execution Mode (if no :auto/:confirm suffix)\n103: A) Interactive (:confirm)\n104: B) Autonomous (:auto)\n105: ```\n106: \n107: Hard stops:\n108: \n109: - Do not infer missing operation or type from context.\n110: - Do not split setup across multiple prompts.\n111: - Do not continue with missing required fields for the selected operation.\n112: \n113: ## 4. Setup Dashboard\n114: \n115: | Field | Required | Rule | Value |\n116: | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n117: | `create_agent_verified` | Yes | `true` or `skipped-chained` | `[value]` |\n118: | `skill_name` | Yes | explicit, hyphen-case | `[value]` |\n119: | `operation` | Yes | one of four operation values | `[value]` |\n120: | `type` | Conditional | required for reference-only and asset-only | `[value]` |\n121: | `skill_path` | Yes | default if omitted | `[value]` |\n122: | `execution_mode` | Yes | `:auto` or `:confirm` | `[value]` |\n123: | `spec_choice` | Conditional | required for full-create and full-update | `[value]` |\n124: | `spec_path` | Conditional | required for A/B/C/E | `[value]` |\n125: | `memory_choice` | No | prior-work choice or skip | `[value]` |\n126: \n127: Proceed only when every required field validates.\n128: \n129: ## 5. Completion Result Template\n130: \n131: ```text\n132: Unified Skill Workflow Complete\n133: \n134: Skill: [skill_name]\n135: Operation: [operation]\n136: Type: [type or N/A]\n137: Mode: [:auto|:confirm]\n138: Target: [skill_root_or_target_file]\n139: \n140: Validation:\n141: - DQI: [score] ([band])\n142: - Hard minimum: 75\n143: - Operation target: [operation_target]\n144: \n145: Context:\n146: - Spec path: [spec_path or none]\n147: - Memory saved: [yes/no]\n148: - Memory indexed: [yes/no]\n149: \n150: STATUS=[OK|CANCELLED|FAIL] PATH=[skill_root_or_target_file]\n\n(Showing lines 1-150 of 151. Use offset=151 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# /create:skill Presentation Contract\n\nThis file is the single source of truth for user-facing presentation in `/create:skill`: startup questions, setup/status dashboards, operation display, and result templates. The command router owns asset routing only. The workflow YAML owns execution behavior.\n\n## 1. Phase 0 Verification Display\n\nRun this automatic self-check before setup. This is not a user question.\n\n```text\nSELF-CHECK: Are you operating as @markdown OR under a valid chained parent handoff?\n\nCase A: Valid chained handoff detected with --chained\n- Required parent fields: skill_name, operation, execution_mode, parent_create_agent_verified=true\n- type is required only for reference-only or asset-only\n- If all fields are present: create_agent_verified = skipped-chained; chained_handoff_valid = true\n- If fields are missing: chained_handoff_valid = false and continue to Case B\n\nCase B: Standalone invocation\n- Verify @markdown indicators and sk-doc validation behavior\n- If present: create_agent_verified = true; phase_0_status = PASSED","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/create/assets/create_skill_presentation.md","text":"# /create:skill Presentation Contract\n\nThis file is the single source of truth for user-facing presentation in `/create:skill`: startup questions, setup/status dashboards, operation display, and result templates. The command router owns asset routing only. The workflow YAML owns execution behavior.\n\n## 1. Phase 0 Verification Display\n\nRun this automatic self-check before setup. This is not a user question.\n\n```text\nSELF-CHECK: Are you operating as @markdown OR under a valid chained parent handoff?\n\nCase A: Valid chained handoff detected with --chained\n- Required parent fields: skill_name, operation, execution_mode, parent_create_agent_verified=true\n- type is required only for reference-only or asset-only\n- If all fields are present: create_agent_verified = skipped-chained; chained_handoff_valid = true\n- If fields are missing: chained_handoff_valid = false and continue to Case B\n\nCase B: Standalone invocation\n- Verify @markdown indicators and sk-doc validation behavior\n- If present: create_agent_verified = true; phase_0_status = PASSED\n- If missing or uncertain: hard block\n```\n\nHard-block message:\n\n```text\nThis command requires @markdown for template-first generation and sk-doc validation.\nRestart with: @markdown /create:skill <skill-name> [operation] [type]\n\nSTATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"Markdown agent required\"\n```\n\n## 2. Auto Setup Resolution\n\nFor `:auto`, resolve setup using the system auto-mode contract, then load `create_sk_skill_auto.yaml` only when every required field is available.\n\nPre-bound setup schema:\n\n```yaml\nPRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:\n  skill_name: my-skill\n  operation: full-create\n  type: workflow\n  skill_path: .opencode/skills/\n  execution_mode: AUTONOMOUS\n  spec_choice: new\n  spec_path: <spec-folder>\n  memory_choice: skip\n  chained_handoff_valid: false\n```\n\nDefault resolution table:\n\n| Field | Required | Resolves Via | Default | Tier-2 Candidate |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| `skill_name` | Yes | first positional token, marker, or chained parent value | none | No |\n| `operation` | Yes | second positional token, marker, or chained parent value | none | No |\n| `type` | Conditional | third positional token, marker, or chained value | none | Yes, when operation requires type |\n| `skill_path` | Yes | `--path`, marker, or default | `.opencode/skills/` | No |\n| `execution_mode` | Yes | `:auto`, `:confirm`, or marker | `AUTONOMOUS` under `:auto` | No |\n| `spec_choice` | Conditional | marker, chained value, or targeted choice | none | Yes, for full operations |\n| `spec_path` | Conditional | marker, derived from spec choice, or chained value | none | No |\n| `memory_choice` | No | marker, prior-work detection, or default | `skip` when no prior continuity exists | No |\n| `chained_handoff_valid` | No | `--chained` plus parent fields, marker, or default | `false` | No |\n\n## 3. Consolidated Startup Prompt\n\nAsk one prompt containing only applicable questions. Do not split these questions across turns.\n\n```text\nBefore proceeding, please answer:\n\nQ0. Skill Name (if missing)\nRequired format: hyphen-case.\n\nQ1. Operation (if missing)\nA) full-create - new skill end-to-end\nB) full-update - update existing skill and resources\nC) reference-only - create/update one reference document\nD) asset-only - create/update one asset document\n\nQ2. Type (only for reference-only or asset-only)\nFor reference-only: workflow | patterns | debugging | tools | quick_ref\nFor asset-only: template | lookup | example | guide\n\nQ3. Spec Folder (required for full-create/full-update)\nA) Existing\nB) New\nC) Update related\nD) Skip\nE) Phase folder\n\nFor reference-only/asset-only:\nA) Attach existing spec path for continuity tracking\nB) Skip spec linkage\n\nQ4. Prior Work Context (when the existing spec has prior continuity)\nA) Load most recent spec-doc record\nB) Load up to 3 most recent spec-doc records\nC) Skip\n\nQ5. Execution Mode (if no :auto/:confirm suffix)\nA) Interactive (:confirm)\nB) Autonomous (:auto)\n```\n\nHard stops:\n\n- Do not infer missing operation or type from context.\n- Do not split setup across multiple prompts.\n- Do not continue with missing required fields for the selected operation.\n\n## 4. Setup Dashboard\n\n| Field | Required | Rule | Value |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| `create_agent_verified` | Yes | `true` or `skipped-chained` | `[value]` |\n| `skill_name` | Yes | explicit, hyphen-case | `[value]` |\n| `operation` | Yes | one of four operation values | `[value]` |\n| `type` | Conditional | required for reference-only and asset-only | `[value]` |\n| `skill_path` | Yes | default if omitted | `[value]` |\n| `execution_mode` | Yes | `:auto` or `:confirm` | `[value]` |\n| `spec_choice` | Conditional | required for full-create and full-update | `[value]` |\n| `spec_path` | Conditional | required for A/B/C/E | `[value]` |\n| `memory_choice` | No | prior-work choice or skip | `[value]` |\n\nProceed only when every required field validates.\n\n## 5. Completion Result Template\n\n```text\nUnified Skill Workflow Complete\n\nSkill: [skill_name]\nOperation: [operation]\nType: [type or N/A]\nMode: [:auto|:confirm]\nTarget: [skill_root_or_target_file]\n\nValidation:\n- DQI: [score] ([band])\n- Hard minimum: 75\n- Operation target: [operation_target]\n\nContext:\n- Spec path: [spec_path or none]\n- Memory saved: [yes/no]\n- Memory indexed: [yes/no]\n\nSTATUS=[OK|CANCELLED|FAIL] PATH=[skill_root_or_target_file]","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":150,"totalLines":151,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/create/assets/create_skill_presentation.md","time":{"start":1781143466200,"end":1781143466206}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_05a22d8d0b49e51e016a2a17aa2bf881919388d6d71b9bcd09"}},"id":"prt_eb46c70d1001s8KNI1PAxiJ3Bv","sessionID":"ses_14b95d46bffeZ6ztCn3DXZD284","messageID":"msg_eb46c55ea001lx550C9w7btHiF"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781143466261,"sessionID":"ses_14b95d46bffeZ6ztCn3DXZD284","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_ZERpUXqlsjLij0iNWSjfPAZ2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/create/skill.md","offset":1,"limit":90},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/create/skill.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: description: Create or update OpenCode skills via one unified command with operation routing. :auto/:confirm.\n3: argument-hint: \"<skill-name> [operation] [type] [--path <dir>] [--chained] [:auto|:confirm] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\n4: allowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Glob, Grep, TodoWrite\n5: ---\n6: \n7: # /create:skill Router\n8: \n9: This command is a thin router. It separates execution routing from user-facing presentation.\n10: \n11: ## Routing Assets\n12: \n13: | Asset | Path | Purpose |\n14: | --- | --- | --- |\n15: | Presentation contract | `.opencode/commands/create/assets/create_skill_presentation.md` | Startup questions, setup dashboard, operation/status display, and completion template |\n16: | Auto workflow | `.opencode/commands/create/assets/create_sk_skill_auto.yaml` | Autonomous unified skill workflow execution |\n17: | Confirm workflow | `.opencode/commands/create/assets/create_sk_skill_confirm.yaml` | Interactive checkpointed unified skill workflow execution |\n18: \n19: ## Execution Order\n20: \n21: 1. Read `.opencode/commands/create/assets/create_skill_presentation.md`.\n22: 2. Run the presentation contract's Phase 0 verification and setup resolution.\n23: 3. Resolve operation from setup: `full-create`, `full-update`, `reference-only`, or `asset-only`.\n24: 4. Resolve execution mode from `$ARGUMENTS` or the setup answer: `:auto` or `:confirm`.\n25: 5. Load exactly one workflow YAML:\n26:    - `:auto` -> `.opencode/commands/create/assets/create_sk_skill_auto.yaml`\n27:    - `:confirm` or omitted mode -> `.opencode/commands/create/assets/create_sk_skill_confirm.yaml`\n28: 6. Execute the selected YAML step by step and route to the resolved operation branch.\n29: 7. Use the presentation contract, not this router, for user prompts, setup/status dashboards, and final result display.\n30: \n31: ## Routing Rules\n32: \n33: - This command is the canonical `/create:skill` entrypoint and uses the same workflow YAMLs as `/create:sk-skill`.\n34: - Do not edit workflow YAML while executing this command.\n35: - If any referenced asset is missing, stop and report the missing path.\n36: - The YAML owns workflow behavior; the presentation Markdown owns user-visible wording and layout.\n37: \n38: User request: {{args}}\n\n(End of file - total 38 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ndescription: Create or update OpenCode skills via one unified command with operation routing. :auto/:confirm.\nargument-hint: \"<skill-name> [operation] [type] [--path <dir>] [--chained] [:auto|:confirm] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Glob, Grep, TodoWrite\n---\n\n# /create:skill Router\n\nThis command is a thin router. It separates execution routing from user-facing presentation.\n\n## Routing Assets\n\n| Asset | Path | Purpose |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| Presentation contract | `.opencode/commands/create/assets/create_skill_presentation.md` | Startup questions, setup dashboard, operation/status display, and completion template |\n| Auto workflow | `.opencode/commands/create/assets/create_sk_skill_auto.yaml` | Autonomous unified skill workflow execution |\n| Confirm workflow | `.opencode/commands/create/assets/create_sk_skill_confirm.yaml` | Interactive checkpointed unified skill workflow execution |\n\n## Execution Order\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/create/skill.md","text":"---\ndescription: Create or update OpenCode skills via one unified command with operation routing. :auto/:confirm.\nargument-hint: \"<skill-name> [operation] [type] [--path <dir>] [--chained] [:auto|:confirm] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Glob, Grep, TodoWrite\n---\n\n# /create:skill Router\n\nThis command is a thin router. It separates execution routing from user-facing presentation.\n\n## Routing Assets\n\n| Asset | Path | Purpose |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| Presentation contract | `.opencode/commands/create/assets/create_skill_presentation.md` | Startup questions, setup dashboard, operation/status display, and completion template |\n| Auto workflow | `.opencode/commands/create/assets/create_sk_skill_auto.yaml` | Autonomous unified skill workflow execution |\n| Confirm workflow | `.opencode/commands/create/assets/create_sk_skill_confirm.yaml` | Interactive checkpointed unified skill workflow execution |\n\n## Execution Order\n\n1. Read `.opencode/commands/create/assets/create_skill_presentation.md`.\n2. Run the presentation contract's Phase 0 verification and setup resolution.\n3. Resolve operation from setup: `full-create`, `full-update`, `reference-only`, or `asset-only`.\n4. Resolve execution mode from `$ARGUMENTS` or the setup answer: `:auto` or `:confirm`.\n5. Load exactly one workflow YAML:\n   - `:auto` -> `.opencode/commands/create/assets/create_sk_skill_auto.yaml`\n   - `:confirm` or omitted mode -> `.opencode/commands/create/assets/create_sk_skill_confirm.yaml`\n6. Execute the selected YAML step by step and route to the resolved operation branch.\n7. Use the presentation contract, not this router, for user prompts, setup/status dashboards, and final result display.\n\n## Routing Rules\n\n- This command is the canonical `/create:skill` entrypoint and uses the same workflow YAMLs as `/create:sk-skill`.\n- Do not edit workflow YAML while executing this command.\n- If any referenced asset is missing, stop and report the missing path.\n- The YAML owns workflow behavior; the presentation Markdown owns user-visible wording and layout.\n\nUser request: {{args}}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":38,"totalLines":38,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/commands/create/skill.md","time":{"start":1781143466251,"end":1781143466259}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_05a22d8d0b49e51e016a2a17aa2c0c8191a4bd292038abcb87"}},"id":"prt_eb46c70fa00150ZNALfkPE8JRL","sessionID":"ses_14b95d46bffeZ6ztCn3DXZD284","messageID":"msg_eb46c55ea001lx550C9w7btHiF"}}
