{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781143482068,"sessionID":"ses_14b95d46bffeZ6ztCn3DXZD284","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_13iePsReN5znvDrOLvfcRuGc","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/create/assets/create_folder_readme_presentation.md","offset":1,"limit":70},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/create/assets/create_folder_readme_presentation.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # /create:folder_readme Presentation Contract\n2: \n3: This file is the single source of truth for user-facing presentation in `/create:folder_readme`: startup questions, setup/status dashboards, README/install display contracts, and result templates. The command router owns asset routing only. The workflow YAML owns execution behavior.\n4: \n5: ## 1. Phase 0 Verification Display\n6: \n7: Run this automatic self-check before setup. This is not a user question.\n8: \n9: ```text\n10: SELF-CHECK: Are you operating as the @markdown agent?\n11: \n12: Indicators:\n13: - Invoked with @markdown prefix\n14: - Template-first workflow capabilities are available\n15: - DQI scoring behavior is available\n16: - sk-doc skill integration is available\n17: \n18: If all indicators are present:\n19: - create_agent_verified = true\n20: - Continue to setup\n21: \n22: If any indicator is missing or uncertain:\n23: - Stop before loading workflow YAML\n24: - Display the hard-block message below\n25: ```\n26: \n27: Hard-block message:\n28: \n29: ```text\n30: MARKDOWN AGENT REQUIRED\n31: \n32: This command requires the @markdown agent for:\n33: - Template-first workflow\n34: - DQI scoring\n35: - sk-doc skill integration\n36: \n37: Restart with:\n38: @markdown /create:folder_readme [operation] [target]\n39: \n40: STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"Markdown agent required\"\n41: ```\n42: \n43: ## 2. Auto Setup Resolution\n44: \n45: For `:auto`, resolve setup using the system auto-mode contract, then load `create_folder_readme_auto.yaml` only when every required field is available.\n46: \n47: Pre-bound setup schema:\n48: \n49: ```yaml\n50: PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:\n51:   operation: readme\n52:   target_path: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit\n53:   readme_type: skill\n54:   project_name: semantic-search-mcp\n55:   platforms: all\n56:   output_path: install_guides/Tool - semantic-search-mcp.md\n57:   existing_file: false\n58:   existing_file_action: merge\n59:   execution_mode: AUTONOMOUS\n60: ```\n61: \n62: Default resolution table:\n63: \n64: | Field | Required | Resolves Via | Default | Tier-2 Candidate |\n65: | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n66: | `operation` | Yes | positional token, `--operation`, marker, or path-like default | `readme` for path-like target | Yes |\n67: | `target_path` | README only | README positional target or marker | none | No |\n68: | `readme_type` | README only | `--type`, marker, or targeted choice | none | Yes |\n69: | `project_name` | install only | install positional project name or marker | none | No |\n70: | `platforms` | install only | `--platforms`, marker, or targeted choice | none | Yes |\n\n(Showing lines 1-70 of 221. Use offset=71 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# /create:folder_readme Presentation Contract\n\nThis file is the single source of truth for user-facing presentation in `/create:folder_readme`: startup questions, setup/status dashboards, README/install display contracts, and result templates. The command router owns asset routing only. The workflow YAML owns execution behavior.\n\n## 1. Phase 0 Verification Display\n\nRun this automatic self-check before setup. This is not a user question.\n\n```text\nSELF-CHECK: Are you operating as the @markdown agent?\n\nIndicators:\n- Invoked with @markdown prefix\n- Template-first workflow capabilities are available\n- DQI scoring behavior is available\n- sk-doc skill integration is available\n\nIf all indicators are present:\n- create_agent_verified = true\n- Continue to setup","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/create/assets/create_folder_readme_presentation.md","text":"# /create:folder_readme Presentation Contract\n\nThis file is the single source of truth for user-facing presentation in `/create:folder_readme`: startup questions, setup/status dashboards, README/install display contracts, and result templates. The command router owns asset routing only. The workflow YAML owns execution behavior.\n\n## 1. Phase 0 Verification Display\n\nRun this automatic self-check before setup. This is not a user question.\n\n```text\nSELF-CHECK: Are you operating as the @markdown agent?\n\nIndicators:\n- Invoked with @markdown prefix\n- Template-first workflow capabilities are available\n- DQI scoring behavior is available\n- sk-doc skill integration is available\n\nIf all indicators are present:\n- create_agent_verified = true\n- Continue to setup\n\nIf any indicator is missing or uncertain:\n- Stop before loading workflow YAML\n- Display the hard-block message below\n```\n\nHard-block message:\n\n```text\nMARKDOWN AGENT REQUIRED\n\nThis command requires the @markdown agent for:\n- Template-first workflow\n- DQI scoring\n- sk-doc skill integration\n\nRestart with:\n@markdown /create:folder_readme [operation] [target]\n\nSTATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"Markdown agent required\"\n```\n\n## 2. Auto Setup Resolution\n\nFor `:auto`, resolve setup using the system auto-mode contract, then load `create_folder_readme_auto.yaml` only when every required field is available.\n\nPre-bound setup schema:\n\n```yaml\nPRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:\n  operation: readme\n  target_path: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit\n  readme_type: skill\n  project_name: semantic-search-mcp\n  platforms: all\n  output_path: install_guides/Tool - semantic-search-mcp.md\n  existing_file: false\n  existing_file_action: merge\n  execution_mode: AUTONOMOUS\n```\n\nDefault resolution table:\n\n| Field | Required | Resolves Via | Default | Tier-2 Candidate |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| `operation` | Yes | positional token, `--operation`, marker, or path-like default | `readme` for path-like target | Yes |\n| `target_path` | README only | README positional target or marker | none | No |\n| `readme_type` | README only | `--type`, marker, or targeted choice | none | Yes |\n| `project_name` | install only | install positional project name or marker | none | No |\n| `platforms` | install only | `--platforms`, marker, or targeted choice | none | Yes |","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":70,"totalLines":221,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/create/assets/create_folder_readme_presentation.md","time":{"start":1781143482064,"end":1781143482067}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0dbdb30c764c8305016a2a17b9fa30819198cc61c21fe11e97"}},"id":"prt_eb46caeaf001gpou5qkidVEmHb","sessionID":"ses_14b95d46bffeZ6ztCn3DXZD284","messageID":"msg_eb46c9484001wR0EvtfXvtPXaE"}}
